title: cheesy mixed veggies
directions: Cook veggies, then pour into dish.
Melt Cheez Whiz and soup together.
Pour over veggies.
Bake 1/2 hour at 300°.
Sprinkle can of onions over top.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: minestrone soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet and drain. Mix all ingredients together in a large pot. Simmer at least 30 minutes. We like a little more pasta, so we add 1 cup elbow macaroni and a little more water. Cornbread goes great with the soup! Hugs!!

title: pecan cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Fill a 6 cup ring mold. Chill until firm.
Yields 6 cups.

title: cheese ball by fannie
directions: Let cream cheese soften at room temperature for at least an hour. Stir cheese with fork until smooth. Add lemon juice, then mayonnaise and blend in. Chop only the green part of onions and add to mixture. Blend until smooth. Chop the ham by slicing both ways. Add to cheese mixture. Form into a ball. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill a few hours. Garnish with olives or nuts. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: fruited tea
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add tea bags and mint leaves; cover and steep for 6 minutes.
Discard tea bags. Combine tea mixture and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Let "set up" overnight in the refrigerator before serving.
This enhances the flavor.
Yield:
1 gallon.

title: play dough(eatable)
directions: In saucepan mix all ingredients, stirring constantly until mixture comes away from the side of pan.
Put on smooth surface and knead immediately.

title: missouri mud pie
directions: In a food processor or blender, process cookies until crumbly. Mix in melted butter.
Pat mixture into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch deep dish pie plate.

title: peanut butter ice cream sandwiches
directions: Put a small scoop of ice cream in the center of six of the peanut butter cookies.
Top each with one of the remaining six cookies.
Press gently, but firmly, together.
Press chopped nuts onto edges of cookie sandwiches.
Wrap in foil.
Freeze several hours before serving.

title: quick delicious casserole
directions: Brown the ground beef and drain.
Add soup and mix.
Add mashed potatoes on top of mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: irish cream
directions: Place all ingredients into a blender and whip thoroughly. Pour into a glass bottle and keep it in the refrigerator.
Use before the date shown on the fresh ingredients.

title: double chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350°.

title: one-pan tomato basil chicken
directions: In large skillet, saute rice mix as package directs.
Stir in 2 cups water, chicken and contents of seasoning package, bring to a boil over high heat.
Cover, reduce heat to low, simmer 10 minutes. Stir in broccoli, tomato and basil.
Cover, simmer 5 to 10 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed.
Sprinkle with cheese, if desired.
Serves 4.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all together.
Cook until red hots are melted.

title: caramel chip delight
directions: Follow baking directions on cake box.
Remove cake from oven when finished.
While warm, poke holes with fork in cake.
Pour caramel on top of cake.
Stir chocolate Cool Whip until smooth; layer on cake.
Sprinkle on chocolate Hershey bar.
Better eaten while caramel is warm, but can be refrigerated.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: In saucepan, cook broccoli with onion in chicken broth until tender. Do not drain. While broccoli is cooking, blend butter and flour in another saucepan. Stir in milk and cook until thick, stirring constantly. Add salt, pepper and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts. Add vegetables to mixture.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave cheese dip
directions: Microwave butter until melted.
Stir in onion.
Microwave for 2 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add cheese and tomatoes. Microwave 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Stir once during cooking time.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: zucchini drop cookies
directions: Thoroughly combine zucchini, soda, sugar and margarine.
Add egg.
Combine flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cranberry pudding pie
directions: Put the cranberries in the bottom of an 8-inch greased pie tin. Sprinkle the sugar and nuts over the berries.
Beat the margarine, melted shortening, sugar, egg and flour.
Beat well.
Pour batter over berries.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.
Serve with scoop of ice cream or whipped cream or sprinkle warm pie with powdered sugar.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Put all ingredients in large 3-quart pot.
Simmer on stove for 15 minutes.
Serve topped with shredded Cheddar cheese or sour cream.
Freezes well.
Good with nacho chips.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and take off bones and skin, cut into small pieces.
Place chicken into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix chicken broth and cream of chicken soup.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, melted margarine and milk until smooth. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.

title: chocolate covered mints
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into flat shapes the size of quarter and place on a cookie sheet.
Chill 1 hour.
Melt one 12 ounce bag semi-sweet chips and paraffin in a double boiler and dip to coat.
Place on waxed paper to dry.

title: sweet 'n' sour shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place sesame seed on baking sheet; bake 10 minutes or until golden brown.
In large skillet, over medium high heat, heat 2 tablespoons salad oil.
Add pepper strips and shrimp; saute 2 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Stir in sweet and sour sauce, pineapple, water chestnuts, green onions, 1/2 teaspoon salt and the sesame seed; heat through.
Serve over rice. If desired, garnish with green onions.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry devil's food bundt cake
directions: Bake in a greased and floured Bundt pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chopstick tuna casserole
directions: Combine mushroom soup and water.
Add chow mein noodles, celery, cashews, onion and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Place in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup chow mein noodles over top.
Bake at 375° in the oven for 15 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: meat filled pie (greek)
directions: Saute meats and onions in oil; season with salt, pepper and oregano.
Add tomato sauce and cook down until almost dry.
Remove from heat and add cheese and eggs.

title: turkey breast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rub butter on skin.
Season with paprika, salt and pepper.
Scatter onions over all sides.
Put turkey in roasting pan.
Pour wine and broth in bottom of pan (1/2 inch liquid in bottom).
Roast about 1 1/2 hours until 160° to 165° on meat thermometer or until liquid runs clear.
Baste during roasting.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage.
Place in a greased baking dish.
Brown beef and onion.
Stir in rice and place mixture on the cabbage.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Combine soup and water; pour over all.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salsa chip dip
directions: Cream together, with a fork, the cream cheese and salsa. Blend well.
Serve with chips.

title: un croque madame
directions: Smear bread with butter.
Put 1 piece into a hot skillet with the butter facing the bottom.
Put cheese and ham and bread (butter side up).
Brown both sides.
Fry an egg and put it on top of the grilled open-faced ham and cheese sandwich.

title: ozark pudding
directions: Beat egg well; add sugar, flour, salt and baking powder.
Add chopped apples and nuts.
Bake in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Pour milk into large bowl, add pudding mixes.
Beat 2 minutes. Let stand 5 minutes. Gently stir in 2 cups Cool Whip.
Cut the marble loaf into 1/2-inch cubes.
Arrange 1/2 of the cake cubes in 3 1/2-quart serving bowl.
Drizzle with 1/2 of chocolate syrup, layer with 1/2 of chopped candy bars and 1/2 of pudding mixture. Repeat layers, ending with pudding mixture. Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.
Makes 12 servings.

title: ham and cheese sandwiches
directions: Melt margarine and add other ingredients.
Spread mixture on dinner rolls and add slices of ham and Swiss cheese.
Place on cookie sheet and heat in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: quick and hearty tuna dinner
directions: In 4-quart saucepan put water, Lipton onion soup mix and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Gradually add uncooked noodles, then stir in green beans or broccoli.
If you use peas, add after noodles have cooked for about 5 minutes.
Return to a boil and cook and stir slowly over high heat for about 2 minutes.
Simmer covered, stirring occasionally, for 7 minutes.
Add tuna, cheese, pimento and heat until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sausage-apple stuffing
directions: Fry sausage slightly; do not drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix. Stuff a 2 1/2 pound pheasant.
Double recipe for 5 pound chicken or duck.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Combine margarine and sugar in a pan.
Cook over low heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add eggs to cooled mixture; add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add coconut and nuts to sugar mixture.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars while warm; remove from pan when cool.
Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Chop onions and celery.
Cook, along with other ingredients, until thick.
Stir often to prevent scorching.
Use low to medium heat.
You can use maple syrup if desired instead of brown sugar.

title: oreo ice cream cake
directions: Let ice cream soften while preparing crust.
Crush Oreos (reserving 1/4 to 1/2 cup crumbs).
Mix margarine and crumbs and pat evenly in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread ice cream on crust. Pour chocolate syrup over ice cream.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle nuts and reserved cookie crumbs on Cool Whip.
Keep in freezer.

title: nutty caramel corn
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and syrup.
Bring to
a boil over medium heat and cook 5 minutes. Add soda and stir.
In roasting pan, pour syrup mixture over popcorn.
Stir until popcorn is well coated. Bake, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
These muffins are better if allowed to ripen for 24 hours.

title: banana-pecan cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Pour buttermilk over bananas.
Mix shortening and eggs.
Add buttermilk and the shortening and eggs alternately to flour mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use tube pan.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Sift together flour, cocoa, coffee and baking soda.
Add alternately with buttermilk to sugar mixture.

title: spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, blend envelope of vegetable soup mix, container of sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Drain the frozen chopped spinach and squeeze out all the excess water and add to mix.
Drain and chop can of water chestnuts and add to mix.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix stir until well blended.
Chill for at least 1 hour and serve.

title: buffet beans
directions: Combine all ingredients except pork and beans.
Let stand 15 minutes; add pork and beans. Mix well.
Spoon into greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chocolate cobbler
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven. Mix flour, 3/4 cup sugar, 1 1/2 tablespoons cocoa, milk and vanilla in small mixing bowl.
Spoon this batter over margarine (don't mix margarine into batter).
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa together.
Sprinkle over batter.
Then pour boiling water on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Good to eat over ice cream.

title: beverly's sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in a double boiler.
Mix Bisquick and sausage. Add melted cheese.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls (1-inch). Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sausage balls will be browned. Yields 4 dozen.

title: summer veggie splash
directions: Cut cucumbers, tomatoes and squash up and mix together in a bowl.
Pour dressings over with salt and pepper.

title: orange carrots(method:  one pot)
directions: Heat butter in a large skillet.
Add sugar, orange juice and spices.
Cook for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add carrots; spoon sauce over them.
Cover with orange slices and cook, partially covered, until carrots are tender.
Baste frequently with liquid while cooking.

title: duffie's fishing camp broiled trout
directions: Dress and scale pan sized trout and cook whole.
Lay up to three fish on a
large piece of aluminum foil.
Squeeze one lemon on fish.
Add some	butter and Louisiana spice or paprika.	Fold aluminum foil good	and
tight
and
place	over hot charcoal fire for about 15
minutes.
Fish
should be done and tender by then. Serve on
plate.
Use fork to rake the tender fish from the bones. It is delicious.

title: oriental rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion (do not add salt).
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Stir at 1 hour.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: Mix vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper, paprika, ketchup and clove of garlic mashed well thoroughly; add green onions and celery. Dressing should be poured over cooked shrimp.
Marinate 4 to 5 hours.
Serve cold on shredded lettuce.

title: impossible pie
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and mix well.
Pour into 10-inch glass pie plate.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Good last minute dessert.

title: delicious apple pie(no sugar)
directions: Dissolve cornstarch in apple juice concentrate.
Combine with apples, salt and spice.
Simmer together until thickened.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Dot with margarine and add top crust. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or whipped topping.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Drain pineapple and peaches well.
Mix lemon juice and condensed milk.
Add fruit; fold in whipped topping.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and chill.
This may be frozen.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use an ungreased tube pan.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Mix walnuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Alternate batter and sugar mixture in tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Completely cool before removing from pan.
On plate right up, sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: *Or use 1 (16 ounce) bag frozen vegetable combination (broccoli, cauliflower and carrots), cooked and drained, and 1 cup cubed, cooked, peeled potato.

title: greek style beans
directions: Saute onions in bacon drippings.
Put beans in pan.
Add tomato sauce and cook very slowly, at least 1 hour (longer if possible). The longer and slower they cook, the better.
Pour the water in on 2 cans of beans; if that's all you need, drain the last can.

title: snow peas oriental
directions: Coat a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Add oil, and place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add snow peas and carrot. Saute 2 minutes.
Add water chestnuts and broth.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook onions in microwave 3 minutes until soft, but not done.
Spray large casserole dish with Pam.
Place zucchini in bottom of dish. Cover with onions.
Add tomato slices and season to taste.
Top with cheese.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking until zucchini reaches desired tenderness.

title: rumaki
directions: Wash and remove fiber from chicken livers.
Soak in soy sauce for 1 hour.
Cut chestnuts in slices.
Place 1 piece of chestnuts in the center of 1 piece of liver.
Wrap bacon around liver and chestnut.
Secure with wooden toothpick.
Place on ungreased baking dish, about 1/4-inch apart.
Bake at 350° until bacon is crisp. Serve hot with a salsa type dip.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, grapes, celery, nuts, nutmeg and a little salt if chicken isn't salted.
Stir in Hellmann's, whipped cream and add a little sugar gently.

title: bear stew with dumplings
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes.
Brown sliced onions in a stew pot along with the meat.
Add water and simmer until the meat is almost tender.
Add potatoes, carrots, turnips, celery, onions and bay leaves.
Salt and pepper to taste and cook until vegetables are done.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Put cereal in bowl; combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine.
Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth.
After 1 minute, stir in vanilla; pour over cereal.
Put in Ziploc bag with powdered sugar; shake, then pour onto wax paper to cool. Makes 9 cups.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together chicken, soup, vegetable and broth.
Salt and pepper to taste and place in a 9 x 11 baking dish.
Mix flour, margarine, milk and baking powder together, it will be soupy like pancake mix.
Pour on top of chicken mixture.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 425 degrees or until crust is brown and bubbly.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on side panel.
While noodles are cooking, beat egg yolk lightly with fork and add cream.
Melt butter.
Place drained hot noodles in warm serving bowl or platter.
Pour egg and cream mixture over noodles.
Add melted butter and half the grated cheese.
Toss noodles with fork and spoon until well blended, adding balance of cheese a little at a time while tossing.
Top with additional grated cheese, if desired.
Serve immediately.

title: dynamite dilly dip(kids cooking)
directions: Have a grown up slice the veggies into strips.
Kids can:

title: tutti-frutti ice cream
directions: Beat well eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add evaporated milk (chilled).
Blend.
Add pineapple, cherries and bananas.
Pour into freezer and add enough milk to fill freezer.

title: crispy oven fried mexican chicken
directions: In a large shallow glass pan combine V-8 juice, hot sauce and chicken.
Marinate 30 minutes at room temperature or cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Drain and discard marinade.

title: german slaw
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Then mix sugar, vinegar, turmeric and mustard.
Bring to a boil (until sugar is dissolved) and pour over cabbage.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours before serving.
Will keep several days.

title: hot fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; stir gently to mix.
Heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
May be served hot or cold.

title: melt-in-your-mouth blueberry cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to keep them stiff.
Cream shortening and vanilla.
Add remaining sugar gradually.
Add unbeaten egg yolks and beat until light and creamy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fold in beaten whites and blueberries.
Take a small amount of flour from recipe and shake on blueberries to keep them from settling. Place in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle top lightly with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta per package directions.
Rinse with cold water. Mix with dressing to taste.

title: raisin zucchini bread
directions: Finely shred zucchini to measure 2 cups; set aside.
Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs, zucchini and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder; mix well.
Add raisins and nuts to dry ingredients.
Combine with zucchini mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) greased and floured loaf pans.

title: polly day's pralines
directions: Combine sugar, baking soda, buttermilk and salt in heavy, deep pan.
Cook briskly for 5 minutes on high heat, stirring constantly with long handled wooden spoon.
Without ceasing the stirring process, add butter and pecans; continue cooking on high heat for an additional 5 minutes.
Test by dropping a dab in cold water. Unless mixture forms a soft ball, return to heat and cook another minute.

title: pizza dip
directions: Layer ingredients in pie plate as listed.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
We use this dip for nachos.
Very good.

title: spinach balls(makes 80 to 100)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Shape into balls (size is optional).
Put on cookie sheet in prepared oven until golden brown.
Serve hot.
These are delicious if you are having friends over for cocktails for the holidays or any type party or if you want something different with dinner.

title: marinated chicken kabobs
directions: Stir dressing, lemon juice and oil together.
Pour over chicken and vegetables; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate 3 hours.
Arrange on skewers.
Broil 3-inches from heat for 16 minutes or until cooked through.
Turn frequently.
Discard any remaining marinade.
Serves 4.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Stir first 5 ingredients; mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork.
Stir in nuts.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and the 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Scald milk with sugar and shortening.
Then add the yeast which has been dissolved thoroughly in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add 8 cups flour, mixing well.
Let rise until doubled in bulk.
Add salt, baking powder and soda.
Add enough flour, about 1 cup to make a soft dough.
Place in a bowl and grease top of dough. Cover.
Place in refrigerator.
Makes rolls as wanted, also can be used for doughnuts.
Will keep for a week, in refrigerator and makes 4 dozen.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add beef, chicken or pork (2 1/2 pounds) kabobs.
Marinate 24 hours.
Cook about 20 minutes on grill.
Put on skewers with peppers, onions and tomatoes.

title: quiche
directions: Beat mixture of all ingredients except meat and cheese.
Then folk in cheese and meat.
Bake pie shell for 5 minutes at 450° and then pour in mixture. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Remove skin from chicken and cut up. Place raw rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Salt and pepper to taste on chicken and rice. Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken. Add cream of mushroom soup mixed with water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: french silk pie
directions: In small bowl, beat sugar and butter 4 minutes or until fluffy.
Blend in cooled chocolate and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating on medium speed of electric mixer after each addition and scraping sides of bowl constantly.
Turn into baked pastry shell.
Chill several hours or overnight, until set. Garnish with whipped cream and chocolate curls, if desired.
Cover and chill.
Makes 10 servings.

title: shrimp chowder
directions: Begin 1 hour ahead.
In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium heat, in hot butter or margarine, cook onions until tender.
Add water, potatoes, salt and seasoned pepper.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender; do not drain.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Fold the pudding into the pineapple.
Add whipped topping, marshmallows and nuts.
Chill for 2 hours and serve.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in container with tight fitting lid.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons to a cup of boiling water.

title: basil vinaigrette chicken
directions: Coat chicken with mixture of flour, 1 teaspoon salad dressing mix and pepper. Heat 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet over medium heat. Add chicken and cook 4 to 5 minutes per side until cooked through. Remove to plate. Thinly slice peppers and coarsely chop onion. Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil to pan and add peppers and onion, stirring occasionally. Cook approximately 3 minutes or until browned. Stir in rest of salad dressing mix, cauliflower and 3/4 cup water. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer approximately 3 more minutes. Add chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and cook until cheese melts.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix in celery and onion.
Cook until soft and yellow.
Mix remaining dry ingredients together and add celery and onion.
Add eggs and broth.
Put in baking dish and bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.

title: jiffy macaroni and crab
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook macaroni until just tender, about 10 minutes.
Drain off water, leaving macaroni in pot.
Stir in lettuce, scallions, pimientos, crab, peas and carrots, sesame seed, vinegar, soy sauce, sesame oil and pepper. Toss to mix well.
Serve immediately or refrigerate and serve chilled.

title: icing
directions: Cook the milk, sugar and butter 4 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add the chocolate chips. Beat well.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti in 3-inch pieces and cook according to package instructions.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients to cooled spaghetti.
Mix.
Chill in covered dish, about 24 hours.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Fry bacon; remove from pan.
In bacon grease, fry potatoes, onion and green pepper until tender.
Crumble bacon and add to mixture.
Season to taste.

title: fruit salad
directions: Dump all cans of fruit and their juices into a large bowl. Slice and add bananas.
Gently stir in lemon juice and dry pudding mix.
Chill and serve.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and creamy.
Add egg and beat well again.
Sift flour, soda and cream of tartar together. Then add to creamed mixture.
When well blended add the vanilla and Rice Krispies.
Mix well.
Put in small heaps on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a preheated 350° oven until light brown.

title: calico beans
directions: Reserve most of grease, and add vinegar, brown sugar, dry mustard, salt, catsup and dash of garlic salt.
Stir together and mix with all the cans of beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham salad
directions: Mix ingredients and add Miracle
Whip to your taste for thickness.

title: orange julius
directions: Fill blender 1/3 full with orange juice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend until thoroughly mixed, rather slushy.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in oil, add mushrooms, olives, tomatoes, tomato paste, basil, oregano, garlic, Tabasco, and onions.
Cook the meat sauce an hour or more, the longer the better.
The noodles should be cooked almost dome and well drained.

title: antonia's red pepper appetizer
directions: Cook whole red peppers over grill or in 350° oven until tender.
Turn on sides to cook evenly.
When done, let cool.
Take skin off when cool enough to handle.
Discard seeds and stem.
In a large jar, place cooked red peppers and garlic in; cover with oil.
Keep in refrigerator.
Serve as an appetizer with Italian or French bread or crackers.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Wash and chop vegetables.
Arrange in the bottom of a roaster. Mix water, flour, salt and pepper.
Pour over vegetables.
Place roast on top of vegetable.
Spread horseradish all over roast. Roast covered in oven at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 30 minutes. Serve with Yorkshire Pudding.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups sugar, flour and cocoa in a heavy saucepan. Combine milk, egg yolks and melted oleo. Beat, using wire whisk, until well blended.

Gradually add milk mixture to sugar mixture, stirring until smooth. Cook chocolate mixture over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly (about 10 minutes). Spoon chocolate mixture into pastry shell. Set aside.

title: diet fruit and noodle pudding
directions: Grease 1-quart casserole with 1/2 teaspoon margarine; set aside.
In small bowl, combine prunes and boiling water; set aside.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo, add water and bouillon cubes.
Bring to boil.
Add noodles and cook until almost done.
Add broccoli, cook 5 minutes.
Add milk and cheese.
After cheese melts, let simmer, but do not boil, for a few minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Spray 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
In pan, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat both sides of beef, shaking off excess flour.
Set flour mixture aside. In nonstick skillet, heat 1 1/2 teaspoon oil; add beef.
Cook 5 minutes on each side until well browned.
Remove to baking dish. To drippings in skillet, add remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil; add mushrooms and onion and cook about 6 minutes until vegetables are lightly browned.
Transfer vegetables to baking dish.
Place reserved flour mixture in small bowl.
Using wire whisk or fork, gradually beat in beef broth and water.
Pour mixture over contents in baking dish, cover and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes until beef is tender.

title: diabetic - cooked pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake in pan, sprayed with Pam, at 350° for about 50 minutes, or until firm in middle.
This can also be used as a pie filling.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Whip eggs, cream and milk. Mix sugar, cornstarch and chocolate in saucepan. Stir in egg and milk mixture; cook over medium heat until mixture thickens. Remove from heat; add margarine and vanilla. Beat. Pour into a 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: tropical island punch
directions: (I freeze a mold of some of this mixture for the punch bowl.) Thaw concentrated juices.
Combine in a large container.
Add water and sugar.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill well.
Add ginger ale.
Pour all into punch bowl with crushed ice and the frozen mold.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together.
Add enough water to make frying easy.
Shape into desired size patties.
Fry in fat until lightly browned on both sides.
Yields 8 pancakes.

title: harlequin casserole
directions: Shred Cheddar cheese (makes 1 1/4 cups).
Save 1/4 cup for biscuits.
Melt butter in saucepan; blend in flour.
Gradually add tomato juice and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa together with egg yolks and mix the milk, gradually stirring and beating the mix so it won't lump, then put on burner and add butter and vanilla.
Cook until thick. Pour into baked pie shell.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Heat milk, butter and cheese until partially melted.
Pour over noodles.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hot cheese and pineapple dish
directions: Combine pineapple and cheese. Combine sugar and flour.
Stir sugar/flour into pineapple/cheese mixture.
Pour into baking dish. Combine crackers and butter.
Add to top of casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients.
Add rest and simmer for 2 hours.

title: bun bar(microwave candy)
directions: In a 4-cup measuring cup, add chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and peanut butter.
Pour 1/2 mixture into a wax paper lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put in freezer.
In the other half, add peanuts; set aside.
In a small mixing bowl, add pudding, milk and margarine.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove and stir. Blend well with mixer; add maple flavoring and powdered sugar. Stir together.
Take chocolate out of freezer; spread this mixture on top.
Top all with remaining chocolate/peanut mixture.
Place back into freezer for several hours.
Must be stored in refrigerator.

title: chocolate bird nests
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter together.
Crumble biscuits.
Add crumbled biscuits.
Form small nests.
Fill with jelly beans, M&M's or other candy.

title: romaine salad
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients together and pour over lettuce and strawberries.

title: kass's pecan lady finger cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into ladyfingers or roll into 1-inch balls and flatten slightly to no more than 1/4 to 1/2 thick.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes in 325° oven. Roll in powdered sugar when cooled.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease a 9-inch round cake pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup nuts. Dip biscuits in melted butter, then in cinnamon/sugar mix. Overlap biscuits 15 around, 5 in center.
Put apple slice between each biscuit.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: carrot chiffon pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar until thick; add mashed carrots, milk and seasonings.
Cook in top of double boiler until thick.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Stir into hot mixture. Beat egg whites stiff, add 1/2 cup sugar and mix well.
Add egg whites to hot carrot mixture and fold in.
Pour into cool pie shell and chill until firm.
Delicious served with whipped cream.

title: spoon burgers
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Add soup and 1/2 soup can of water, the mustard and the ketchup.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Spoon over hamburger buns.
Makes a quick and easy lunch or dinner and kids love it.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Slightly beat eggs.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat in remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done.
Cool and frost.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Shred cucumber and onion; blend together and drain well.
Mix with all remaining ingredients.

title: sweet chili
directions: Brown hamburger, sliced onions and sliced green pepper.
Mix rest of ingredients and cook.
Turn down heat to a simmer. Simmer as long as you prefer.

title: summer squash casserole *
directions: Wash, cut and boil squash until soft.
Mash.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix and pour into 2 1/2-quart greased (with margarine) baking dish.
Bake at 375° until brown (about 45 minutes).

title: dear abbey's pecan or walnut pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar and salt.
Melt butter and vanilla.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle pecans over filling. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
May be topped with whipped cream or ice cream or serve plain.
Excellent recipe.
I use light brown sugar.

title: john wayne's favorite casserole
directions: Combine cheeses, chilies and onions.
Pour into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Combine egg yolks, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Fold in egg whites. Pour mixture over cheese, gently moving it to the bottom mixture. Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Remove from oven, put sliced tomatoes on top and bake an additional 30 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: chorizo burritos
directions: Fry meat for approximately 10 minutes.
Drain.
Add chilies and beaten eggs.
Serve with warm tortillas to make burritos.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a Dutch oven.
Cook over medium heat on top of stove until heated through and potatoes are done.
The longer you cook this, the better it tastes.
You may put ingredients in a crock-pot and cook all day.
This recipe is from Billy's aunt, Frances Yeats.

title: almond ecstasy
directions: Pour all ingredients into the jar of a blender and process until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour into 4 glasses and garnish with whipped cream and chocolate shavings, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Wash the berries and cook with the water, sugar and tapioca until all berries have popped.
Set aside and let cool.
Fold the marshmallows, apples and nuts in first mixture.
Put in refrigerator.
Keeps well.

title: creme de menthe pie
directions: Place cookies in 2 large Baggies.
Tie tightly and crush with rolling pin.
Mix cookies with butter and press into a large, flat Pyrex baking dish.
Put aside a handful to sprinkle on top.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour, coconut and nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While cake is hot, spread marshmallow cream.
Cool completely before adding icing.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix 1 1/2 cups sugar, butter, shortening and eggs together.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Mix 2 tablespoons sugar and the cinnamon.
Roll balls in mixture to coat.
Place 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: favorite dinner recipe
directions: Preset oven to off.
Place children and/or husband in car with yourself.
Drive to the nearest, or your favorite, restaurant.
Let each member of your family order their favorite dinner.
Return home to a clean kitchen.

title: apple brownies
directions: Melt Crisco; mix with egg and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix all together and add apples.
Bake 40 minutes.

title: sandwich filling
directions: Grind vegetables and cook a few minutes in vinegar.
Blend in other ingredients.
Stir and cook 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Just add to hot water!

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake in a hot oven (425°) for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 1/2 hour or more until filling is set.
Cool.

title: mom's zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add oil, egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in zucchini.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook zucchini and onion in butter until tender. Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese.
Stir in vegetables. Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in ungreased quiche pie pan or an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Press to form bottom and sides.
Spread mustard and pour in vegetables.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until knife comes out clean. Set for 10 minutes before serving.
If it becomes too brown, cover with foil for the last 10 minutes of cooking.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to boil margarine, sugar and cocoa.
Boil hard 4 to 5 minutes.
Take off stove, put remaining ingredients in.
Mix well and pour out on lightly buttered cookie sheet or however thick you want it.

title: straw and hay casserole
directions: Cook fettucine noodles according to package directions; drain and rinse in cold water.
Brown meat in large skillet.
If sausage is used, remove casing and crumble sausage.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Add mushrooms and spinach and cook until mushrooms are slightly browned.
Remove from skillet.

title: red beans and sausage with rice
directions: Cut sausage in small slices.
Mix all ingredients together without adding any liquid except that in the beans.
Cook in crock-pot on high for 3 to 4 hours or on low all day.

title: chicken and crabmeat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into a baking dish.	Top with 1 cup crushed corn flakes.
Pour 2 tablespoons melted butter over all.
You may use crab legs (in chunks) or shrimp, instead of the 1/2 can crab meat. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles by directions.
Brown ground beef, drain and add seasonings (except parsley).
Add tomato paste and water; simmer 5 minutes.
Blend eggs and cottage cheese; set aside.

title: mother's rocks(cookies)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and butter.
Add flour, salt, soda and milk. Mix 1/2 cup flour with fruit.
Add to batter.
Drop from spoon onto baking tins.
Bake in moderate oven (350°).

title: easy fruit parfait
directions: In glass dish, layer yogurt, granola and fruit salad, then repeat with yogurt, granola and crushed pineapple.

title: old fashioned sweet potato cobbler
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Quarter potatoes, cutting lengthwise.
Put in large pot with water and salt and boil until potatoes are just barely tender.
Lift potatoes out into a bowl. Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix together flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring liquid to boil.
With a wire whisk beat the flour mixture into the boiling liquid and whip until there are no more lumps.
Put in 1 stick of the butter and whisk around until it melts.
Spray deep baking dish with Pam.
Arrange potatoes in dish and pour liquid mixture over potatoes.

title: oven-roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Scrub potatoes with vegetable brush. Cut potatoes into large chunks.
In large plastic bag or bowl, add all ingredients.
Close bag and shake or toss in bowl until potatoes are evenly coated.
Empty potatoes into shallow baking pan.
Bake, stirring occasionally, 40 minutes, or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain vegetables overnight.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salad oil, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and cool down.
Pour over drained vegetables and let stand one day before eating.

title: chocolate cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large mixer bowl, combine cream cheese and sugar.
Beat well. Blend in cocoa.
Add eggs and vanilla. Blend well. Blend in whipping cream.
Pour into crust. Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Center will be soft but will set upon cooling.
Cool to room temperature. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Garnish with pie filling.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken in iron skillet.
Pour 1/4 of sauce over chicken and cook 30 minutes.
Turn and pour rest of sauce over chicken. Cook at least 1 hour at 350° or until tender.
Add more sauce if family likes a lot.

title: mark's chicken
directions: Cut the chicken crosswise into strips about 1/2 inch wide and thinly slice the onion.
Heat the oil in a large frying pan.
Add the onion.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until the onion is translucent (probably about 3 minutes).
Push to one side of pan.
Add the chicken strips and cook, stirring until the chicken begins to brown, about 3 minutes longer.
Now reduce your heat to about medium.
Combine the sour cream and and paprika. Stir into the chicken and onion mixture.
Season with salt and pepper to your liking.
Heat through without allowing the sauce to boil.
Serve pronto.
This is nice over quick-cooking rice.

title: one step pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Blend at low speed for 1 minute.
Beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt or tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean (insert toothpick in the center).
Cool cake upright in pan for 15 minutes.
Move from pan and cool completely.
Serve with favorite ice cream.

title: herman coffeecake
directions: Mix well, and place Herman in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle topping over Herman.

title: quick 'n easy chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in a roaster or cake pan. In a bowl stir dressing and soup mix thoroughly. Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Line a sheet cake pan with whole graham crackers.
Combine pudding mix, milk and Cool Whip; blend until smooth.
Spread pudding mixture over crackers.
Top with whole graham crackers. Frost with chocolate icing.
Chill until serving time.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Add strawberry Jell-O to cake mix.
Add oil, water, 1/2 of strawberries, and eggs, one at a time.
Mix a total of 4 minutes. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13 x 2 1/2-inch pan.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Cut middle out of a loaf of any flavor round bread.
Spoon dip inside bread.
Break or cut up the middle of the bread to use with the dip.

title: baked mac and cheese for 30 people
directions: Boil macaroni according to directions on package; drain. While hot add grated cheese, saving some to put on top.
Add margarine and eggs which have been beaten into the milk.
Mix dry mustard with a little of the milk.
Place all in a large greased casserole. Spread cheese and bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden.
Delicious for large picnics or parties.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa mixture, egg white and milk together. Then add to cocoa mixture.
Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour into two small pie crusts that are done (cooked).

title: chicken piccata
directions: Cut chicken
in slices about 1/2-inch wide and 2-inches long. Combine flour and salt.
Dip chicken into flour mixture to coat. In	skillet
cook
chicken	pieces	in hot butter or margarine, stirring
and turning, until lightly browned, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Add wine, lemon juice, bouillon granules and pepper. Cook
and
stir
until
mixture thickens slightly and boils. Serve with rice.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
When ready for a cup of hot chocolate, boil water and add 2 tablespoons to water.
Add more or less cocoa mixture according to your taste.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, then add last 3 ingredients.
Mix and drop on waxed paper, 1 tablespoon per cookie.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: crock-pot round steak italiano
directions: Cut steak into serving sizes or strips. Remove excess fat. Pour a small amount of spaghetti sauce into crock-pot to cover bottom.
Add some meat.
Repeat step, making sure meat is covered on top with sauce.
Add spices as you go along.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 9 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops about 20 minutes.
Add liquid; simmer 20 minutes. Add rice; simmer until tender, about 20 minutes.

title: crispy onion biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place biscuits in 8-inch round pan. Mix the butter and onion soup mix.
Spread on each biscuit.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: decadent brownie pie
directions: Bake pastry shell for 10 minutes at 375° and remove from oven.
Reduce temperature to 325°.

title: fudge
directions: Cook to soft boil.
Take off fire.
Add 1 (12 ounce) package chocolate chips, 1 pint marshmallow cream and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat to blend.
Add nuts as you like.
Pour into buttered pans.
I like to add raisins to part of mine.

title: banana trifle
directions: Line bottom of glass bowl with cubed cake. Melt fudge topping on low and stir in Kahlua or coffee. Pour fudge topping over cake. Sprinkle 2/3 of Butterfinger crumbs over this. Mix pudding, milk and whipping cream with a wire whisk. Pour over cake. Refrigerate 45 minutes. Slice bananas on top of this. Spread with Cool Whip, being sure to cover entire top. Sprinkle with remaining Butterfinger crumbs. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: parmesan rolls
directions: Melt butter.
Dip top of each roll into butter.
Place on cookie sheet.
Generously sprinkle tops with Parmesan.
Bake at 350° until brown and crunchy.
Can use a variety of breads sliced thin.
Great flavor and complements any meal.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid. Remove skins & bones from salmon. Flake with fork and set aside. Combine cracker crumbs and reserved liquid; let stand 5 minutes or until liquid is absorbed. Stir in salmon, cornmeal, and next 3 ingredients. Shape salmon mixture into patties. Fry patties in hot oil over medium heat until browned, turning once. Drain on paper towels.

title: frozen mocha cheesecake
directions: Combine cookie crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press into buttered spring-form or 9 x 12-inch dish on bottom and sides.
Save some for top.
Chill.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 1 hour or more.

title: tater tots and meat casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion;
drain.
Add mushroom soup and water.
Simmer for about 5 minutes.
Line a casserole with frozen Tater
Tots and pour the mixture over it.
Stir and add cheese. Bake
about 25 minutes at 350°; add additional cheese on top the last 5 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: ham and broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli until tender, drain well.
Cook onions in butter in sauce pan until done, but not brown. In a large mixing bowl stir together mushroom soup, milk and cheese.
Add broccoli, cooked onion, ham, rice and Worcestershire sauce, mix well.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees until rice is done (about 45-50 minutes).

title: plum nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix until smooth and add the plums with tapioca.
Combine flour, cinnamon, salt and ground cloves.
Gradually add to moist batter and beat until well blended (3 minutes).
Add the baking soda to the buttermilk and stir. Gradually add to the batter and stir in walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Bake in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pans that have been sprayed with Pam.

title: egg substitutes
directions: Clean opossum well, cut up as desired and boil until it is tender.
Take 4 large sweet potatoes and boil until tender. Place opossum and sweet potatoes in a large pan and bake until brown.
Season as desired and serve while hot.

title: zucchini almondine
directions: Combine zucchini, 1 cup Cheddar and bread crumbs and put in a dish. Saut onion in butter; add salt and pepper and blend with zucchini mixture. Combine milk, eggs and almonds and pour over zucchini and stir. Put in casserole dish. Top with 1/4 cup grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli or mixed vegetable scallops
directions: May increase recipe, if needed.
Grease casserole dish.
Put in broccoli or mixed vegetables.
Put croutons on top.
Add can of soup and bake at 350° over 30 to 40 minutes.
Put cheese on top and put back into oven, about 5 minutes, to melt.
(I have cooked my vegetables first, so they just need to be heated through with other ingredients.)

title: chocolate chip cookies with pudding
directions: Cream Crisco and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: spanish meat balls
directions: Make into balls the size of an egg.
Boil 2 hours in 1 quart of tomatoes.

title: monkey bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, blend sugars, then roll the biscuit quarters in the sugar. Thoroughly grease a Bundt cake pan and place nuts in bottom, then place biscuit quarters on top of the nuts.
Pour melted butter over biscuits. Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Slice favorite summer vegetables into long, chunky pieces. Coat evenly with olive oil. Place on aluminum foil on bread pan. Roast in 500° oven for approx. 10 to 12 minutes. Toss with kosher salt, pepper and balsamic vinegar. You may also add feta cheese or other favorites.

title: creamed onions
directions: Cut up onions into quarters.
Boil in water until tender. Drain.
Make cream sauce by melting butter.
Stir in flour.
Slowly add milk.
Bring to boil until thickened.
Add salt and pepper. Place drained onions in casserole dish, cover with cream sauce. Top with stuffing mix.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Melt fat in frypan.
Cut meat into 1-inch strips; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place meat, onion and garlic in frypan; brown.
Add peppers and bouillon; cover and cook 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes; simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce and water; add to meat mixture and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Makes four servings.
Serve over rice.

title: plum sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, combine plum preserves, vinegar, brown sugar, onion, red chili pepper or crushed red pepper, garlic and ground ginger.
Bring mixture to boiling, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Refrigerate in a covered container overnight to blend seasonings.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: pralines
directions: Stir the first 3 ingredients until sugar is thoroughly mixed. Put mixture on medium heat.
Let it cook and bubble up, stirring constantly, until it turns brownish color and soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add the oleo, vanilla and pecan halves.
Beat until mixture begins to turn sugary.
Drop on wax paper.

title: french onion soup
directions: Lightly brown onions in butter.
Add stock and cook 20 minutes.
Place toast in heated soup bowls.
Pour soup over and sprinkle with cheese.
Additional cheese may be passed in a bowl. Canned consomme may be substituted for brown stock.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mushrooms a la don and doreen
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Wash and dry mushrooms.
Put mushrooms in a baking dish, hollow side up.
Stir butter to soften. Stir in bacon, onion, parsley and garlic.
Put one scallop in each mushroom cap.
Cover with melted butter mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: corn flake bars
directions: Mix sugar and syrup; heat and bring to
a boil.
Add peanut butter; pour over corn flakes and mix.
Spread on sheet pans.

title: pancho pie
directions: Saute onions and green pepper in shortening.
Add meat, chili powder and salt.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and corn. Boil briskly.
Stir in cornmeal, milk and olives.
Bake in uncovered dish for 1 hour at 325°.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Measure pudding mix into a small, heavy saucepan.
Add water slowly, mixing well.
Stir constantly over moderate heat until a bubbling boil is reached; remove from heat.
Slowly pour on top of beaten eggs, stirring constantly.
Return to saucepan; cook and stir over low heat for 1 to 2 minutes, until thick and smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and artificial sweetener until dissolved and blended.

title: peabody hotel muffins
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Do not beat.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy beef and noodles
directions: Mix all soups and beef, no seasonings.
Simmer on top of stove 3 hours or cook on low in crock-pot all day; thicken with flour. Serve over noodles.

title: linguine and tomatoes
directions: Cook linguine.
Saute garlic, red pepper and onion in oil until lightly brown (5 minutes).
Add tomatoes and basil.
Stir gently for 2 minutes.
Pour over noodles.
Add cheese, salt and pepper to taste.

title: first prize barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given in mixing bowl with wire whisk.
Use as a base when cooking meats.
Especially good on spareribs.

title: garlic bread with tomato salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion, rosemary and parsley with 1/4 cup olive oil. Chill and let marinate for 1 hour.
Slice bread into 1-inch slices. Spread with butter and garlic.
Broil slices until lightly toasted.
(At this point, you can top with Mozzarella and broil until cheese melts.)

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Place thawed broccoli in the bottom of an overproof casserole dish.
Sprinkle chicken cubes over broccoli.
Make a sauce of the mayonnaise, soup, curry powder and lemon juice. Spread sauce over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well.
Blend in sugar, flour and salt.
Blend in condensed and evaporated milk.
Add vanilla.
Pour in freezer. Add Butterfingers and fill to 2/3 full with cream or whole milk. Freeze.

title: albino enchiladas
directions: Cut up cooked chicken and white onion; mix. Mix green chilies and cream cheese together; melt. Add sour cream and chicken. Add lots of salt and pepper. Roll in flour tortillas. Put in greased pan. Whip cream and pour over top. Put cheese over all. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: triple layer cheese cake* * * * *
directions: Combine cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter; blend well. Press into bottom and 2-inches up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Combine 1 package cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar; beat at medium speed of electric mixer until fluffy.
Add 1 egg and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla; beat well.
Stir in melted chocolate and 1/3 cup sour cream.
Spoon over chocolate crust.
Combine remaining cream cheese, brown sugar and flour; beat until fluffy. Add 1 egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; beat well.
Stir in pecans. Spoon over chocolate layer.
Combine 5 ounces cream cheese and remaining 1/4 cup sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add remaining egg and beat well.
Stir in remaining 1 cup sour cream, 1/4 teaspoon vanilla and almond extract.
Spoon gently over pecan layer.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave cheese cake in oven 30 minutes.
Open oven door and leave cheese cake in oven another 30 minutes.
Cool.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours.
Remove from pan and spread warm chocolate glaze over cheese cake.
Garnish if desired with curled chocolate and chocolate leaves.

title: savory sausage rice
directions: Lightly brown sausage in Dutch oven; pour off excess fat.
Add celery, green pepper and onion; saute until tender.
Set aside.

title: linda's green beef or chicken enchiladas
directions: Note: May substitute chicken or turkey for the hamburger.

title: pork chops and rhubarb casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim fat from chops.
In heavy skillet, brown chops in oil and butter and season with salt and pepper to taste.
Set chops aside then pour in any pan drippings over the bread crumbs, mixing with a fork.
Combine remaining ingredients. Butter a shallow casserole large enough to arrange chops in one layer.
Sprinkle bottom of casserole dish with half of bread crumbs then cover with half of the rhubarb mixture.
Place chops on top then layer the rest of the rhubarb.
Cover casserole and bake 40 minutes.
Remove cover, top with rest of bread crumbs and bake another 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: escalloped corn(corn is good with any meal.)
directions: Place corn, salt, butter, green pepper and sugar in a greased baking dish and stir.
Spread crumbs on top.
Pour milk over mixture and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and
take out 1 cup heaping full and add chopped pecans.
Then add eggs, sour milk and baking soda, mixed with a little flour.
Add to the first mixture and place in 10 x 10-inch square pan and then spread the 1 cup of dry mixture over the top, pressing lightly into it so it stays in place after baking.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place rolls on bottom of greased baking dish and slightly up sides.
Sprinkle sausage over crust.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese. Mix beaten eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Sprinkle top with sharp Cheddar cheese (shredded).
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked bananas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter, lemon rind and juice in baking dish.
Place in oven for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove and stir. Peel bananas, put them in the dish.
Turn them so they are coated with mixture.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake for 15 minutes. Serve hot with heavy cream.

title: golden cheddar broccoli bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 of the butter.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually, mixing until smooth, stirring constantly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Mix 1/4 cup crumbs and all corn.
Arrange broccoli in a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Pour cheese sauce over broccoli.
Toss remaining 1/2 of crumbs with rest of melted butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: salmon souffle
directions: In a buttered 1-quart casserole, alternate a layer of flaked salmon with a layer of bread cubes until salmon is all used, ending with a top layer of bread cubes.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over salmon and bread cubes mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven until mixture rises and is browned on top (approximately 45 minutes).

title: beef hash
directions: Melt butter; add remaining ingredients. Heat thoroughly and brown hash, stirring occasionally.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Simmer onions, pepper, celery and garlic in corn oil until soft.
Add seasonings; stir and mix well.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
Add cornstarch to thicken.
Add shrimp; cook 15 minutes.
Let set 1 hour before serving.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: harvest chowder
directions: Boil bouillon and water.
Crumble raw meat into boiling water. When meat is cooked, let cool.
Skim any excess fat.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Potatoes and carrots can be chopped into small pieces or if you like a thicker consistency the vegetables can be grated.
Cook over medium-high until vegetables are tender.

title: homemade granola
directions: Place 1/4 cup of mung beans in a quart jar and cover with tepid water.
Cover with cheesecloth and tie securely.
Soak overnight.
Drain water off.
Set in a warm, dark place.
Every day, rinse with tepid water and drain.
Place in a warm dark place again.
Repeat 4 to 5 days or until sprouts are as big as you want.

title: banana split dessert
directions: In a mixing bowl, toss together the graham cracker crumbs and the melted 1/2 cup butter.
Press crumb mixture onto bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: cucumbers in cream
directions: In a bowl combine cucumbers, onion, water and salt.
Let stand for 1 hour; drain and rinse.
In a serving bowl, mix cream, sugar and vinegar.
Add cucumbers and onion; toss gently.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add beaten egg, milk and liquid sweetener.
Add melted margarine.
Do not overmix.
Fold in the blueberries.
Place in a muffin pan, fill each cup 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, until lightly browned.
Yield: 12 muffins.
Carbohydrate 14 g, protein 3 g, fat 4 g, calories 104. One muffin = 1 bread starch exchange, 1 fat exchange.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze water from spinach until very dry. Stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, water chestnuts and green onions.
Blend well.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Stir before using.
This dip is good on Town House crackers or vegetable crackers.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Beat until light and creamy, butter and sugar.
Add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Shape into crescents on a greased baking sheet. Refrigerate for 30 minutes, then bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Drain sweet potatoes, reserving 1/4 cup syrup.
In large skillet, heat brown sugar, butter, orange rind, cinnamon and reserved syrup to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer until slightly thickened, about 1 minute.
Add sweet potatoes, heat through, gently stirring, to coat with glaze.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 7 to 8 minutes.

title: wanda's wonderful cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with Pam.
Sprinkle nuts and coconut on bottom of pan.
Pour cake mixture into pan.
Mix cream cheese, milk and powdered sugar thoroughly and drizzle over unbaked cake batter.
Bake about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: molokhiya(egyptian soup)
directions: Thaw molokhiya; set aside.
In a large pot, boil chicken in water with chicken bouillon.
In a food processor, blend tomatoes and onion.
Add this to boiling chicken; let this boil about 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove chicken and add molokhiya.
Stir together well.
In a separate frying pan, fry oil, crushed garlic and coriander until golden.
Add to boiling molokhiya.
Serve with pita bread.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Grease a cookie sheet or pizza pan. Press out cookie dough (not very thick as it will rise). Bake until done (according to package directions). Cool.

title: cinnamon icebox rolls
directions: Soak yeast
in
warm
water.
Add
remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let rise
until
double in bulk.
Roll in rectangle. Add cinnamon, sugar, raisins,
nuts, etc.
Roll up and slice 1-inch thick.
Rise for 15 minutes.
Bake
at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes, until beginning to brown.

title: country potatoes(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a baking sheet with vegetable cooking spray.
Cut each potato in half lengthwise.
Cut each half diagonally into 1/4-inch slices, keeping slices together.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except tomato juice.
Form a loaf.
Pour tomato juice over meat loaf.
As this cooks, the juice will form a gravy.
Cook at 350° for about an hour.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Crumble and brown sausage.
Scramble eggs with sausage.
Heat shells.
Spoon sausage, eggs and picante sauce (to taste) in shells and roll up.
(If you like, add onions, green peppers, tomatoes, cheese or fried potatoes.)

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix and shape into balls.
Roll balls in flour.
Put into a baking dish.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Saute onions and brown beef; pour off fat.
Add the remainder of ingredients and simmer.

title: chicken with apricots and prunes
directions: Place chicken breast halves, prunes, apricots, olive oil, wine, garlic, brown sugar, salt and pepper in a bowl large enough to marinate for several hours.
(May be left overnight.)
Remove chicken from marinade when ready to bake.
Arrange in a shallow baking casserole dish and spread marinade on top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with rice or mashed sweet potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine butter and sugar in a 9 x 5-inch pan.
Drain pineapple reserving juice.
Spread pineapple over bottom layer.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Press into prepared pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Invert loaf for serving.

title: mexican low-fat pinto beans
directions: Soak beans overnight. Mix water, beans and onion in a 4-quart Dutch oven. Cover and heat to boiling; boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour. Add just enough water to cover beans. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and boil gently, stirring occasionally, until beans are tender, about 2 hours. Add water during cooking if necessary. Drain.
Reserve broth for recipes calling for bean broth. Cover and refrigerate beans and broth separately.
Use within 10 days. Yields 6 cups, 12 (1/2 cup) servings; 2 cups broth.

title: irish coffee
directions: Line up 8 warmed glasses or mugs.
Place 1 1/2 teaspoons of sugar in each glass.
Stir in enough coffee to dissolve sugar. Add 1/4 cup whiskey.
Fill to within 1-inch of rim with more coffee.
Top with whipped cream (do not stir) and serve immediately.

title: taco salad
directions: In skillet brown beef, stirring to keep crumbly.
Drain off fat.
In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Garnish with Cheddar cheese.
Serve at once.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef.
When done, add to the 3 beans.
Add ketchup, sugars and dry mustard.
Then add the onion and bacon, crumbled.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: spring temptation pie(preparation time:  10 minutes plus freezing)
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in medium bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in sherbet; mix until melted. Refrigerate 25 minutes or until gelatin mixture is slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping, marshmallows and pineapple. Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rainbow trout with lemon and capers
directions: Saute trout in 1/2 tablespoon butter and oil.
Remove from pan; reserve warm.
Melt 1/2 tablespoon butter in pan.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring to deglaze.
Pour over trout and serve immediately.

title: jalapeno-corn muffins
directions: Grease mini muffin pan and place pan in 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Place cornbread mix in bowl.
Make a well in center. Combine egg and remaining ingredients.
Add to cornbread mix, stirring until moistened.
Spoon into muffin pan, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 11 minutes.
Serve with Hot Turnip Green Dip.

title: spinach-cheese casserole
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Cook spinach until limp; drain well. Transfer to large bowl.
Saute garlic in 1 tablespoon butter until light brown.
Add remaining 3 tablespoons butter.
Pour butter garlic over spinach; stir in cheese, cottage cheese, salt and pepper.
Spoon cooked rice into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish; top with spinach.
Bake, uncovered, until cheese melts.
Cover with Mozzarella slices and broil until browned.

title: auntie pearle's apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a mixing bowl, combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. In a separate bowl, combine flour, salt, soda and spices.
Slowly add flour mixture into mixing bowl.
Stir in nuts, raisins, coconut and vanilla.
Stir in grated apples.
Pour batter into a tube or Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan with Crisco.
(I sprinkle a few finely chopped nuts in pan at this time; it looks nice.)
In a large bowl, combine the white sugar and cinnamon.
Shake to mix well.
Quarter each biscuit and drop pieces into cinnamon-sugar mixture.
I use scissors to quarter biscuits.
Put top on bowl and shake biscuit quarters.
Make sure each piece is coated all over with mixture. Sprinkle any remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture over biscuits.
Place the coated biscuit quarters evenly around in Bundt pan.
Melt the margarine/butter and brown sugar together in a saucepan.
Pour evenly over biscuits.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Immediately remove from Bundt pan onto a serving plate.
It sticks if left in pan to cool.
Makes 8 servings.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, both sugars and eggs.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and soda; then stir in chips.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: In heavy skillet, cook meat, onion and pepper until meat is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain, stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: cinnamon chicken
directions: Marinate chicken at least 1 to 2 hours.
Broil 20 minutes on each side, basting with marinade.
Divine!

title: basic stuffing
directions: Chop celery and onion together until fine.
Add poultry seasoning, salt and pepper.
Chop until mixed well.
Add melted butter, beaten egg, chopped turkey and broth; mix well.
Add one pan of crumbled cornbread.
Mix until consistency for making patties by hand.
May need more cornbread.
Fry in small patties in oil or can be baked.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: speedy spicy quesadillas
directions: Place 1 Velveeta slice on each tortilla. Fold tortillas in half. Place 2 tortillas on microwave plate. Microwave on High 30 to 45 seconds or until cheese is melted. Repeat with remaining tortillas. Cut each tortilla in half and serve with sour cream, tomato and guacamole, if desired.

title: prune spice cake
directions: Cook unsweetened prunes; chop and cool.
Cream shortening well and add sugar, creaming until well mixed.
Add unbeaten eggs one at a time, beating mixture well after each egg is added.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with prune juice to original mixture, a small amount at a time.
Add chopped prunes.
Bake in moderate oven.
Can be baked in four greased and floured one pound coffee cans.

title: orange-vodka julius
directions: Put all ingredients in blender.
Blend until all is mixed well and ice is crushed.
Pour in glass and enjoy.
Can also add vanilla ice cream to mix.
Cut milk in half.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on package.
Punch many holes in cake with tooth pick,
while still warm.
In a boiler bring 2 c. sugar with 1 c. milk to a boil.
Boil one minute, then pour over cake. Cover cake in pan with foil and let cool.
When completely cool, mix 1 cup powdered sugar with Cool Whip and spread over top of cake.
Toss coconut until flakey,
then sprinkle on top of cake. Slightly press coconut down into Cool Whip mixture.

title: crispy baked fillets
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Wash and dry fillets and cut into serving pieces.
Season, dip in oil and coat with cornflake crumbs.
Arrange in a single layer in a lightly oiled shallow baking dish.
Bake 10 minutes without turning or basting.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Cover bottom of large pan with foil.
Lay chicken pieces on the pan.
Mix all the remaining ingredients together and pour on top of chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: no-bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: You will need sheets of wax paper.

title: rice pudding
directions: Use 4-quart pot.
Add rice, raisins and water to cover rice. Cook 15 to 20 minutes or cook until rice is done.
Leave enough water to be level with rice.
Stir to keep from sticking to the pot.
While rice cooks, beat together eggs, sugar, vanilla, lemon extract, Pet milk and milk.
Add to cooked rice and raisins, all together.
Let come to simmer.
Remove from heat and pour in large baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Better when its warm. Serves 8 people.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Add butter; mix well.
Press mixture evenly into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine eggs, sugar and lemon juice in medium bowl; stir in egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned and set. Sprinkle lightly with additional powdered sugar.
Cool and cut into 1-inch squares.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, put butter in and heat in a 350° oven. Mix flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk and mix well.
Then take pan with butter and pour batter in butter.
Don't mix.
Spoon apple, peach, blueberry, cherry or pineapple.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate layer cake with broiled on topping
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Blend in chocolate.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk, beating until blended after each addition.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beef and barley soup
directions: Brown meat in fat.
Pour off drippings.
Add water, onion, barley, bouillon, thyme, marjoram, pepper and bay leaf.
Cover tightly and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in carrots, celery and green beans (if canned, add at the end and heat).
Cook, covered, for 45 minutes or until all are cooked through.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk in a saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick paste forms, about 10 minutes.
Cool completely. In a mixing bowl, cream the oleo and sugar.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Gradually add the milk mixture; beat 5 minutes.
Frost cake. Refrigerate.
Good on any cake.

title: chili rellenos won ton appetizers
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Combine beef with all remaining ingredients except wrappers.
Place a spoonful of mixture on each wrapper and follow package directions for folding and sealing. Deep fry 1 to 1 1/2 minutes until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.
Makes 6 dozen appetizers.

title: crusty fried oysters
directions: Combine egg and water.
Dip oysters in egg mixture; roll each in cracker crumbs.
Fry oysters in salad oil heated to 375°.
Cook for about 2 minutes, or until golden brown.
Yields 3 to 4 servings.

title: turkey marsale
directions: Flour cutlets; fry in oil until light brown.
Slice mushrooms and fry in same pan as cutlets-add wine to mushrooms, and let stand a minute or two so mushrooms get wine flavor.
Pour cutlets in mixture and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: quick casserole dinner
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery in skillet.
Drain fat and stir in flour, sauce, seasonings and peas; simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour into shallow baking dish.
Top with biscuits and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: picante sauce
directions: In blender, coarsely grind tomatoes.
Add green pepper, onion, jalapenos and garlic to tomatoes.
Process until vegetables are coarsely ground.
Stir vinegar, salt and sugar into vegetable mixture.
Transfer vegetables to a 3-quart pot.
Simmer uncovered over low heat until desired consistency.
Stir in oregano, cayenne and cumin.
Season to taste with salt.
Store in refrigerator or process.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Place all ingredients except soda in heavy pan (iron frying pan does best).
Cook until about 12 peanuts pop or syrup starts to crack in cold water.
(If using candy thermometer, 294°.)
Remove from heat, stir in soda.
Pour out on greased cookie sheet.
Cool. Crack into pieces.

title: old fashioned ginger cookies
directions: Blend sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs and the molasses dissolved in coffee.
Add spices and a little flour at a time, until you have a soft dough that you roll out and cut.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: crab gumbo
directions: Brown in flour in oil until golden brown or darker.
Add chopped vegetables, saute 5 to 10 minutes.	Pour vegetables in 6 quart pot, add water; let simmer for 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes, let simmer for one hour. Then add okra, cook 15 minutes. Add crabmeat, let simmer for 15 more minutes.
Serve over rice.
I like to saute my okra in small amount of oil for 10 to 15 minutes the add to gumbo, not sticky.
For seafood gumbo add 2 pounds of shrimp and one pint of oysters.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Halve peaches; peel, pit and cut into 1/4-inch slices; set aside.
Combine Bisquick, milk, the 2 tablespoons sugar, the oil, egg and lemon peel; beat 30 seconds.
Spread in greased 15 x 9 1/2 x 2 1/4-inch baking pan.
Arrange slices in rows on top of batter. Sprinkle blueberries over the peaches, pour melted butter over fruit.
Combine the 1/2 cup sugar, the brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over fruit.
Bake in hot oven (400°) 25 to 30 minutes. Cut into squares.
Serve with ice cream or freshly whipped cream.

title: my mother-in-law's best popcorn balls she makes for me!
directions: Put popped corn in a large bowl.
Combine sugars, corn syrup, water, vinegar and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium-high heat, stirring frequently.
Cook, stirring constantly, to 260° on candy thermometer or until small amount dropped in very cold water forms a hard ball.
Reduce heat to low; stir in butter until melted.
Pour syrup in thin stream over corn in bowl, stirring until corn is well coated.
Cool slightly.
Butter hands. Shape mixture into 3-inch balls and place on waxed paper.

title: champagne salad
directions: Soften the cheese and blend with sugar.
Add all other ingredients, mixing well. Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch pan; freeze. Take from freezer about 1/2 hour before serving.
Cut into squares.
Serves 12.

title: buckeyes
directions: Melt margarine (butter).
Mix margarine, peanut butter and sugar together until completely blended and smooth.
If mixture is too soft for rolling, add a little extra sugar.
Roll into smooth balls about the size of a buckeye.
Melt together one 12 ounce bag of chocolate chips and 1/8 cake of paraffin.
Using toothpicks, dip balls into chocolate chip mixture, leaving a portion around toothpicks uncoated.
(It may be necessary to prepare a second batch of the chocolate chip mixture.)
Place dipped balls on waxed paper or baking paper until chocolate has hardened.
Store in tin can.
Makes about 150 to 200 buckeyes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve
orange
juice
and jello in large bowl by the cup of boiling water.
Put in marshmallows and cream cheese so they
will melt.
