Whip cream.
Whip jello mixture and fold in cream, oranges and pineapple.
Refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box and let cool completely.

title: soft christmas cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in oleo or margarine.
Mix to consistency of cornmeal.
Blend in eggs, water and vanilla. Mix all together.
Roll out on floured board and cut thick with Christmas cookie cutters.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.
Do not let brown.
Put sprinkles or icing on them if desired.

title: oatmeal raw apple cookies
directions: Mix all together and drop by spoonful on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Take out of oven while still soft.

title: peach blackberry crisp
directions: In mixing bowl, combine brown sugar, oats, flour, lemon peel and cinnamon; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in walnuts.
Sprinkle crumb mixture over filling. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
If using frozen fruit, bake 40 minutes.
Serve warm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces (this takes about 2 months).
Cook slowly over an open fire for 6 weeks, covered with gravy.
This serves 3,800 people.
If more is needed, add 2 rabbits, but only if necessary as most people don't like to find hare in their stew.

title: beer flavored chicken
directions: Combine soy sauce, pineapple juice, garlic, onion, ginger, brown sugar and beer.
Cook on low until sugar is dissolved (this is your marinade).
Place chicken in a large bowl and pour marinade over the chicken.
Let stand one hour at room temperature or 3 hours in fridge.
When ready to cook, drain off marinade and save.
Cook chicken in butter or oil, turning often, then add marinade and simmer on low for 30 minutes.

title: jogging in a jar
directions: Take out 1 cup of apple juice.
Replace with vinegar and grape juice.
Keep in refrigerator.
Drink 2 ounces a day.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: In mixer, combine pumpkin, brown sugar, salt, pumpkin spice mix, 3 egg yolks and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in last.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: apple-pear salad
directions: Mix apples, pears and celery slices.
Shake orange juice, honey, cinnamon and nutmeg in tightly covered container.
Pour over apple mixture.
Toss until evenly coated.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Arrange apple-pear mixture on salad greens.

title: garlic cheese biscuits
directions: Mix milk, mayo, sugar and only 2 cups of the flour.
Use as much of the remaining flour as needed to make the dough thick enough to be dropped by spoonfuls and still hold its shape.
Add cheese food.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Drop dough so that biscuits will be 1 inch apart.
Spray top of each biscuit with Pam and sprinkle with more cheese food and garlic salt.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Darn close to Red Lobster biscuits.

title: sweet-sour baked beans
directions: Combine bacon-onion mixture and beans.
Bake in a 3-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: chestnut apple stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish for 1 hour in 325° oven.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
After they cool, peel and grate them.
Mix everything together with hands.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, or until hot.

title: texas hash
directions: In skillet, brown beef, onion and green pepper.
Pour off grease.
Stir in rice.
Sprinkle chili powder, salt and pepper over it.
Add tomatoes.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cook 25 to 30 minutes until rice is tender.

title: overnight cornbread casserole
directions: In a 12 x 8 x 2 inch microwavable baking dish, stir together stuffing mix, vegetables and ham.
In a medium bowl combine eggs, milk, salt and black pepper.
Pour over cornbread mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate overnight.
Remove plastic wrap; cover with wax paper.
Microwave on high (100% power) for 6 minutes; rotate 1/4 turn.
Microwave on medium-high (80% power) until a knife inserted 1 inch from the center comes out clean; about 7 to 9 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand, covered, for 10 minutes.
Stir slightly before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: theo's shrimp dip
directions: Blend together all ingredients with mixer.
Serve with crackers.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar slowly, folding as for a meringue.
Add a pinch of salt.
Stir or fold in nuts (I use a mixture of pecans, walnuts and almonds) into meringue, being sure they are all well coated.
Melt oleo in large, shallow pan. (Sometimes I use the broiler pan.) Spread meringue coated nuts in melted oleo.
Place in a 325° oven; allow nuts to cook slowly. Stir every 15 minutes; keep baking until nuts are brown and all oleo is absorbed.
Cool on waxed paper; store in airtight containers.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add Cool Whip and sugar.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze 8 hours before serving.

title: angel salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice.
Drain all other fruits.
Cut up maraschino cherries.
Combine eggs, 1/3 cup pineapple juice, sugar and lemon juice in double boiler.
Cook until thick.
Cool.
Soften cream cheese and blend into dressing. Fold in whipped cream.
Combine the fruits and pour the dressing over the top.
Mix well.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk, beating until smooth and creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill 5 hours.
Top with chopped peanuts.

title: apple ham casserole
directions: Arrange cooked diced ham in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish; spread with mustard. Arrange the cored and sliced apples over ham. Sprinkle with lemon juice. Combine brown sugar, orange rind and flour and sprinkle over ham. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: "lotts" of fruit salad
directions: Mix Tang and pudding box contents.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate.
Serves about 6.

title: sugarless fruit-nut bars
directions: Boil dates, raisins, prunes and water 5 minutes.
Add margarine and salt.
Let cool.
Add eggs, vanilla, soda, flour and nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 11 x 7-inch pan.

title: radish cole slaw
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put in layers.
Make sure all are dry, not wet from water.
Will make salad soggy.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar in a small bowl.
Chill overnight.
Combine broccoli, pecans, apples, raisins and onion in salad bowl; toss.
Pour salad dressing over salad; toss to mix. Sprinkle with bacon.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients and onions.
Blend in egg and buttermilk. Add to dry ingredients.
Allow to sit for 1/2 hour and then drop by tablespoons into deep hot oil.

title: party pizza
directions: In a skillet, brown the hamburger and sausage.
Drain grease. Dice Velveeta cheese and melt through the meat concoction.
Add garlic salt.
Stir constantly over low heat until cheese is melted.
Put meat on individual party rye slices.
Put on a cookie sheet.
When ready to eat, heat at 350° for ten minutes.
These can be made up and frozen until ready for use.
Kids love them!!

title: rice krispie cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add other ingredients.
Roll into balls a little larger than walnuts and flatten with a fork. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: wine-baked fillets
directions: *Fish fillet suggestions:
cod, flounder, orange roughy, pike, sea bass, sole or whitefish.

title: oreo dirt
directions: Crush Oreos in blender.
Mix milk, sugar, cream cheese, and pudding together.
Layer Oreos on bottom, then layer pudding mixture on top of that.
Top with Cool Whip.
Start over with layering, ending with Oreo layer.
Gummy worms are optional.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place greased muffin tins in oven while making dough.
Pour flour and salt in bowl.
Add milk and mix well.
Add unbeaten eggs and beat hard with egg beater until light.
Half fill the hissing hot muffin tins and bake 45 minutes.
Serve with butter and jam.
Makes 8.

title: blackberry wine
directions: Mash the berries in a crockery container.
Add water and allow to stand, covered, for 3 days.
Strain through a jelly bag and put the juice back in the crock.
Add the sugar and let the juice work. When fermentation has stopped, skim the wine, strain and bottle.

title: jog in a jug
directions: Mix and drink every day.

title: orange chicken and rice skillet
directions: Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken strips. Cook and stir 3 minutes.
Drain.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in combined Miracle Whip, juice from orange segments, pineapple chunks and sugar.
Add rice and green pepper strips.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat.
Add oranges and pineapple.
Let stand 5 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken for a crowd
directions: Boil chicken.
Usually takes 2 to 3 hours.
After cooled, take the meat off.
Cook spaghetti.
While it is cooking, prepare the rest.
Melt Velveeta cheese.
Can cut it in small cubes.
Place in a large baking dish.
Melt it in the oven.
Add cream of chicken soup, peas and mushrooms to the melted cheese.
Drain spaghetti. Add that and chicken to the melted cheese.
Mix all together. Place in oven and heat thoroughly.
Serve with buttered bread.

title: nut fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, salt, margarine, milk and vanilla in the top of double boiler.
Place over simmering water and stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix.
Spread into an 8 inch x 8 inch buttered pan.

title: beef and mushroom platter
directions: In saucepan, combine water, salt, and lemon juice; bring to boil.
Drop in onion rings and remove immediately.
Drain well on paper towel.
Slice mushrooms into thick lengthwise pieces. Arrange meat, onions, and mushrooms in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Stir together vinegar, mustard, remaining salt, herbs, and pepper. Gradually blend in oil.
Pour over beef and vegetables.
Cover with plastic wrap; chill several hours or overnight, basting occasionally.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Serve on sandwich rolls. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: pasta with asparagus and salmon
directions: In a small bowl, combine the olive oil, soy sauce, vinegar, garlic and ginger.
Cook the rotini until al dente according to the package directions.
Five minutes before it is time for the rotini to be done, add the asparagus to the pot with the pasta and continue simmering for 5 minutes.
Immediately drain the pasta and asparagus and put into a large serving bowl.
Add the salmon, soy sauce mixture and sesame seed and toss until the pasta and asparagus are coated with the sauce.
Serve immediately while still hot.
You can substitute broccoli or green beans for the asparagus.
Healthy recipe.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Cut stems from broccoli flowers (save stems for soup at a later date).

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix cookies and butter together and pat into a 9 inch spring form pan. Beat remaining ingredients together and pour on top of crust. Bake at 300° until firm, about 1 hour. Cool, then refrigerate.

title: beefy casserole
directions: Combine and simmer 5 to 10 minutes, beef, salt, sugar, tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic, salt and pepper, diced onion and green pepper.

title: divine milk(makes 5 servings)
directions: In a pitcher combine milk and carbonated beverage. Stir and serve.

title: marinated venison roast
directions: Bone out the hind quarter of a small deer.
Marinate the meat in Italian dressing for 8 to 24 hours.
Remove from marinade, roll up and tie with a clean string, making sure to make a secure, tight rolled roast.
Place meat on rotisserie over low heat on a gas grill.
Cook for 4 to 6 hours.
Check frequently to see that the roast remains tied.

title: julia child's potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until clear.
Add flour and mix with onion.
Add potatoes in water (add salt).
Cook for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.
Dilute bouillon cubes in small amount of soup.
Add this and milk to soup.
Stir frequently.
After soup heats again, add parsley and half of sour cream.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve soup with a side dish of sour cream to add if you wish.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together, adding eggs last.
Empty into wax paper and press into deep bowl.
Cover with wax paper; chill overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: lime congealed salad
directions: Drain juice from can of fruit cocktail and finish out to one cup with water and bring to a boil.
Mix with jello and let begin to jell.
Add milk, nuts and fruit cocktail and refrigerate.

title: super bowl chili
directions: In a 4-quart Dutch oven, brown beef and pork.
Drain.
Stir in undrained chili beans, tomatoes, onions, bell peppers, garlic, chili powder, sugar, red pepper, wine vinegar and cumin.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring frequently.

title: apple crumb pie
directions: Peel and slice apples into pie shell; sprinkle with 1/2 cup of sugar mixed with cinnamon.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup of sugar with flour.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill at least 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate milk shake
directions: Blend in a covered blender at high speed until smooth.
Pour into chilled 12-ounce glass.
Serve at once.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook the macaroni according to package directions.
Drain; set aside and keep warm.
In a saucepan over medium-low heat, melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Stir to make a smooth paste. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Heat and stir until thickened.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in cheese until melted. Pour over macaroni and mix well.

title: cranberry frozen salad or dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese, pineapple, sugar and Cool Whip. Fold in cranberry sauce and pecans. Pour into a lightly buttered (8 or 9-inch) pan and freeze. May be prepared weeks or even months ahead as it keeps very well. Serve sliced or scooped on lettuce leaf.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending each until smooth.
Add flour to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a 12-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Mix flour, white sugar and Crisco like pie dough.
Drop in beaten eggs, milk, vanilla and soda.
Roll thin.
Bake on greased pan about 10 minutes at 375°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on the package.
Add softened cream cheese and whipped topping.
Mix well.
Line a clean flower pot with foil.
Layer pudding with Oreo cookie crumbs, ending with Oreos.
Chill thoroughly.
Place a plastic flower into "dirt," if desired.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook 7-Up, sugar and cornstarch until thick.
Remove from heat. Stir in Jell-O and let cool.
When cool, fold in strawberries and pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: blackberry sour punch
directions: Dissolve blackberry gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in frozen lemonade until melted.
Add sugar and stir until dissolved.
Add club soda.
Serve immediately over ice cubes.
Garnish with lemon slices.
Makes 12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix together for 2 to 3 minutes.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and yellow rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken in at least 2 quarts of water, until done.
Debone chicken and put in a large baking dish.
Cook onions and yellow rice in chicken broth until tender.
Add cream of chicken soup and stir.
Pour over chicken and bake about 20 minutes, until done. Top with bread crumbs before baking (optional).

title: cauliflower and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook vegetables.
Place in casserole.
Melt butter.
Mix well with cream cheese and soup.
Pour over vegetables.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: christmas wreath treats
directions: Melt margarine in large
double boiler.
Stir in marshmallows until melted.
Add enough green food coloring to make mixture bright green.
Stir in coarsely crushed corn flakes.
Mix until coated with marshmallow mixture.
Let cool until warm but not too hot for children to handle.
With greased hands on waxed paper surface, shape into wreaths.
Push in red hot candies for color.

title: jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling.
Add Jell-O.
Chill until it begins to gel.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: yule kage
directions: Break up yeast and cover with 4 tablespoon sugar.
This will liquefy and will take a little while.
Heat milk and add butter and 12 tablespoons sugar.
When butter and sugar are melted, add yeast and 4 cups of flour.
Beat well until bubbles form on top.
Then add eggs, cardamon, salt and gradually about 4 cups flour.
Let rest on board for 15 minutes.
Knead lightly and put into greased bowl to rise to twice in bulk.
Take from bowl, shape into loaves, add raisins and citron to taste.
Let stand until twice in bulk and bake.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Stir together.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: tarolli(boiled cookies)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and oil until thick and creamy.
Add flour as needed.
Knead at least 10 to 15 minutes.
Roll dough into strips, the size of thumb thickness.
Shape into rings.
Have a pan of boiling water ready.
Drop a few cookies at a time into water.
Boil cookies about 3 minutes.
Remove from the water.
Put on cloth to dry for about 1 - 1 1/2 hours.
Cut around the cookie with a sharp knife.
Place on oven rack (not on cookie sheet). Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar and lemon flavoring.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Mix water chestnuts, vegetables, soup, water and rice mix. Pour in baking dish.
Place raw pork chops on top and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain and add package of spaghetti mix, the Ragu sauce and a little water.
Boil noodles (just until done). Meanwhile, in a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer as follows:
noodles and cottage cheese, 1/2 of sauce, 1/2 of Parmesan and 1/2 of Mozzarella.
Repeat until all ingredients are used.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat until blended.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream crisco, sugar and eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and flour with scant tsp. salt. Add whipping cream.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put in well greased and floured tube pan and place in cold oven.
Set oven at 325 degrees for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: butterhorns
directions: Break yeast in lukewarm water to dissolve.
Add sugar, eggs, shortening, and flour last.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Take out portion to use and roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into triangles and roll towards small end.
Let stand 2 1/2 hours to raise.
Bake 15 minutes at 375° in oven.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and cooking oil.
Add eggs and beat well. Combine flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Gradually add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla, coconut, dates, apples and nuts.
Batter will be thick.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Reduce heat to 275° for 30 minutes longer.

title: pie filling bars
directions: Mix eggs, flour, sugar, vanilla and shortening.
Spread 2/3 of the batter in a cookie sheet with sides.
Spread pie filling over the batter.
Spot on remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool and cut to serve.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all and chill well before serving.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat for 5 minutes eggs, sugar and pumpkin.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Spread evenly on long cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for 5 minutes.
Invert on dish towel.
Remove paper. Roll long ways towel and all.
Cool completely approximately 15 minutes.
Unroll, fill, reroll and refrigerate or freeze.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and put in casserole.
Pour butter over top.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese is melted.

title: strawberry banana dessert
directions: In large bowl, combine first two ingredients.
Add pudding mix and beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream, then fold in strawberries and bananas.

title: skillet rice and noodles
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add white scallions, rice and noodles.
Cook, stirring constantly, for about 6 minutes. Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; add to rice.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 20 minutes, covered. Serve.

title: corn-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper with oleo in a large skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bake in a casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with grated cheese and continue to bake until cheese melts.

title: blender pie
directions: Put all the ingredients in blender and blend for 5 minutes. Pour into 9-inch pie dish and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: rice delight
directions: Saute onions in butter. Mix with soup. Drain mushrooms and water chestnuts, reserving the liquid. Add water to make 1 1/4 cups of liquid. Add mushrooms, water chestnuts, liquids and rice to soup mixture. Mix well. Pour into a lightly oiled baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: italian cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in Crisco with a pastry blender. Add beaten eggs, milk, vanilla and whiskey.
Mix with your hands. Let rest a few minutes and mix again.
Add flour until you can roll a small amount of dough in your palm without it being sticky. Form dough in balls the size of walnuts.
Place on greased cookie sheet; bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cool cookies.

title: rhubarb coconut pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar, salt and water.
Add flour and butter, blending well.
Add rhubarb and mix thoroughly.
Turn into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 45 minutes or until filling and crust are done.

title: cheese apple
directions: Shape into apple.
Roll in paprika and garnish with leaf.

title: pistachio dessert(can be frozen; allow 3  hours for thawing)
directions: Melt the oleo in pan and add crushed cracker crumbs. Set aside 3/4 cup for top of dessert. Pat remainder in a 9 x 13 pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°. (Put in freezer until real firm to make it easier to spread the next layer.)

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of butter; add jar of Cheez Whiz.
Add vegetables and mix well.
Place in a casserole dish.
Melt the other 1/2 stick of butter and add to crackers.
Place this crumb mixture over the vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: marinade for barbecue ribs
directions: Crush garlic and ginger.
Combine with remaining ingredients. Add to spareribs and marinate 6 to 8 hours.

title: sausage bread
directions: Let pizza dough stand at room temperature.
Brown sausage and grate cheese.
Spread pizza dough about 1/2-inch.
Whip egg and spread 1/2 over dough.
Sprinkle sausage and cheeses over dough. Roll up sides and secure ends.
Spread remaining egg over dough and bake at 325° until golden brown.

title: avocado dip
directions: Blend avocado with cheese until smooth.
Add other ingredients; blend well.
Cover; chill.

title: date pudding
directions: Pour brown sugar and boiling water in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Stir until dissolved.
Mix rest of ingredients in a bowl.
Gently spoon mixture onto dissolved brown sugar.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Combine milk and juice. Add Cool Whip. Mix well. Spoon 1/2 cup raspberries in crust. Top with filling. Chill or freeze.

title: pina colada ice cream
directions: Combine sugar and eggs. Mix well. Add remaining ingredients, except milk, and mix. Add enough milk to fill freezer 2/3 full or to fill line. Freeze.

title: italian sausage soup
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, cook sausage slices until lightly browned on the outside and no longer pink inside when cut.
Remove from Dutch oven with a slotted spoon; drain on paper towels and set aside.
Spoon off and discard all but 3 tablespoons of drippings.
Add garlic and onions and cook, stirring occasionally, until onions are soft (about 5 minutes). Stir in tomatoes; break up with a spoon.
Add tomato liquid.
Add sausage slices, broth, wine and basil.
Bring to a full, rolling boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir in parsley, green pepper, zucchini and noodles.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until noodles are al dente (10 to 15 minutes).
Skim off and discard fat.
Pass cheese at table to spoon over individual servings.

title: chilli with beans
directions: Crumble and brown ground beef in large skillet.
Drain.
Stir in tomato juice, Williams chili seasoning and beans.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Garnish with cheese and onion.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon oatmeal crisps
directions: Cream together the butter or margarine and sugar.
Add the egg, vanilla and lemon extract and beat well.
Sift together the flour and salt.
Add to the creamed mixture, adding the oats last.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 7 to 10 minutes until edges are lightly browned.
Remove while hot and cool thoroughly before stacking.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: "popeye" chicken
directions: Butter 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Place spinach in bottom. Put the cut-up chicken on top of spinach.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and curry powder and mix well.
Pour over chicken. Cover with a layer of grated cheese.
Add layer of cornflakes. Dot with butter and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can be made earlier but add cornflakes just before baking.

title: sister marie's spaghetti sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Bring to boil and simmer at least 1 hour.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Dip chicken pieces in sauce made by combining next five ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: seafood dip
directions: Stir together cream cheese and mayonnaise, followed by onion, shrimp and crab.
Heat and serve warm or refrigerate and serve cold.

title: cauliflower soup
directions: In a large saucepan, heat onion in oil until opaque. Add flour.
Cook 2 minutes. Slowly pour in broth. Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add cauliflower. Simmer 2 minutes. Stir in milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Stir in sherry. Garnish with chives.

title: turnip souffle
directions: Steam turnips in a small amount of water until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add butter, cheese, milk and well-beaten egg yolks. Season to taste and mix thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pile lightly into a well-oiled baking dish.
Bake in a 375° oven until inserted knife comes out clean (about 35 to 40 minutes).

title: holiday nut cake
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream the margarine;	add
sugar.
Add
egg, vanilla and nuts.
Add other dry
ingredients
alternately
with
milk.	Bake
in
a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.
Frost with butter
and confectioners
sugar
frosting (make with canned, unsweetened milk).
Place 1/2 nut meat on each piece of cake.

title: *curabie 3(butter cookie)
directions: In a large bowl, whip the butter until light and fluffy.
Add confectioners sugar
and beat an additional 5 minutes.
Add egg yolk, vanilla and brandy and beat for 10 minutes.
Add almonds and flour and mix well.
Knead for a few minutes.
Pat dough to 1/4-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not brown. Cool and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown chops and drain off fat.
Stir in soup, water, carrots, onion and sage.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add green pepper and cook 15 minutes more or until done.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually, creaming well until fluffy.
Add eggs, which have been well beaten, and blend into creamed mixture.
Mix the cut fruit with part of flour.

title: blueberry cream cheese muffins
directions: Sift flour and soda.
Set aside.
Combine egg, honey, oil and milk.
Add flour mix and blueberries.
Partially fill each muffin cup with batter.
Add small ball of cream cheese; add batter to fill 2/3 of cup.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: 5 minute pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add condensed milk and evaporated milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add lime juice.
Blend slowly until thickened.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill
1 1/2 to 2 hours until firm.
Garnish with lime slices and berries.

title: ann's broccoli casserole
directions: Use butter (in addition to the 1/4 cup) to grease all sides of a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook cornstarch, sugar and water until thick and clear.
Add Jell-O; let cool and add strawberries.
Put into pie shell and cool.

title: lo-cal almost snickers - weight watchers
directions: Mix peanut butter, Alba hot cocoa mix, mashed banana, Equal, vanilla flavoring and Grape-Nuts.
Form into a candy bar and freeze.

title: polynesian salad
directions: In bowl, blender or food processor, combine oil, soy sauce, lemon juice, onion and honey and mix well.
In large salad bowl combine greens, sprouts, water chestnuts, radishes and sesame seed.
Pour dressing over and toss to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: grandma's wimpies
directions: Saute onion and pepper until tender.
Add ground beef and cook until all meat has browned.
Drain excess grease, then add vinegar, sugar, mustard, and water.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into quarter-inch cubes.
Brown meat in olive oil. Then put onions and mushrooms in and saute them.
Put tomato paste over that.
Sprinkle flour over mixture, blend well.
Add bouillon mixture, season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cover and let meat cook until tender, about 2 hours.
Five to 10 minutes before serving, add sour cream and Mueller's wide noodles.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Rinse chicken.
Pat dry.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Melt butter.
Add lemon juice and mustard.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, basting often.

title: super peanutty layer cake
directions: Cream
peanut
butter
and
shortening;
gradually
add sugar, beating
well.
Add
eggs, one at a time, beating well after each
addition.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add
to creamed
mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into 3
greased
and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes
out clean.
Cool
in pans 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely on wire racks.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and soak chicken in it for at least 1 hour (longer for more flavor).
Barbecue until done.

title: mushroom melange
directions: Saute mushrooms in margarine and olive oil.
Add remaining ingredients and blend together over low heat.
Season liberally with grated Parmesan cheese.
Cover and keep warm until serving time.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: low-fat mexican apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, water, vanilla and butter sprinkles together; heat to dissolve sugar.
Mix apples and cinnamon.
Put about 1/2 cup of apple mixture in each tortilla and roll up.
Place tortillas in a 10 x 13-inch baking dish; cover with foil and bake at 350° for about an hour.
Each tortilla has about 7 grams fat.

title: no milk-no eggs applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add applesauce.
Add raisins to cooled mixture.
Gradually add flour, spices and nuts.
Mix well and pour into tube pan or loaf pan if desired.
Bake at 350° until done.
The longer it sets, the more moist it will be.

title: devil's food float
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Gradually add milk and stir well.
Add vanilla.
Add butter last.
Stir only enough to make a smooth batter.
Put in a well-greased flat pan and pour sauce on top.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Place crackers in bottom of pie plate (1/4-inch thick).
Pour melted margarine over cracker crumbs in pie plate.
Saute onions in 2 tablespoons margarine until clear.
To eggs, add milk, salt and pepper.
Add cheese and onions; stir.
Pour over cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Check for doneness.
Let set before serving.
Serves 8 small pieces.

title: easy new orleans style beignets(been-yea)
directions: In a large pot, Dutch oven or Fry Daddy cooker, heat enough oil to deep fry biscuits.
While oil is heating, slice biscuits in half.
Fry biscuits in oil until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar until covered.

title: hot fudge sundae dessert
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil and watch carefully.
Let simmer a few minutes.
Add vanilla, then cool.
Crush 1 box chocolate wafers or at least 24 wafers.
Add softened or melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze for 30 minutes.
Put softened ice cream on top; freeze another 30 minutes.
Put cooled sauce on top.
Freeze another 30 minutes.
Put Cool Whip on top; sprinkle pecans or reserved cookie crumbs for top.
Freeze 24 hours.

title: beef log
directions: Day 1:
Mix all ingredients well with your hands.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix butter, 2 cups flour and powdered sugar and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: waffles deluxe
directions: Heat waffle iron.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg yolks in a medium size bowl.
Add sifted dry ingredients, melted butter and cream.
Stir until mixed well. Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour onto your waffle iron.

title: quick sausage dinner
directions: Cut sausage into 1/4-inch sections.
Slice vegetables same. Place all in pan on stove top.
Add margarine to taste.
Cook until vegetables are soft.

title: hot chicken burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Butter each side of bun. Spread filling between buns and wrap each in foil.
Heat at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 6.
These can be made a day ahead and refrigerated.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell; set aside.
Combine all ingredients except pecans in a mixer bowl.
Beat on medium speed 30 seconds. (Do not overbeat.)
Stir in pecans; pour into shell.
Arrange pecan halves on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; cool.
For full flavor, cover and let stand 1 day before serving.

title: quick beef stew
directions: *Takes a lot of these.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into small, bite-size pieces.
This should take about 4 weeks.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over kerosene fire for about 6 weeks at 465°.
Serves about 3,800 people.
If more people are expected, two rabbits may be added, but only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hair in their stew.

title: lazy cabbage rolls
directions: Chop cabbage fine; set aside.
Brown ground beef with onion soup mix; drain well.
Mix tomato soup and water.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan, making 2 layers of each, in order:
cabbage, ground beef mixture, rice, sauerkraut, if desired, and soup mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes 8 servings, 260 calories each.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Boil sugar and water until sugar is dissolved.
Add the frozen orange concentrate and 1 juice can of water.
Add the wine and all of the fruit.
Freeze.
Stir 3 or 4 times while it is freezing. Remove from freezer a short time before serving.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: chicken fricassee
directions: Fry
chicken;
drain
oil, except 1/2 cup.
Add rest of ingredients; bring to a boil to make brown gravy.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add egg and sorghum; beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients; blend very well.
Shape into small balls (about a teaspoon of dough).
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Place on rack to cool.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream margarine with 2 cups sugar. Add flour, then add egg yolks, buttermilk, vanilla and lemon juice.
Fold in 3 beaten egg whites. Put in unbaked crust and bake 10 minutes at 400°, then 300° for 30 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening, milk and salt.
Mix with a fork or whip until smooth.
Add flour.
Don't overmix.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Divide into 2 parts.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except powdered sugar. Beat 10 minutes. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top when cool.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pour into a 13 x 9-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and frost hot cake with a blending of the final 4 ingredients. Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.
Do not freeze.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time. Add soda to hot water, then add to buttermilk. Combine flour and salt. Add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition. Stir in vanilla, lemon and almond flavorings.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool cake in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool completely.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook on low for approximately 30 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Run about 1/2 cup water through kraut; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in covered dish.
Refrigerate until chilled well.

title: lemon sheet cake
directions: In large bowl beat cake mix and eggs until well blended. Fold in pie filling. Spread into greased 15X10 baking pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 18-20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool on wire rack. In a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar until smooth. Stir in vanilla. spread over cake. Store in refrigerator.

title: berry fruit salad
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream, sugar, milk and extract with mixer until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Spoon over fruit.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese rice krispies
directions: Cream flour, oleo and cheese good.
Add Rice Krispies and pepper.
Roll in hands into marble size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Dip fork in flour (will be better).

title: raisin bars
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup sugar; cut in 1/3 cup butter with a pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Press into bottom of a lightly greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine eggs and next 8 ingredients, stirring until blended.
Pour over baked crust.
Bake batter at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Combine 2 teaspoons orange juice, lemon juice and 1 1/2 teaspoons butter in a small bowl; beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until smooth.
Pour mixture over hot layer.
Cool on a wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Freeze in an airtight container up to 3 months, if desired.
Yield:
about 3 dozen.

title: kraut relish
directions: Comb. all ingreds.; cover and refrigerate for 8 hrs.
Serve with hot dogs or meats.
Makes 1 qt.

title: summer slush
directions: Mix together.
Put in freezer until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured angel food cake pan at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan. Dust with powdered sugar or use lemon glaze and garnish with pecans.

title: potato stuff
directions: Beat all together until stiff.
Grease 2 1/2-quart casserole. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roasted garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Scrub the potatoes; pierce with fork to allow steam to escape. Wrap garlic cloves in aluminum foil.
Bake potatoes and garlic 1 hour or until potatoes are soft.
Heat oil and rosemary over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes or until rosemary is fragrant.
Cut potatoes in half; carefully spoon potatoes into large bowl. Save skins for another use or discard.
Slip skins off cloves of garlic; discard skins.
Add garlic, oil mixture and salt to potatoes.
Mash until fluffy, adding milk until desired consistency.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy wild rice soup
directions: Saute onions, celery, carrots and mushrooms in butter until tender. Sprinkle flour over vegetables until well coated (mixture will be pasty). Add the water and bouillon cubes to the wild rice. Add coated vegetables and whipping cream. Heat and stir to make sure the vegetables blend into the soup. Do not boil. No salt needed. Serves 6.

title: stuffed shrimp
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter until tender. Soak bread in milk; blend thoroughly and add salt, pepper and cayenne pepper. Split raw shrimp almost in half. Leave tail on shrimp. Stuff shrimp with crabmeat mixture and press halves together. Dip shrimp in seasoned flour, then in beaten egg. (Beat 1 egg at a time. It may not be necessary to use all 3 eggs.) Roll shrimp in cracker meal and fry in deep hot fat; fry at about 375° until golden brown. Serve with desired sauce. Serves 6.

title: "grannie wood's" cornbread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add sour cream and hot water.
(Add more hot water if needed).
Add eggs and mix.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: cream chicken chow mein
directions: Simmer chicken until done.
Saute onion, celery and carrots. Mix chicken soup and milk; warm.
Mix all together and simmer in crock-pot on low for 3 hours.
Server over chow mein noodles and rice.
Sprinkle cashew nuts on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sweet and delicious kugle
directions: Mix all ingredients together while noodles are still warm. Pour into well-greased 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Measure flour in bowl.
Make well in center and add egg yolks, whole egg and salt.
With hands, thoroughly mix eggs into flour. Add water just enough to make a ball, adding water a tablespoon at a time.
Turn dough onto well flour covered breadboard; knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Divide dough into two parts. Roll each part separately.
Cut in 1/8-inch strips for narrow or 1/4-inch for wide.
Shake out strips.
Place on cookie sheet and let dry for 2 hours.
Cook in broth about 12 to 15 minutes until tender.
Put a drop or two of yellow food coloring in noodles if they look too pale.

title: nacho pie
directions: Prepare turkey as directed on taco mix.
Spread refried beans on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Layer meat mixture on next, then spread with grated cheese.
Spread picante sauce evenly over top. Top with peppers, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with chips.

title: fresh diet apple cake
directions: Cream butter; add egg and vanilla.
Add apples.
Add all dry ingredients and sweetener, nuts or raisins.
Put in a greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
(A very moist cake.)

title: california cabbage
directions: In bowl mix cabbage and noodles.
Brown sliced almonds in oil.
Mix salad oil, sugar and seasonings.
Mix and toss all ingredients together.
Chill overnight.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and chunky mixed fruit before adding to peach pie filling. Add as many strawberries as desired. You can also add other fruits such as grapes or kiwi fruit. Add sliced bananas last. Let chill before serving.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix flour, egg and sugar together.
Add corn, butter and milk. Put into 2-quart casserole and bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: hot chili cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips.
Heat, stirring occasionally, over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve as a dip with chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Remove from refrigerator and bake one hour, or until celery is done. bake in 350° oven for one hour.

title: pea casserole
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan on low heat, add green pepper, onion, and celery, cook over low heat until vegetables are tender. Remove from heat, add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs. Spoon mixture into a greased 10 x 6 x 2 inch baking dish, sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake uncovered, at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: applesauce custard pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, evaporated milk and applesauce and pour in pie shell.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Simple and delicious.

title: pecan tassie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Mix cream cheese and oleo; add flour and mix well.
Chill; divide dough into quarters and divide each one into 12 balls.
Press each ball into bottom and sides of mini muffin pans.
Stir together eggs, brown sugar and vanilla; stir in pecans.
Spoon into pastry shells, filling each cup.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until pastry is golden brown; cool 5 minutes and remove from pans.

title: good tuna casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in small amount of oil.
Add soup and milk.
Heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Spread crushed potato chips on top.
Serve. Delicious!

title: danish muffins
directions: Cream oleo and sugar until light and fluffy; add eggs, one at a time.
Alternate flour and baking powder together.
Add 1/2 flour and 1/2 milk, beat well and repeat.
Fill muffin forms 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes on middle rack in oven.
Cool on wire rack.

title: party canapes
directions: Mix well and spread on slices of party rye or pumpernickel. Place on pan and run under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: peel - candied
directions: SAVE ALL OF YOUR MANDARIN PEELS!
Yes, save those mandarin peels, slice in thin slices and dry them for future flavoring.
The peels are easily dried in a conventional food drier, in the sun or in a very low oven.
Store in an airtight jar.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix all ingredients except stuffing mix.
Place in 2-quart greased baking dish.
In a separate bowl mix dry stuffing with herb mix and make moist with water or chicken broth.
Place stuffing mix on top of chicken mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: hush puppy
directions: Sift cornmeal, flour, baking powder, garlic salt and salt together in bowl.
Add egg and milk to cornmeal mixture; stir until well mixed.
Let stand for 5 minutes; add additional milk if needed.
Drop by small spoonfuls into hot oil in skillet.
Fry until golden brown; drain on paper towels.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in shortening in skillet. Drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients except buns.
Simmer for 15 to 20 minutes, adding more tomato juice, if necessary.
Spoon onto split hamburger buns. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: no knead oatmeal bread
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, oats, sugar, yeast and salt.
Combine milk and butter in saucepan.
Heat to 120° to 130°. Add milk mixture and eggs to flour mixture.
Beat at medium speed 3 minutes.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour by hand until smooth.
Cover; let rise until double in size, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir batter down. Put into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Cover; let rise again 40 to 50 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Brush with butter.

title: mom's green tomato mincemeat
directions: Grind the tomatoes; add salt and let stand overnight.
Squeeze out as much of juice as you can with your hands.
Add the other ingredients.
Put all together in a roaster and bake slowly at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.
Freeze or seal in jars.
(You would never know this is made from green tomatoes.)

title: turkey tortilla casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine onion, chicken broth, and celery.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 5 to 6 minutes or till vegetables are just tender.
In a large bowl, stir together undrained onion mixture, cooked turkey, corn tortillas, chili peppers, soup, and pepper.
Reserve 1/2 cup each cheese; set aside.
Stir remaining cheese into tortilla mixture. Transfer mixture to a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with salsa and reserved cheeses.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: different salmon croquettes
directions: Drop from teaspoon into deep hot fat.
Turn once; remove and drain.
If you want larger croquettes, drop from a tablespoon. These are good hot or cold.

title: mother's fresh apple cake
directions: Peel and chop apples and set aside.
Measure oil into large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy with an electric mixer.
Sift flour, then measure.
Sift again with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add a small amount of flour mixture at a time to creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
Fold in pecans and chopped apples.
Spread evenly in a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350°
for 55 to 60 minutes.
Turn out on rack to cool.
Cut in squares.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese with pineapple juice.
Add cream, marshmallows and pineapple gradually. Let stand for 2 or 3 hours until marshmallows dissolve.
Put in refrigerator, not in freezer, in a long flat dish.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Put nuts, dates and candy in 1 c. flour.
Set aside.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk, add remaining flour to candy mixture. Add coconut, dates and candy.
Place 13x9-inch oblong pan in oven.
Put butter in pan.
Add cake mixture.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Blend orange juice and powder sugar.
Pour over hot cake in pan.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Fry meat with onion in small amount olive oil.
Drain.
Then add tomatoes, salt and pepper and any other spices.
Boil 1 minute.
Add tomato paste and stock.
Simmer 1 hour.
Add small handful sugar.
Mix flour with small amount water; add to thicken sauce.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together and layer on a jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, turning once.
Makes a good crisp potato.

title: beer batter fried fish
directions: Mix all ingredients until the consistency of batter, adding more beer, if needed.
Marinate 2 to 3 pounds fish fillets in lemon juice for 2 hours.
Dip in batter and fry in 1-inch of hot oil until crispy brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cajun tarts
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add egg and mix well. Sift flour and baking powder together; add to batter, alternating with milk and vanilla.
Roll out on floured board to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 5-inch circles.
Put a spoon of preserves on 1/2 of the circle.
Fold pastry in half and seal with a fork. Place pastry on a cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yield:
to 10 tarts.

title: refrigerator rolls(old recipe)
directions: Mix and knead well, let rise to twice the size.
Put in refrigerator.
About 2 to
hours
before ready to use, make into rolls and let rise
to
twice	the
size.
Bake
20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: chocolate oatmeal bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream the butter and brown sugar. Add corn syrup and vanilla; beat well. Stir in oatmeal; press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on a wire rack.

title: easy-serve salad bundles
directions: In bowl, combine the green pepper, cucumber, celery, zucchini and tomatoes.
Stir together the sour cream, salad dressing, salt and pepper; fold dressing into the vegetable mixture.
Split rolls horizontally; scoop out centers, leaving a 1/2-inch shell.
Spoon salad mixture into hollowed rolls; cover with roll tops. Individually wrap bundles in foil; chill until serving time.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked ground hog
directions: Preboil hog until done and tender.
Remove hog and place on broiler.
Lightly sprinkle with flour and salt and pepper to taste. Bake until golden brown.
Cut tops of apples off and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake with hog.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions.
Drain.
Mix soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add to vegetables.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Top with onions.
Heat for 10 minutes more.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Prepare Dream Whip as directed on package.
Add confectioners sugar and beat.
Add cream cheese and beat until well mixed.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Sprinkle with pecans, top with pie filling.
Chill.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt butter and chips in microwave or over low heat.
Add slowly, egg mixed with powdered sugar.
Stir quickly and remove from heat.
When cooled, add marshmallows.
Fold until all are coated.
Spread nuts on waxed paper.
Pour mixture on nuts, forming a log 18-inches long.
Roll up and store in refrigerator.
Slice as needed.

title: red and green pepper relish
directions: Remove seeds from peppers and grind in food grinder.
Mix with the onions and pour boiling water over the mixture.
Let stand 5 minutes, then drain.
Make a weak solution of vinegar.
Take one part vinegar and 2 parts water.
Put pepper mixture in the vinegar; let come to a boil.
Let stand 10 minutes, then drain again.
Add 1 pint of vinegar, the salt, sugar and mustard seed.
Let come to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Place in jars and seal.

title: cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cheese, sugar, flour and egg until smooth.
Place biscuits in a 9-inch round cake pan.
Press over bottom and sides of pan to form crust.
Pour cheese mixture over crust.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over cheese mixture.

title: mrs. lauritsen's shrimp bites
directions: Chop shrimp and parsley in a food processor.
Remove to a medium bowl and add crumbs, salt, egg and mayonnaise.
Mix well and form into large marble sized balls.
Cut bacon slices into thirds.
Wrap each ball with bacon and secure with a wooden toothpick.
Place shrimp bites on a baking sheet and broil, turning once to cook bacon on both sides.
Serve hot.
Makes about 50.

title: winna's fudge
directions: Note:
May use mint chocolate, butterscotch or peanut butter chips instead of semi-sweet chips.

title: jackpots
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef and drain; add barbecue sauce, onions and brown sugar.
Set aside.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook 6 to 8 hours in slow cooker on low.
Cook rice or egg noodles.
Serve with beef tips.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil; set aside.
Mix flour and spices including soda.
Mix with sugar, eggs and oil mixture.
Beat on low speed about 2 minutes.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts, stirring with spoon.
Pour in Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cake from oven and immediately place in brown paper bag.
Seal tightly until completely cooled.

title: cracker spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into ball.

title: yule log roll
directions: Mix together the vanilla wafers, pineapple, cherries, pecans, milk and bourbon.
Form into 3 rolls.
Roll each in powdered sugar.
Wrap each separately in heavy foil.
Store in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks before cutting for best taste.
Slice thin.

title: really good corn
directions: Dissolve flour in small amount of warm water.
Pour cream in bowl and stir in flour, then corn.
Pour into baking dish.
Put butter on top of corn.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Stir once after 15 minutes.

title: crock-pot steak soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except butter and flour in crock-pot. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours.
One hour before serving, turn to high.
Make a roux of the butter and flour.
Stir until smooth.
Pour into crock-pot and stir until thickened.
Cook soup on high until thickened.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cook in saucepan until it bubbles.
Add 1 3/4 cup milk and cook until thick.
Stir in 3 cups frozen corn.
Beat 3 eggs until frothy and stir into corn mixture.
Pour into a dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle top lightly with cinnamon and sugar. Bake for 45 minutes at 350° until knife come out clean.

title: johnny m casserole
directions: In saucepan over moderate heat, brown ground beef until crumbly.
Stir in seasoning mix, tomato paste and water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cook macaroni in boiling salted water according to package directions until tender; drain.
Stir in meat mixture, corn and 1 cup of cheese.
Turn into buttered 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered
in 350° oven for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Add taco mix and water.
Simmer, uncovered, until mixture is thickened, about 15 minutes.
Lightly grease bottom of a 11 x 7-inch baking dish. Spread refried beans evenly on the bottom.
Sprinkle with shredded lettuce, onions and chilies.
Top with ground beef mixture.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken and save broth.
Remove chicken to cool in order to remove skin and chop.
Add the rest of ingredients to broth. Simmer until done.
Add chicken and uncooked spaghetti.
Cook until spaghetti is done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Put into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Top with crushed crackers that have been coated with melted butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese with rice
directions: Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add cheese until melted.
Add saute mix to broccoli and soup.
Stir well.
Add uncooked rice and mix.
After all mixed together, pour into an 11 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Combine sugar and salt; add to eggs.
Add vanilla, half and half, whipping cream and pudding.
Mix well.
Pour into freezer and add enough milk to fill freezer.
Turn until hard.

title: bonnie's chocolate pie
directions: Cook
egg yolks, sugar, flour, cocoa and milk in double boiler until
thick
as
desired.
Remove
from
heat and add butter, vanilla and salt.
When cool place in baked pie shell. Top with egg whites or whipped cream.

title: joel's grilled ginger chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken together and pour over the chicken.
Marinate for at least 12 hours.
Grill on the barbecue grill for 15 minutes a side, until skin is darkened.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: something with nothing(or a smashing spoof; diabetic)
directions: Put gelatin in a cup; soften with 1/4 cup cold water.
Add boiling water; stir until the gelatin is completely dissolved. Add the sugar substitute and extracts.
Put in refrigerator until very firm.
When the mixture is firm, put into a blender.
Add 1 cup cold water; blend on high speed until frothy.
Pour into sherbet glasses and serve.
You may use any extract you wish.

title: italian dressing slaw
directions: Mix Italian dressing according to package instructions.
Cut up cabbage.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on cabbage.
Dice green pepper and add to cabbage.	Add 1/2 cup of mayonnaise and 1/2 cup Italian dressing; mix all together.

title: strawberry jello and apple salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water and when slightly thickened, add the cinnamon, celery, apples and nuts.

title: mulligan stew
directions: In a large saucepan, cook beef, onion and garlic until beef is brown and tender.
Stir in soup, beans and water.
Then add celery, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over broken saltine crackers.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Mix together.
Put in a tube or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Blend in flour.
Work into a long cake pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes on about 300°.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Remove crust from oven.
Pour mixture into crust and bake for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in pan. Remove from heat. Blend in flour, salt and mustard. Add milk.
Heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens a little and is smooth. Add cheese.
Heat until melted, stirring occasionally.

title: rabbi melon
directions: Cube or ball melons into large bowl.
Add cherries if desired. Pour in liqueur and mix it all up.
Cover and store in the refrigerator overnight.
When the melon is eaten, I guarantee you'll be drinking the syrup with a spoon!

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash and remove stems of mushrooms.
Scrape out some of the meat making a hollowed out shell.
Put all of the mushroom stems and meat in the Cuisinart, adding bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and black olives.
Add enough mayonnaise to make the mix stick together.
Stuff each mushroom with a mounded teaspoonful of the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and serve hot or cold.

title: chili dip
directions: Combine chili and cream cheese in a
medium saucepan over low heat until cheese melts.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in sauce and olives.
Serve warm with assorted chips.

title: sweet pickle relish
directions: Combine vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with cold water.
Let stand 4 hours.
Drain and rinse.
Press out all excess liquid.
Combine sugar, vinegar and seeds.
Bring to a boil until sugar is dissolved.
Add vegetables; simmer 10 minutes.
Fill jars and seal.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix and serve cold with vegetables.

title: mexican chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts with celery, onion, salt and pepper until chicken is done.
Remove from broth and chop into bite size bits. To the broth, add the Ro-Tel tomatoes and red beans with juice; bring to a boil.
Return chicken to mixture and reheat again to boil.
Serve this soup over steamed rice.
Low-fat and low-cholesterol, but good!

title: blueberry pudding
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stirring well.
In a blender or food processor, blend dissolved gelatin, tofu, apple juice concentrate, vanilla, brown sugar, cinnamon and 1 cup of blueberries until smooth.
Pour pudding into bowl, fold in remaining cup of blueberries.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix well; let chill until firm.
Add topping.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind all together and add mayonnaise.

title: breakfast potatoes
directions: Coat a 9-inch microwave-safe plate with nonstick cooking spray. Arrange potato and onion slices on plate; sprinkle with seasonings. Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese. Cover and microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Yield: 2 servings.

title: english muffin canapes
directions: Mix all ingredients and pile on 12 muffin halves.
Place on a cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, place in baggies and return to freezer.
To serve, cut each muffin into 8 pieces.
They are easier to cut when still a little frozen.
Place on broiler pan and broil until bubbly.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook until thick and seal in jars.

title: hot hamburger cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Let cheese melt, then serve with corn chips.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Flake crabmeat.
Combine all ingredients; put in greased individual baking dishes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs; dot with butter.
Bake in a 350° oven until well-browned.

title: apple bundles
directions: Peel apples and cut in 16 wedges.
Unroll dough.
Separate into triangles.
Cut each in half to 16.
Place apple slice at wide end of strip and roll up.
Juice the orange or use any orange juice.
Put juice in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put bundles in pan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and zest.
Spoon over bundles.
Drizzle oleo over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with Cool Whip or ice cream.
This is quick and tasty.

title: southern barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Makes enough for 2 to 2 1/2 pounds of chicken (3/4 cup sauce).

title: sunshine chicken
directions: Combine curry powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over chicken; rub seasonings onto top and bottom surfaces of each chicken piece and set aside.

title: chile-cheese spread
directions: Scald milk; pour over cheese.
Beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until mixture is almost smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and beat 1 minute.
Serve spread with assorted crackers.

title: chocolate mint chip pie
directions: Spread softened ice cream into crust.
Freeze 2 hours.
In saucepan, combine the remaining ingredients.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until thickened.
Cool.
Spoon over cut servings of pie.
Garnish with fresh mint, if desired.
Makes 1 pie.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. This recipe makes it own crust.

title: pecan crescents
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into crescents.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: tracey's "apple-tizer"
directions: In microwave, place Marshmallow Creme and heat until Marshmallow Creme is softened.
Pour in middle of large plate. Heat caramel topping in microwave until warm and pour into Marshmallow Creme, making a swirl.
Cut apples in small wedges and place around the marshmallow and caramel.
(Using red and green apples makes it more colorful!)
Dip apples in Marshmallow Creme to enjoy!

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into a ball.

title: daddy's good dinner
directions: *Slice thicker than lunch meat, but not too thick; they need to be rolled.

title: nita's cracker pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar together.
Pour into saucepan and heat gradually.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
Add crackers and coconut; cook until thickened.
Pour into baking dish.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar to egg whites.
Beat until stiff.
Spread over pudding, then brown under broiler.

title: apple cinnamon walnut bread
directions: Mix yeast, sugar and warm water.
Proof 5 minutes.
Add warm milk, butter, cinnamon, baking soda, orange rind, apples and walnuts.
Add flours.
Knead 10 minutes.
Let rise until double. Divide into two.
Roll into rectangle.
Add 1/2 cup raisins soaked in Grand Marnier.
Put in pans (bread).
Let rise.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes and 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: delicious hominy casserole
directions: Cook onion, pepper and celery in oil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add soup and milk.
Stir until smooth.
Add cheese and seasonings. Fold in 1 can of hominy.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole which has been well-greased.

title: corn casserole
directions: Grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish with butter; mix all ingredients together and place in dish.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cherry cola jello
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Measure syrup; add water, if necessary to make 2 cups.
Heat syrups to boiling.
Pour over Jell-O until dissolved.
Add Coke.
Chill for 1 1/2 hours. Combine fruit and almonds.
Fold into Jell-O.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown beef mixture with onions.
Blend tomatoes and water in blender.
Add tomatoes, paste and spices.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Cook noodles.
Layer sauce, noodles and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables, tossing lightly.
Combine remaining ingredients.
In a medium saucepan, bring to a boil over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir to blend. Cover and chill 24 hours.

title: kentucky-style fried chicken
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, flour, salt, lemon juice and butter into a paste and coat chicken evenly.
Stack pieces in a bowl; cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
About 1 hour before serving, heat about 1 1/2 pints cooking oil in heavy 9-inch saucepan.
Put 2 cups milk or club soda in bowl and dip each piece of chicken in the liquid.
Combine pancake mix, paprika, sage and pepper.
Dust chicken with pancake mix.
Dry pieces a few minutes without letting them touch.
Fry a few pieces at a time 5 to 6 minutes.
Place fried chicken on cookie sheet or shallow pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stroganoff casserole
directions: When draining noodles, leave a small amount of water in order to melt cheese into noodles.
Mix meat, onion and soup.
Stir into noodles.
Place in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Freezes well.

title: onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter over low heat for 20 to 30 minutes until tender and transparent.
Blend in flour, pepper and salt and cook over medium heat, stirring until bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in milk and stock gradually.
Return to heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Add Parmesan cheese, stirring constantly for 1 minute, then serve.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together. Bake at 350° in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish until it browns.
Put under broiler to brown top, if necessary.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove from bones and broth.
Cook noodles in broth.
Drain noodles.
Mix chicken, noodles, soup and sour cream and place in baking dish.
Break chunks of bread and place on top. Pour butter over bread.
Bake in oven until bread browns.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in freezer until slushy.
Stir and serve.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Saute steak and onions in olive oil until done.
Add soups and wine.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Serve on hot noodles.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados; add tomato and onion. Stir well and add lemon juice and salt. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: aunt mary's irish bread
directions: Heat oven while preparing ingredients.
Mix the flour, salt and baking powder with a spoon.
Blend butter into flour.
Add dissolved baking soda to the milk.
Pour milk and baking soda mixture into the flour and blend.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: burger of the day
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except rolls. Mix well.
Form
into
burgers
and	grill over medium fire until done to your liking, about 3 minutes per side for medium rare. During
last
30 seconds of cooking, place the rolls on the grill, inner
side
down,
to
toast.
Remove burgers and rolls from grill and serve with your choice of accompaniments.

title: banana cherry cheese pie
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add cold water and lemon juice. Gradually add sugar and jello mixture to softened cream cheese. Mix until well blended.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip until fluffy.
Fold in bananas and cherries.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm.

title: vanilla wafer pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add milk and wafers.
Mix well.
Add coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased/floured tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili(low-fat)
directions: Brown turkey and onion, then drain.
Mix all other ingredients and meat mixture together and simmer until ready to serve.
Using turkey makes it low in fat.

title: pork stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown pork in oil; drain fat.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is tender.
Transfer to slow cooker. Combine mushrooms, bouillon, dill weed and pepper.
Add 1 cup water.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on low heat setting for 10 hours.

title: basic bread dough(for decorations)
directions: You can add 3 tablespoons instant tea to white flour to give it color.
Dissolve this in the warm water.
Mix all ingredients to make dough; knead until smooth.
You may have to add more flour and water to get smooth dough.
Work with small amount of dough at a time.
Store unused dough in plastic bag to keep it from drying out until you use it.
Any dough left over can be stored in the refrigerator for about 2 weeks.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Combine dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until coarse crumbs form.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Knead dough about 1 minute on floured surface.
Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll each into 1/4-inch thick squares.
Spread each with 1/2 pound sausage.
Roll up from one end.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix all together and chill until set.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain. Melt butter in pan and add carrots and onion.
Saute until tender. Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups bread cubes, soup, and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.
Spoon into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Melt remaining butter and add remaining bread cubes.
Toss gently.
Sprinkle buttered bread cubes over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.

title: pikes peak apple crisp
directions: Place apples in an 8 to 10-inch pie pan.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Cover apples with topping and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry jelly
directions: Bring pectin and juice to a boil.
Add sugar and boil rapidly to jelly stage.
Pour into sterilized jelly glasses.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes or according to sealing directions.

title: overnight slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and purple onion in a large bowl.
Combine sugar and remaining ingredients, stirring until sugar dissolves. Pour over cabbage mixture; toss gently.
Cover with a slotted spoon.

title: holubki (pigs in blanket) or stuffed peppers
directions: Soak rice for 10 minutes or cook slightly. Slightly fry chopped onion.
Combine these ingredients.
Parboil or soak in boiling water the leaves of cabbage or remove seeds from the green peppers and use without further preparation.
Stuff meat mixture into peppers or fill cabbage leaves.
To close, roll and tuck ends in.

title: swieback
directions: Mix warm water, powdered milk and sugar.
Add yeast (sprinkle on and let set until bubbly, 5 minutes.)
Beat in flour to form batter dough.
Beat hard and add oleo and salt.
Add flour to make soft roll dough, kneading gently.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in size.
Pinch off a small ball, the size of an egg.
Place 1 inch apart on greased pan.
Put a similar ball, but a bit smaller, on top of bottom ball.
Press down with thumb. Let rise until double in size (approximately 1 hour).
Bake at 400° to 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: favorite "spicy" chicken soup
directions: Puree tomatoes, garlic, vinegar, oil and bread in a food processor.
Add 1/3 cup each cucumber, onion and green pepper to tomato mixture and continue processing until smooth.
Reserve remaining cucumber, onion and pepper to serve separately, along with croutons, for garnish.
Season soup.
Chill at least 3 hours. Serve in chilled soup plates or bowls.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Add seasoning mix and water to hamburger.
Stir well together and layer in pan.
Soften cream cheese and sour cream.
Blend together and spread over hamburger mixture.
Drizzle taco sauce over cheese layer.
Then sprinkle chopped onions over sauce.
Mix soups and spread over previous layer.
Put cheese over next layer. Top with olives, then tomato and green pepper.
Bake in oven until hot and cheese melts.
Also works good in electric frypan. Keep warm.
Serve with tostada chips.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy saucepan.
Cook to soft ball stage (238°).
Remove from heat; add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Stir vigorously.
Pour into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: karo pecan pie
directions: Mix together well. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes to 1 hour. Let cool before cutting.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch pans.
Cream margarine and shortening with sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Add vanilla, then sift together flour and soda, adding alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff; gently fold into batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: herbal power shake
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth. Makes one serving.

title: medium white sauce
directions: Melt the butter in saucepan.
Blend in the flour, salt and pepper. Heat until mixture bubbles.
Add the milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook rapidly until sauce thickens.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.

title: sweet-sour sauerkraut
directions: Add ingredients to 1-quart jar of well drained sauerkraut. Mix well and put in jars.
Leave upside down for 24 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: bacon and cream cheese scrambled eggs
directions: Place cream cheese and butter in a 1-quart glass casserole. Heat on Full power for 40 seconds or until cream cheese is softened.
Stir to blend.
Add egg mixture to cheese mixture.
Add bacon and stir.
Cook 3 to 3 1/2 minutes on 100% power or until eggs are almost set.
Stir after 2 minutes.

title: grandpa's campfire beans
directions: Sort and wash the beans, broken, halves, etc., included. Combine the garlic, onion, chili powder, black pepper, garlic salt, red pepper and salt pork.
Fill heavy-duty pot to full level with hot water.
Bring to a boil and continue to boil at medium heat until beans become partly soft.
Add sugar and catsup.
Add salt to taste and cook for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cake mix oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl. Combine oil and eggs; add to dry ingredients, stirring well. Stir in pecans and vanilla. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove to wire racks to cool. Yield: 5 dozen.

title: veal and shrimp basilica
directions: Cook angel hair pasta al dente; dust veal medallions in flour. Butterfly shrimp individually.
Saute veal medallions and shrimp with butter and basil in a large skillet until veal is browned, turning as needed.
Drain butter from pan; add white wine.
Simmer until shrimp is white and firm.
Serve over angel hair.
You may substitute chicken breast for the veal.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs, add pumpkin, flour and sugar, then add the milk, water and spices.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 (8-inch) pies.

title: orange glaze
directions: In medium size saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add juices slowly and stir until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook over low heat until thick and glossy (mixture will be thin). Cool.
Spread on any type of pound cake.
If desired, split cake into 3 layers.
Pour glaze between the layers and over the top and sides of the cake.
(Very good on Carrot Pound Cake.) Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain.
Mix all soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes together.
Line bottom of baking dish with chips, layer of beef, then soup mixture and repeat.
