Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: moore-moore casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and pepper.
Mix with cooked and drained noodles.
Add other ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into baking dish and top with cheese.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
(I bake until bubbly.)

title: grandma creamer's blackberry jam cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and lard.
Mix dry ingredients and add them to the egg mixture a little at a time, alternating with the milk.
Then add the cocoa/water mixture.
At this point, you may or may not need to add a little more flour.
This batter should be thicker than a normal cake.
Last, add the blackberry jam.
Put in 3 round cake pans and bake at 375° until done.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Spoon ice cream into pie shell.
Freeze until firm.
In a medium bowl, combine pumpkin and spice mix well.
Add whipped cream topping and mix well.
Spoon pumpkin mixture over ice cream. Sprinkle peanuts on top.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain fruits, reserving juices.
Add water to juice to make 1 1/2 cups plus 2 tablespoons.
Add sugar.
Bring to a boil; stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add fruit and ginger ale.
Chill until very thick, but not set.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into a 5-quart mold.
Chill until set.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Boil cranberries 10 minutes in 2 cups water with
soda.
After 10 minutes, take from stove and add jello, sugar and marshmallows. Put in refrigerator and let set until almost jelled. Beat well and add remaining ingredients. Put in refrigerator until set.

title: fruited tea
directions: Boil 3 cups water. Add tea bags and mint. Steep 15 minutes. Discard mint and tea bags. Add sugar, juices and remaining 3 1/2 cups water.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: swedish pineapple nut cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add pineapple and eggs to dry ingredients.
Mix.
Add nuts.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: fruited rice
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Drain cherries and cook this juice with sugar, flour and eggs until thick.
Mix this with pasta and chill 2 to 4 hours or overnight.
Drain crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Cut oranges and cherries in half. Fold fruit and Cool Whip into pasta.
Chill.

title: easy italian chicken
directions: Melt butter and add 1/2 package of seasoning mix.
Brush chicken breasts with butter mixture.
Roll in cornflakes.
Place breasts in ungreased, uncovered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, depending on the size of the breasts.

title: luau chicken
directions: Cook sauce over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens.
Marinate chicken in sauce, then baste as you broil or barbecue.

title: hello dollys
directions: Bake in oven at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: texas buffalo chips
directions: Cream together the butter and the sugars in a large bowl. Sift together the flour, baking powder and soda.
Add to sugar mixture.
Blend well and then add rest of ingredients as listed. Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, eggs and mushroom soup in casserole.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and cheese on top. Cook at 350° until slightly brown.

title: california salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix all together.
Chill for 12 hours.

title: pumpkin-raisin bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut each bread slice into 4 slices.
In a very large bowl, with wire whisk or fork, beat milk, sugar, pumpkin, flour, ground ginger, vanilla extract and eggs until well mixed.
Add bread; gently press down bread to coat well.
Let bread soak in milk mixture 15 minutes.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Add butter and onions. Saute 10 minutes.
Add flour; cook 5 minutes more.
Add clam juice, potatoes, thyme and pepper; simmer 15 minutes.
Add clams. Add milk and cream; stir well over low heat.
Do not boil or soup will curdle.
Add parsley and serve!
Makes 10 servings.

title: green apple cake
directions: Prepare apples; set aside.
Combine and sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a large mixing bowl, beat eggs briskly.
Add sugar, salad oil and vanilla extract; mix well. Add combined dry ingredients to egg mixture, stirring until well blended.
Fold chopped apples and nuts into batter.
(The batter will be thick, rather like a cookie dough.)

title: old-fashioned rice pudding
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Combine ingredients in greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake 2 hours.

title: pork and apples
directions: Cook and stir pork, apple, pepper and scallions in hot margarine in large skillet until browned.
Add sugar, salt, water, apple juice, soy sauce and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in rice; cover. Remove from heat; let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat; mix all together.
Bake in oven 1 hour at 350° or 12 minutes in microwave.

title: cheese ball
directions: Work together.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: williamsburg corn chowder
directions: Fry salt pork or bacon until brown and crisp.
Add onion; cook on medium heat, stirring, for 5 minutes.
Add celery, potatoes, chicken broth and 1 cup water.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Add corn, parsley and rosemary; heat 5 minutes.
Heat milk and butter, salt and pepper, and add to soup.
Let it simmer to meld.

title: bean dip
directions: Place drained beans in food processor and process until almost smooth.
Add hot sauce and lime juice.
Mix well.
Spread bean mixture over bottom of large baking dish or platter.
Spoon and spread chili sauce over beans.
Sprinkle green onions over top. Cover mixture with sour cream, then salsa.
Garnish with cilantro or parsley.
Serve with baked tortilla chips.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream together.
Add enough powdered sugar to thicken.
Serve with various fruits; strawberries and kiwi are good.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Defrost hash browns.
Cook and crumble bacon.
Melt Hellmann's and Velveeta together in microwave.
Stir bacon bits into Velveeta and Hellmann's.
Add the hash browns.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 3 to 5 hours or bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot beef spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in shallow baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Great with crackers.

title: granny smith salad
directions: Combine pineapple, flour, juice, sugar and egg together.
Cook on low until thick.
Cool completely.
Combine mixture with cut up apples, 1/2 cup nuts and Cool Whip.
Top with remaining nuts.

title: wilted lettuce with chicken
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine romaine, red leaf lettuce, mushrooms and onion.
Toss lightly to mix.
Set aside.
In a 12-inch skillet, heat one tablespoon of olive oil over medium heat. Add chicken and mustard seed.
Cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in 3 tablespoons of olive oil and the vinegar.
Add apples and cook for 30 seconds.
Remove skillet from heat and immediately add lettuce mixture.
Carefully toss for about one minute or until lettuce begins to wilt.
Spoon lettuce mixture into 4 salad plates. Garnish with egg wedges.
Makes 4 servings.

title: jamaican chicken
directions: Place pineapple in baking dish. Top with chicken breast. Dissolve cube in water.
Add coffee, salt and soup.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts. Serves six.

title: popover pizza
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Add spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce. Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over mixture. Mix flour, eggs, oil and salt.
Pour over meat mixture.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bake
directions: In 2 qt. baking dish (12 x 8 x 2) combine all ingredients except stuffing mix and butter.
Toss stuffing mix with butter and put over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Bring pudding mix, pineapple juice and lemon juice to a good boil.
Cool.
Pour over fruit.

title: chicken stew
directions: Boil chicken, debone and reserve broth.
Boil broth, tomatoes and onion until onions are tender.
Add meat back to mixture.
Add shredded cheese and crackers until desired consistency.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients
for about 35 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Add
broken
tomatoes, parsley, clams and juice.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Mix
cornstarch and water; add to chowder and cook until slightly thickened.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In another bowl, mix pudding and whipped topping.
Combine mixtures.
Put 1/3 of crushed cookies in bottom of foil-lined clay pot or plastic sand pail.
Add 1/2 of pudding mixture.
Top with rest of cookie crumbs before serving.
If desired, add green flowers.
Serve with garden spade.
Kids love it!

title: kalbi(korean-style barbecued ribs)
directions: Combine ingredients to make a sauce.
Marinate ribs in sauce for 4 to 6 hours.
Barbecue over coals in a hibachi or broil in oven.

title: fred perez's belgian waffles
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Mix together wet ingredients. Add wet to dry; beat until smooth.
Recipe yields approximately 8 to 10 waffles.

title: microwave cheese ball
directions: Combine beef and water in microwave oven container.
Microwave on High (100% power) for 3 to 4 minutes; drain beef well.
Combine cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, onion,
sour cream and drained beef; mix thoroughly.
Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts and parsley.
Chill.
Makes 1 ball.
May be frozen for later use.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Bake cake in a long pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: armadillo eggs recipe
directions: Upon removal of stems and seeds, stuff with finely grated Monterey Jack cheese.
Make dough with Cheddar cheese, Bisquick and sausage (works best if you use your hands to make dough
stick together).
Pinch enough dough to wrap each stuffed pepper.
Roll in the Shake 'n Bake and place on cookie sheet.
Put in refrigerator for a few hours or overnight.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 24.
If peppers are large, cut them to your preferred size.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a 3-quart casserole dish, greased well with margarine.
Mix crackers and melted margarine.
Spread cracker mixture over top of other ingredients. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until bubbly and brown.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put ham and water into pot.
Bring to boil.
Cook at a slow boil for about 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer at least 30 minutes or longer.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together and store in tight container.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon; drain, reserving drippings.
Crumble.
Add corn liquid, onion, potatoes and salt to bacon drippings.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add celery soup, milk and corn.
Heat on low heat.
Spoon into serving dish and sprinkle bacon over chowder.
Yield: 6 large servings or 8 smaller servings.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place shredded chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Mix crackers with 1/2 stick melted margarine.
Place over soup mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: linda's high-energy caramel corn
directions: In large saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, butter, cream of tartar and salt.
Stir over medium-high heat to boiling.
Stirring constantly, boil rapidly to the hard-ball stage (260°), about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda, quickly but thoroughly.
Pour over large bowl of popcorn.
Stir gently until kernels are coated.

title: breast of chicken shirley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season chicken generously with salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and brown quickly on both sides. Transfer to shallow baking dish large enough to accommodate pieces in 1 layer.

title: kelley's cabbage and noodles
directions: Coarsely chop (with a knife or grater) the cabbage.
Cook and rinse the noodles.
Melt butter in a large deep skillet or large saucepan.
Add paprika, garlic and onion.
Add cabbage.
Cook slowly until the cabbage is cooked (15 minutes).
Stir in cooked noodles.
Cook and stir until mixture is hot.
Cover; let set 1/2 hour.
Warm and serve.

title: country captain chicken
directions: Salt, pepper, flour and fry chicken.
Make a brown gravy where chicken was fried.
To this, add all ingredients, except rice, almonds and currants; add the fried chicken.
Let cook slowly with lid on for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cook the rice.
When the chicken is done, pour over rice.
Top with the toasted almonds and currants that have been boiled a few minutes.
This is a really delectable dish.

title: turkey-bean chili
directions: Cook turkey and onion until turkey is lightly browned and onion is tender.

Drain off fat, add turkey mixture and remaining ingredients to a 3 1/2 or 4-quart slow electric crockery cooker. Cover and cook on high heat setting for 4 to 5 hours, or on low heat setting for 8 to 10 hours.

title: oatmeal sheet cake
directions: After stirring together, add oatmeal mixture; stir and pour into sheet pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sensational spice cake
directions: Combine everything except flour, baking powder and soda. Heat until boiling and simmer 5 minutes; set aside to cool. Dissolve baking soda in 2 teaspoons hot water; pour into cooled mixture. Add flour and baking powder; stir until blended. Bake in greased 8 x 12 pan at 350° for 25 minutes. Ice with Penuche Icing.

title: theopal's peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, flour and milk in a saucepan and cook over medium heat.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thick, then add vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour into baked crust.

title: pineapple stuffing
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in pineapple.
Fold in bread.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour. This is a perfect side dish with baked ham.

title: meat loaf
directions: In very large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Form into three small loaves.
Place all three loaves into a foil lined baking pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
One loaf serves 3 to 4.
(Freezer other 2 loaves for later use.)

title: foil dinner
directions: Cut carrots, celery, onion and potatoes into bite size pieces. Place one piece of chicken and 1/4 vegetables on each of four pieces
of foil. Add a pat of butter and salt and pepper.
Bring foil up over chicken and fold edges tightly. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken and vegetables are tender.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix the sugar and the cornstarch in two-quart saucepan.
Stir in water slowly until smooth.
Add sliced berries.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and clear.
Add red food coloring; cool.
Stir in remaining berries, saving 1/4 cup for garnish.

title: foil fish bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Clean and rinse fish; allow to drain. Sprinkle lightly with salt.
Make stuffing:
Mix together margarine, parsley, dill sprigs, chives, onion and lemon juice. Stuff and wrap each fish separately in aluminum foil, sealing the edges carefully.
Bake 20 minutes.
Unwrap; remove to hot platter. Garnish with parsley and lemon juice or slices.

title: zucchini bake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch baking dish, mix vegetables together.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until onions and zucchini are translucent.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Add together all liquid, then all dry ingredients.
Set aside. Peel and dice apples, add cinnamon, sugar and 1/4 cup flour.
Mix well.
In greased and floured tube pan, place a layer of batter, then a layer of apples.
Sprinkle with leftover cinnamon mixture. Repeat, ending with apples on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Clean and wash shrimp; fry in hot oil.
When they turn pink, add minced onion, pounded garlic and ground pepper; allow to cook slightly.
Add chopped parsley, ground red pepper with its liquid, tomato sauce, ketchup, bay leaf, wine, salt, Accent, ground pepper, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Allow to cook for 25 to 30 minutes on medium heat.
Serves six.
"Cuba!"

title: egg custard
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture.
Pour in melted margarine.
Add milk and vanilla; mix.
Sprinkle top of custard with nutmeg.
Makes 2.

title: hot spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, omitting salt. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup spinach liquid.
Melt butter and saute onion until tender.
Add flour and mix well.
Add milk and reserved spinach liquid.
Add seasoning and Worcestershire sauce. Add cheese (cut in small pieces) and melt.
Add spinach.
Put in 1-quart buttered casserole dish and top with 2 cups buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: biscuit breakfast ring
directions: Combine ingredients, except biscuits, and cook in microwave for 1 minute.
Stir to mix well butter, sugar and seasonings.
Add the quartered biscuits and stir to coat.
Place in microwave and cook on Full power for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Let stand for 2 minutes.
Invert ring onto serving platter and serve immediately.
Bake in ring-shaped pan.
Yields 1 ring cake.

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a large saucepan; cover with water. Cover and bring to boil. Cook for 20 to 25 minutes or until very tender; drain well. In mixing bowl, mash potatoes. Add cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, sour cream, onion, egg, salt and pepper; beat until fluffy. Transfer to a greased 2-quart baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through. Sprinkle with additional cheese, if desired. Yield: 10 servings.

title: hot and spicy rice
directions: Mix rice and chicken noodle soup with boiling water; set aside.
In large heavy skillet, brown sausage, onion, celery and bell pepper.
Mix with rice mixture.
Place in large casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with sliced almonds over top.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine.
Mix in crumbs and pack in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Mix 2 sticks margarine, eggs, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat with mixer at high speed for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread over crust.
Add pineapple and sliced bananas in layers.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts and cherries on top.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic.
Stir in tomato sauce, water and seasonings.
Grease a 3-quart casserole dish, then alternate layers of meat, beans and corn chips.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and top with cheese, then bake for 10 minutes more.
Garnish with grated cheese, shredded lettuce, chopped onion, chopped tomato and chopped jalapenos.

title: pumpkin cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and margarine until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add combined dry ingredients, mixing just until moistened.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour, or until wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pans.
Glaze with combined powdered sugar and milk.
Garnish with pecan halves or red maraschino halves, if desired.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix together the cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread on slices of luncheon ham (Dak).
Place 1/8 dill pickle, sliced lengthwise, on short side of ham.
Roll up and slice.
Hold together with toothpicks.
Green onion may be substituted for pickle.

title: overnight pull-apart coffee cake
directions: Before going to bed, place frozen dough balls into a large greased Bundt pan.
Mix sugars and cinnamon and sprinkle over rolls.
Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans.
Melt margarine; cool slightly and drizzle on top.
Cover loosely with folded tent of foil.
Place in cold oven.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Stir in beaten egg yolks, flour, grated rind, lemon juice and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour in pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 450°. Reduce to 325° and bake for 20 minutes.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, melt butter.
Let cool slightly. Sprinkle cracker crumbs in pan, then sprinkle each of the following over the crumbs, one upon the other:
chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and nuts.
Pour milk over all; do not mix or stir.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Spread margarine in Teflon pan.
Add sugar and cream, then add chocolate and let this mixture reach a temperature of 235° on medium heat.
Remove from stove and add peanut butter and vanilla. Place pan in 1-inch of cold water and whip candy until it begins to thicken.
Spread into a buttered dish.
Slice when cool.
Makes 12 pieces.

title: cornish game hens a la orange
directions: Halve the 2 hens.
Place 1/4 of green onion under each half and dot with butter.
Place in greased baking dish.
Pour orange juice, thawed, and equal amounts of white wine (use juice can for measuring) over hens.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn up oven for a few minutes to brown.

title: pumpkin marble cheese cake
directions: Combine crumbs, pecans and melted butter or margarine; press onto bottom and up 1 1/2-inches up the sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Sift cornmeal and flour.
Add eggs, butter and milk.
Mix into soft dough.
Cook until brown.
Crumble bread into a large bowl. Add onion, celery, salt, pepper, sage and turkey broth.
Mix well. If too dry, add more broth.
Bake in shallow pan at 400° for 15 to 25 minutes.

title: "green wave" mint sticks
directions: Combine beaten eggs, melted butter, sugar, baking chocolate and vanilla.
Beat well and blend in 1 cup flour.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: plain pie crust
directions: Mix together flour and salt.
Add shortening and cut into flour with fork or pastry blender.
Add water and mix gently with fork in stirring motion.
Gather pastry into a ball and place in pie tin.
With tips of fingers, spread pastry along bottom and sides of pie tin, shaping a high fluted edge.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie shell.
For baked shell, prick with fork deeply and at close intervals on sides and bottom.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Roll out bottom crust of pastry to fit 9-inch pie plate. Break crackers coarsely into pastry-lined plate.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan.
Boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.

title: banana delight pie
directions: Prepare pie filling with milk as directed on package for pie. Measure 1 cup filling; set aside.
Pour a thin layer of remaining filling into pie shell.
Cut bananas into slices and arrange on top of filling.
Top with the remaining filling.
Blend whipped topping into the 1 cup filling that was set aside.
Spread over pie.
Chill for 3 hours.
Garnish with remaining bananas and additional whipped topping.

title: silly putty
directions: Pour liquid starch over Elmers glue already in pie tin, a little at a time, mixing with hands.

title: garden patch salad
directions: Gently combine peas, beans, pimento, celery, mushrooms, onion and green pepper in a medium-large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and carefully toss with vegetable mixture to coat evenly.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In a covered 6-quart Dutch oven, cook garlic, celery, onion and carrot in butter over medium-low heat about 10 minutes. Stir in chicken broth and water. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and stir in tortellini. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until tortellini are tender.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Cut artichokes into thirds.
Make a paste from the cheese, mayo and oregano.
Place artichoke thirds on bread and cover with paste.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar, syrup and salt on medium-high heat; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Then remove from heat, stir in soda and vanilla. Put popcorn in large baking pan.
Pour caramel over corn and mix. Turn into shallow pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Take out and spread on wax paper until cool.

title: applesauce
directions: Heat apples and water to boiling over medium heat; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally to break up apples, until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat to boil.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Makes 4 servings (1 cup each).
Each serving contains 190 calories.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, egg and shortening.
Beat until fairly smooth, about 1 minute.
Bake in greased 8-inch square baking pan in preheated hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes about 9 servings.

title: freezer favorite 3-way gold cake
directions: Beat yolks with salt until thick.
Gradually add sugar; beat until thick and puffy.
Add hot milk; mix.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain the clams, reserving the liquid.
Place the potatoes, onions and bacon in a saucepan and cover them with the clam liquid and water (just cover).
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter; pour in fruit and juice.
Mix sugar, flour and milk; stir.
Pour on top of fruit.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins(special)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Mash 1/2 cup blueberries into mixture with wooden spoon.
Add rest of blueberries in and stir carefully.

title: pauline oldham's cabbage salad
directions: Stir together the sugar, salt and mayonnaise and add to the cabbage, pineapple and marshmallows.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Combine broth and rice.
Heat to boiling.
Cover and cook until rice is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add mixed vegetables, chicken and parsley.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally. Serves 4.

title: caramel bars
directions: Combine caramels and 1/3 cup of the evaporated milk.
Melt and set aside.
In a large mixing bowl combine dry cake mix, 3/4 cup melted butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Stir by hand until dough holds together.
Press half of dough into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Baked at 350° for 6 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips over crust.
Spread melted caramels over chips.
Crumble the rest of dough on top and bake 15 minutes more.

title: fish fillets with basil and lemon
directions: Arrange fillets in baking dish in a single layer.
In small dish, combine lemon juice, margarine and basil.
Drizzle over fish.
Sprinkle with pepper.
Bake, uncovered, in 450° oven for 8 or 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Sprinkle with herbs or parsley.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add remaining ingredients; blend well. Pour mixture over 9 to 12 sliced peaches in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over batter and pour 1/2 cup water over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until brown and bubbly.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Put 3 tablespoons of white sugar in a heavy frying pan (iron skillet works great) and burn to a real dark brown, stirring all the time.
Remove from fire and immediately add the boiling water. Let this cool before using in cake.

title: butter herb chicken or fish
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan.
Add all ingredients and simmer 5 minutes.
Brush on chicken parts.
Place in oblong dish. Sprinkle with grated Parmesan and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread bean dip on platter.
Spread guacamole dip over bean dip.
Mix sour cream and salsa; spread over guacamole.
Sprinkle chopped tomatoes over top and cover with grated cheese.
Arrange chips around edge of platter like flower petals.

title: bo's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Add remaining ingredients and mix gently but well.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add milk and flour.
Peel and slice peaches (enough to make 1 quart).
Sweeten lightly with sugar and sprinkle with 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Place in baking dish.
Spoon the batter over the fruit and bake at 375° until crust is brown (about 30 minutes).

title: custard pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla, gradually stirring in scalded milk.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all the juices from the fruit.
This yields about 3/4 gallon. This amount serves 20 to 25 people.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Sift together: the flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt. Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill the dough.

title: seafood lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna until done.
Saute green peppers, mushrooms and onions in butter for approximately 5 minutes.
Add flour and blend in well.
Add half and half and sherry wine.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Add salt, black pepper, red pepper, egg yolks and processed cheese.
Stir until cheese melts, then add shrimp and crabmeat.
Mix Mozzarella and Parmesan in a bowl.
Set aside.
Put a thin layer of seafood sauce into the bottom of a large casserole dish.
Place a layer of noodles next.
Cover with a layer of sauce. Sprinkle with mixed cheese and spot with the Ricotta cheese. Repeat for second layer.
Finish with noodles, cheese and sauce. Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: beef tips over rice
directions: Cut steak into small pieces.
Brown meat and onion in margarine; brown well.
Add 1 to 1 1/4 cups water.
Add green pepper; simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: country ham and red eye gravy
directions: Fry ham until brown in iron or heavy skillet.
Remove ham from pan.
Pour grease of ham in bowl.
Pour hot coffee into hot skillet.
Pour coffee from skillet into bowl with ham grease. Gravy is delicious over hot grits or hot biscuits.

title: curried chicken balls
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; mix on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in the next 3 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls, then roll in the Macadamia nuts or toasted almonds.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: kathleen "me-maw" blackwell's egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla and flavoring.
Bring milk to boil, then remove from heat. Combine milk with sugar/egg mixture. Pour this into baked pie shell. Sprinkle nutmeg on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Beat flank steak.
Marinate 4 hours in teriyaki sauce, turning over occasionally.
Fry bacon 1/2 way.
Place steak on flat surface.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese.
Lay bacon on top of steak and roll steak lengthwise.
Hold rolled steak together with toothpicks and wrap in aluminum foil.
Freeze 1 hour until firm.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces.
Broil approximately 5 minutes per side for medium rare.
To serve, pour teriyaki sauce over broiled steak.
Serves 4.

title: slaw salad(1940's)
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into the bowl of lime gelatin; chill several hours, until gelatin sets.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.
Garnish with a little mayonnaise.

title: don't peek casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a covered casserole dish.
Place in 325° oven for 3 hours.
Don't peek or stir.
Serve over rice.
Do not add salt, only pepper.
Can be done in a crock-pot according to manufacturer's directions.

title: peach treat
directions: Use any size rectangular pan.
Line bottom with vanilla wafers, 1 layer of vanilla pudding, 1 layer of vanilla wafers and 1 layer of vanilla pudding.
Top with drained, sliced peaches side by side.
Serve with milk.

title: wesson oil pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients in pie plate.
Add mixed liquids and mix in plate.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 425°.

title: lemon barbecued pork chops
directions: Heat oven to
Trim excess fat from chops.
Place chops in ungreased
baking
pan
8 x 8 x 2-inches, season with salt. Top each
chop
with
slice
onion, 1 slice lemon, 1 tablespoon sugar
and 1 tablespoon catsup.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil and
bake
30 minutes.
Uncover, baste chops and bake until done, about 30 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes, onions and carrots in shallow, large baking dish.
Blend cream cheese and milk in a blender.
Pour over potatoes.
Grind black pepper on top.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar,
Karo and water until syrup forms hard ball in cold
water.
Beat egg whites until they will cling to bowl when upside down.
Syrup and egg whites should be ready at the same time.
Add
syrup
to
egg whites slowly, beating all the time until
it
will
stand
when
dipped
with a spoon onto a plate. Add nuts.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Cook all ingredients except pineapple until thick. Add pineapple and cook a little longer. Cool and put into a baked pie shell. Top with a meringue, or whipped cream.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Drain shrimp.
Break into pieces and add grated cheese and onion.
Mix well.
Add salts, Worcestershire sauce and parsley flakes.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Refrigerate.
Form into a ball and serve with crackers.

title: toll house chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in Nestle semi-sweet morsels and nuts.

title: mints
directions: Mix together and roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Then roll in granulated sugar and press into molds.

title: chocolate peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, white Karo syrup and milk together in a saucepan.
Put on stove and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir mixture in the pan that is sitting in cold water.
Stir until glossy and thicker. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool, cut and serve.

title: venison herb stew
directions: Lightly brown meat in butter or margarine in heavy Dutch oven. Add garlic and onion and saute until transparent.
Add salt, pepper and monosodium glutamate; stir in soup and water.
Cover and simmer about 2 hours.
Add other ingredients.
Cover and cook on top of range until vegetables are tender (about 25 minutes). Serves 6.

title: crazy fruit salad
directions: Mix cheese spread, cream cheese and Cool Whip together. Toss with
remaining
ingredients.
The pimento cheese spread gives this an unusual taste.
Real good!

title: clam chowder soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the bacon and onions. Simmer for 4 to 5 hours.
Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Saute onions in bacon fat.
Add bacon and onions to soup mixture.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Grease and flour 4 pound loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Will freeze well.

title: play dough
directions: Mix well; cook, stirring constantly, about 3 minutes or until it pulls away from pan and forms a ball in the middle.

title: hot crabmeat dip
directions: Cook slowly chopped white onions in butter until soft.
Add crabmeat and mushroom soup.
Cook about 15 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet potato croquettes
directions: Steam potatoes.
Mash and mix with sugar, dash of salt and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Place corn flake crumbs in small bowl.
Heap 1 tablespoon of potato mixture into spoon.
Put 1 marshmallow into center of potatoes.
Roll in corn flake crumbs, forming a ball. Deep fry until golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour,
salt
and
pepper, pound into both sides of meat. Heat oil
in
large
frying pan.
Brown meat slowly (10 minutes) on each
side.
Remove from pan.
Cook onions in same pan until golden.
Stir in remaining flour from dredging.
Add water and tomatoes.
Cook,
stirring,
until sauce comes to a boil.
Put meat in pan and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar, cocoa and milk; boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla; stir until it loses its shine.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: shirley's ham salad ball
directions: Beat cream cheese and mayonnaise until smooth; add ham and rest of ingredients.
Mix well and form into ball and roll in chopped peanuts.
I put all the ingredients in the food processor.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
After beating eggs well, add vanilla.
Sift flour with salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix well with the first 3 ingredients.
Beat well.
Add zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, using Bundt pan.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: With a fork, mix together first 4 ingredients.
In a separate dish, combine eggs, vinegar and water.
Combine the two mixtures; mix until all ingredients are moistened.
With hand, mold dough into a ball.
Chill overnight or can be left in refrigerator a week or more, or frozen.
Take out enough for an 8 or 9-inch pie pan. Roll until thin; it will make 8 or 9-inch pie crusts.

title: garlic bubble bread
directions: Cut bread into 1 1/2-inch thick slices or split in half lengthwise.
Blend together butter, garlic and oregano.
Spread on bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil until top is light brown and bubbly (2 to 3 minutes).

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mash bananas until soupy and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour and soda; add to butter and eggs.
Add pecans and bananas.
Pour into a greased pan (loaf or tube).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Tube pan about 45 minutes (loaf pan 1 hour).

title: coconut chocolate chip bars
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, soda and salt.

title: peach bavarian
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 2/3 cup juice.
Chop peaches into small pieces; set aside.
In another bowl, dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Stir in reserved syrup.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir vanilla and whip cream.
Gently fold into gelatin.
Fold in peaches.	Pour into mold sprayed with Pam or any other spray you use.
Chill overnight.
Unmold and garnish with peaches, if desired.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: parker house cinnamon rolls(these are wonderful for a "coffee or brunch")
directions: Melt and mix 3/4 stick butter and brown sugar.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Next, melt 1 stick of butter in microwave and set aside. Mix the sugar and cinnamon together in a bowl.
Set aside.
Dip each roll (frozen) in the melted butter and then roll in sugar mixture.
Place in Bundt pan, stacking on top of each other.
Let rise on counter overnight (covered).
Next morning, bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan, by turning Bundt pan upside down on top of serving plate.
Guest simply pull off roll.

title: marinated beef kebabs
directions: Combine oil, vinegar and salts, oregano and pepper in a saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Let stand until cool.
Place meat in a shallow pan.
Add mushrooms and zucchini. Pour marinade over meat and vegetables.
Cover or seal. Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours, turning occasionally.
Alternately thread meat and veggies on skewers.
Grill over hot coals 10 to 15 minutes or until done, basting often.

title: korean meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and form into meat loaf.
Bake in 350° oven 50 to 60 minutes or until no juice is seen when pierced with fork.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Use 1/4 cup mix to 1 cup hot water for a mug of hot chocolate.

title: oven cheese fondue
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Remove crusts from bread.
Cut bread into cubes.
Beat eggs, milk and seasonings.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese and onion.
Pour mixture into ungreased baking dish (11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch).
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour or until center is set.

title: sugar cream cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with 2 to 3 teaspoons of powdered sugar.

title: rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in 1-quart casserole.
Add all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: graham cracker dainties
directions: Put butter and sugar on top of stove and melt (don't boil). Arrange graham crackers in single layer on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle nuts over crackers, then pour butter-sugar mixture over all.
Bake at 300° about 10 minutes.
Cool; break apart.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Blend wafer crumbs, sugar and melted margarine and press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and then chill until firm.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Cook ribs until tender in water and 2 tsp. salt.
Drain. Arrange in shallow baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Heat over low fire until jelly is melted.
Cook 5 minutes.
Coat the ribs well with sauce; bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Keep adding barbecue sauce until all is on meat.

title: scrumptious mac and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to box directions.
When macaroni is cooked, rinse slightly and drain.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread butter on sides and bottom of a large bowl or pan.
Cut cheese into medium size cubes.
Place all ingredients into bowl or pan; mix well.
Bake for one hour.
Let stand 10 minutes and serve.

title: chocolate caramel nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/3 cup of the milk in heavy saucepan over low heat.
Mix remaining milk, margarine and cake mix in large bowl.
Press 1/2 of the cake mixture onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup of the walnuts and 1/2 of the chips over crust.
Top with caramel mixture spreading to edges of pan.
Top with teaspoonfuls of remaining cake mixture.
Press gently into caramel mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup nuts and 1/2 cup chips.
Bake 18 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: honey buns
directions: Combine the honey and cinnamon. Divide into 10 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups.
Place 3 pecan halves or chopped pecans in each cup.
Place 1 pan-ready biscuit in each cup and bake according to package directions.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Combine all vegetables in a large glass bowl.
Set aside.
In saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper; bring to boil.
Cool slightly and pour over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: heavenly orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water; cool to room temperature.
Add oranges and juice.
Chill until quite thick.
Mix sour cream and Cool Whip; fold into Jell-O mixture.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Chill until set (about 3 hours).

title: ham and cheese finger rolls
directions: Cook first five ingredients together until bubbly.
Keep warm while slicing rolls in half lengthwise.
Spread both sides of rolls with melted mixture.
Add slices of ham.
Spread cheese on top of ham.
Place top of rolls on top and return to aluminum pan. Heat until cheese is melted, approximately 15 minutes at 350°. Be sure rolls are covered with foil.
If you plan to freeze the rolls, let them thaw before heating.

title: blackberry yum yum
directions: Melt butter in 8 x 13-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and milk and pour evenly over butter.
Mix berries, sugar and water and pour over batter.
Bake 30 minutes in 425°
oven. Tastes great with vanilla ice cream on top.

title: magic bars
directions: Mix margarine, eggs, vanilla and sugar.
Slowly add flour. Stir peanut butter in last.
Pour in cake pan, 9 x 12-inches. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Add brown gravy mix and water.
While browning meat, put potatoes on to boil.
When meat and potatoes are done, carefully fold potatoes into meat mixture.
Spread in pie crust.
Place pie crust on top.
Place slits in top.
Bake until pie crust is brown.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Let cucumbers, onions, salt and water stand for 2 hours.
Do not rinse.
Pour sugar and vinegar over first mixture and let stand for a short time.
Pack in freezer box.
Thaw in refrigerator.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown onion, pepper and hamburger in skillet.

title: chiles rellenos casserole
directions: Line bottom of lightly greased 11 x 7-inch baking dish or casserole with half of the chiles.
Sprinkle half of the grated cheese over chiles.
Top with remaining chiles and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Combine eggs with milk and seasonings.
Pour over chiles and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes and cut into squares to serve.

title: cheese clam chowder
directions: Cook potatoes in saucepan in small amount of salted water (do not overcook).
Pour off all but 1/2 cup liquid.
To potatoes and liquid add the clams, milk and onion and celery soups; heat until simmering.
Remove from heat, add Cheddar cheese gradually, blending well after each addition.
If necessary, return to heat to finish melting cheese, do not boil.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Melt butter in a baking pan.
Mix batter until smooth.
Pour batter into pan.
Pour fruit over batter.
Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes or until brown.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix water, yeast and sugar together and set aside.
Sift together the flour, powdered milk, baking powder and salt.
Mix yeast mixture into dry ingredients.
Knead on lightly floured board until elastic.
Roll out 1/2 inch thick; cut into biscuits.
Brush with melted butter and fold over.
Let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.

title: candied carrots
directions: Boil carrots, scrape and cut into strips.
Mix other ingredients in a baking dish and warm to make syrup.
Put carrots in syrup so it covers them.
Bake until candied in a 350° oven.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, water, raisins in large pot.
Bring to boil; boil for 5 minutes.
Cool to warm.
Add egg and dry ingredients.
Batter should be thick but not dry.
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover with powdered sugar and water glaze.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening. Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well. Sift flour with baking powder. Add flour alternately with buttermilk to cream mixture. Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans. Fold in egg whites. Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or test sooner. Frost with cream cheese icing when completely cooled.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Mix.
Freeze for 24 hours.
Set out 30 minutes before serving, then add as much ginger ale as desired.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until top springs back.

title: one-bowl spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix by hand until just combined.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done. Cool in pan 15 minutes before turning out.
May also be baked for 35 to 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Make pudding according to box directions and chill.
Make cake according to box directions and bake in a 9 x 13 pan.
When done remove from oven and flatten as much as possible while warm. While cake is baking, mix cottage cheese, pineapple, cool whip and refrigerate.
When cake is cool, spread on pudding mix, then the pineapple mixture and sprinkle coconut on top.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Blend shortenings and sugar together well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and milk.
Start with flour and end with flour. Put in greased pan in cold oven.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cheese, bread and egg dish(serves 4)
directions: Spread the slices lightly with butter; cut 2 slices twice across, making 8 triangle pieces.
Cut the remaining bread in cubes until you have 4 cups.
Place layers of cubed bread in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle the layers with 1 cup grated cheese.
Combine and beat the other ingredients.
Pour these over the bread and cheese.
Place the triangles of bread upright around the edge to form a crown.
Bake the dish at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve it at once.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix cinnamon and applesauce until mixture forms a ball, adding more cinnamon, if necessary.
Knead dough on a board dusted with cinnamon.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Peel away excess dough and reroll to use completely.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In mixer bowl, beat 2 1/2 cups margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and 3 teaspoons vanilla, then combined flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir in oats. Drop by tablespoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until set.
Cool.
In saucepan, combine chips, sweetened condensed milk, remaining 2 tablespoons margarine and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Over medium heat, cook and stir until chips melt.
Immediately sandwich cookies together with chocolate mixture.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well (your hands work best).
Transfer to a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; form into a loaf shape.
Bake at 350° for 65 minutes.
Remove from oven and allow to rest for 10 minutes before slicing.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix cornstarch, eggs and salt with enough sweet milk to make a hard paste.
Dip chicken in mixture; fry in hot oil until brown. Place in large baking pan.
Cover with Sauce for Chinese Chicken. Bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
Turn chicken over and cook until sauce is thick.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well. Add eggs, one at a time. Mix soda with buttermilk and add to cake alternately with flour. Stir in dates, orange slices and nuts that have been dredged in a small amount of flour. Add coconut. Bake cake in either a greased and floured tube pan in a 300° oven for 2 hours or a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan in a 250° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: date nut cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add flour and buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Put 1/2 cup of the flour on nuts and dates; fold nuts and dates in last.

title: spice muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine wet ingredients.
Fold together quickly wet and dry ingredients just until flour is moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: tomato fried rice
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet or wok.
Saute onion, green pepper and garlic.
Stir in eggs and scramble/fry until eggs are set. Stir in rice and cooked chicken.
Stir in tomato paste, water (or bouillon), basil and parsley.
Simmer a few minutes.
Serve hot.

title: broccoli-onion deluxe
directions: Cut up fresh broccoli and cook until tender (or frozen broccoli cook according to package).
Cook frozen or fresh onions in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
In saucepan, melt half the butter or margarine.
Blend in flour, salt and dash of pepper. Add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly. Reduce heat; blend in cream cheese until smooth.
Place vegetables in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce mixture over and mix lightly.
Top with cheese.
Melt remaining butter.
Toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle mixture on top.
Bake at 350° until heated through, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lamb theresa
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet and saute chopped garlic for 1 minute.
Add the ketchup and cook until color darkens.
Add chopped parsley stalks and tomato juice.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add lamb (or beef), drained tomatoes and beans.
Bring to a boil, reduce the heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in arrowroot paste.
Return to heat and stir until thickened. Stir in broccoli, mushrooms and pepper.
Bring to a boil, reduce the heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve with yellow rice.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Mix together the sugar, oleo and milk in double boiler.
Boil until full boil, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Add remaining ingredients and pour into 2 buttered 9-inch round cake pans.
Place in refrigerator until set. Cut into squares!

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions in large bowl. Layer with salt. Cover with ice cubes and let stand 1 1/2
hours.
Drain and rinse.

title: chicken terrapin
directions: Thicken the broth with the flour, salt, pepper, and paprika. Add the remaining ingredients.
Stir easily and keep warm until ready to serve.
(It is good to be frozen for later use.)
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: black and white cream cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on back of package.
Spread mix in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix the cheese, eggs and sugar.
Spread on top of cake mix.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Prepare chocolate pudding as directed; spread on top of cooled cake.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: nacho dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in shallow dish.
Spread thin layer of salsa on top.
Top with chopped onions, green peppers, tomatoes and shredded cheese.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cut broccoli in small pieces.
Put in pan with 1 cup water and steam until tender.
Do not drain.
Set aside.
Take oleo and melt.
Stir flour into oleo; cook 2 to 4 minutes.
Stir constantly.
Add chicken stalk; bring to boil.
Add broccoli and half and half and mix together.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: hearty stuffed peppers
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds.
Wash peppers; set aside.
Crumble sausage into a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Add chopped onion and mushrooms; stir well.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small edge of wrap to allow steam to escape.

title: hawaiian cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour, 1 cup sugar and butter until particles are fine and crumbly.
Pat into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Cool slightly.
Blend cream cheese, 4 tablespoons sugar, milk and eggs; fold in vanilla and pineapple.
Spread over crust.
Combine melted butter and coconut for topping; sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until coconut is toasted and filling is set.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: egg sandwich souffle
directions: Place 8 slices of buttered bread in 9 x 13-inch pan, butter side down.
Sprinkle with ham and cheese.
Layer with other 8 slices bread.
Mix eggs, milk, dry mustard and salt together; pour over bread.

title: smothered steak
directions: Brown steak on both sides.
Put in a casserole dish.
Cover with onion slices and soup.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: lasagna
directions: Pour small amount of sauce in bottom of pan.
Add by layers: noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese, sauce, Swiss cheese, sauce, Cheddar cheese and sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: bojangles biscuits
directions: Melt margarine.
Add milk.
Then baking powder and sugar. finally, add flour until no longer too sticky.
Shape into 12 biscuits.
May use another cup of flour.
Bake at 400°.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and cream cheese.
Cut in cubes.
Add 2 cups boiling water and blend ingredients.
Drain pineapple and add 1 cup of pineapple juice to mixture.
Stir.
Chill until semi-firm. Fold in pineapple and Cool Whip.
Chill until firm.

title: baked onions with balsamic vinegar
directions: Cut off roots and stem ends of onions.
Using a sharp knife one should make a deep "X" on top of each onion, cutting halfway down. Place each onion on a 6 x 6-inch piece of aluminum foil with "X" up.
Bring up corners of each square.
Top each with 1 teaspoon olive oil.
Twist foil together tightly to completely enclose onions.
Place twist up on a large baking sheet.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° until tender.

title: black bean soup
directions: Sort beans to remove debris.
Rinse well, drain.
In 10 to 12-quart pan bring beans, stock and spices to a boil.
Boil hard for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally and adding water if needed. Meanwhile, fry up bacon.
When bacon is crisp remove bits (save for later) and saute veggies until tender.
After the beans have boiled, reduce heat to simmer.
Add one quartered onion, salt, pepper and water if needed.
Cook another hour.
Add cooked veggies, cook until desired tenderness.
It is perfect for using leftover meats, ham, chicken or pork could be added when veggies are.
Serve with rice or bulgar wheat.
Great with chopped green onion, Parmesan cheese and bacon bits.
Freezes well.

title: traditional broccoli stir-fry
directions: Stir-fry meat in hot oil until cooked.
Add broccoli, carrots and water chestnuts and water.
Cover and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Add prepared sauce or seasoning mix.
Heat through.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Mix in nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix lemon juice and milk and stir.
Fold in Cool Whip, fruit cocktail and nuts.
Pour into ready made graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate and let chill several hours before serving.
Makes 2 pies.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all together. Pour into pie shells and chill.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: molasses oatmeal bread
directions: Will need three 8 3/4 x 4 3/4 x 2 3/4-inch bread pans.

title: french toast
directions: Add the salt, milk and vanilla to the eggs.
Dip the bread into this mixture and brown on each side on a well-greased hot griddle or frying pan.
Serve hot.

title: penny pizzas
directions: Sift first 6 ingredients together. Stir in cheese, basil and oregano.
Cut shortening into flour mixture to make coarse crumbs. Add milk, tomato paste and unbeaten egg, stirring with fork until dough follows fork around bowl.
Knead on floured board 5 or 6 times.
Roll dough around wieners to form cup.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 350° until brown.
Yields 8 dozen.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter over low heat in a large frying pan. Saute chopped garlic, onion, chopped celery and sliced mushrooms.
Add flour, salt, pepper, white wine vinegar, sugar, bay leaf, paprika, chili powder and hot pepper sauce. Cook 5 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Add chopped tomatoes and liquid and simmer for 20 minutes. Add green pepper and shrimp to frying pan. Cover and simmer for an additional 10 minutes. Serve over hot rice. Serves 4.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup of the sugar, flour and salt in top of double boiler.
Add one whole egg and 3 yolks (whites for meringue). Stir in milk.
Cook, uncovered, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Layer mixture and wafers and banana slices in 1 1/2-quart casserole, ending with custard.
Beat whites with remaining sugar until stiff peaks. Pile on top of pudding surface.
Bake at 425° for 5 minutes or until browned.

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Make topping by mixing 1 stack crushed round crackers and melted margarine.
Spread topping on vegetables and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Precook chicken for 1 hour.
Remove skin and bones and slice meat 1/2-inch thick.
Thaw broccoli and place in bottom of a
9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Arrange chicken on broccoli.
Mix soup, lemon juice and mayo and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples and chop; set aside.
Put oil into large bowl. Add sugar, eggs and sifted flour mixture.
Cook at 375° until you can push on it and it will spring back.

title: asparagus and tomato salad
directions: Rinse asparagus thoroughly.
Gently bend each stalk until it snaps.
Stalks should break where the tough ends begin; discard tough ends.
Stand the stems upright in a double boiler or steamer over boiling water.
Steam for 10 to 12 minutes or until just tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Arrange on a platter.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all ingredients with browned and drained onions and meat. Serve over tortilla chips and top with grated cheese.

title: any cheese appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on bread rounds.
Sprinkle lightly with more cheese.
Brown under broiler.

title: coke salad
directions: Drain liquids from pineapple and cherries; save juices.
In a saucepan, combine juices and bring to a boil.
In separate bowl, combine packages of jello.
Pour boiling juices over jello; stir to dissolve.
Cool slightly.
Add cola to jello and mix well. Refrigerate until thick.
Add cream cheese, cherries, nuts and pineapple.
Fold in.
Return mixture to refrigerator until firm.

title: mildred's mom's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pack in loaf pan and cover top of loaf with the catsup or salsa.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.

title: master mix - bisquick
directions: Put in large bowl and mix until it looks like coarse cornmeal.
Makes 12 cups.
Use Bisquick recipes.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Beat eggs and add milk, salt, mustard and bread cubes. Stir with spoon. Add cheese and sausage.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate overnight.
Bake the next morning.
Bake glass dish in a 325° oven and a metal pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mushroom with sour cream
directions: Clean, wash, drain and slice mushrooms.
Cook onion in butter until wilted.
Add mushrooms and cook 10 minutes.
Blend flour with some of the cream to make a paste.
Stir in remaining cream; add to mushrooms.
Cook, stirring constantly, until it boils.
Add garlic and season to taste.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in dill.

title: pennsylvania dutch mashed potato filling
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and celery in as little water as possible.
Mash together potatoes, onion and celery with water they were cooked in.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add bread crumbs last, adding as much as necessary for desired thickness.
Bake in a buttered casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham with fruit stuffing
directions: Have the butcher bone the ham.
Combine fruit and wine in large mixing bowl; soak at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally. Fill the cavity of the boned ham with stuffing.
Bake in 350° oven for 2 1/2 hours.

title: doctored dill pickles
directions: Place pickles back in jar (rinsed jar).
Boil remaining ingredients for 15 minutes.
Pour over pickles; seal and let stand for 3 days.
Your pickles will be sweet and crispy.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Blend flour and Crisco.
Add beaten egg, vinegar and water. Mix well.
Makes enough dough for 2 double crust pies.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Rinse.
Keep in cold water while fixing vegetables.
Drain macaroni.
Add any amount of the vegetables.
Mix with lite Miracle Whip and Kraft coleslaw dressing.
Season with salt, pepper and celery seed.
Top with sliced, hard-boiled eggs.

title: blueberry-peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine muffin mix, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Cut in butter; stir in nuts.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, combine pie filling, 1/4 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and almond extract.
Spoon crumb mixture over peach mixture.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes, until topping is golden brown.
Serve with ice cream, if desired.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Put over low heat until chips melt, stirring frequently. Mix together other ingredients and add to first 3. Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° about 45 minutes.

title: spiced chicken wings
directions: Place wings in an ungreased wok; add wine.
Cook until almost all of the wine has evaporated.
Add water, cover and cook over medium-high heat for 10 minutes.
Add the star anise and cinnamon and cook, covered, about 5 minutes.
Then add the tamari, sugar and salt.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir often so they don't dry out.
You may need to add some (3 to 4 tablespoons) water.
Average cooking time is 45 minutes.

title: chunky applesauce
directions: Peel, core and slice apples. Combine apples and water in a Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. Cover. Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add cinnamon and nutmeg to apples. Cook, uncovered, over medium heat 10 minutes or until liquid is evaporated. Remove from heat. Stir in brown sugar. Let cool at least 30 minutes. Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Chop onion, garlic and bell pepper.
Brown in skillet with cooking oil.
Add ground beef and cook until done.
In large saucepan, mix mushroom pieces, tomato sauce, tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Add ground beef mixture and simmer for 2 hours.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Cream butter and sugars together, add eggs, pineapple and vanilla.
Stir in rest of dry ingredients until well blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: squash pickles
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Cover with ice water and let stand for 1 1/2 hours.
Mix together next 4 ingredients. Bring to a boil and let simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain squash mixture and add to liquid.
Let come to a boil and can.
Yield: 4 pint jars.

title: sheet cake with filling
directions: Mix flour, shortening, salt and baking powder like pie dough. Add egg and milk.
Roll 1/2 dough between wax paper, the size of a cookie sheet.
Invert on cookie sheet.
Spread with favorite filling.
Roll out other 1/2 of dough.
Cut into strips to make lattice work.
Place on top of filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: congo squares
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar.
Pour in melted butter.
Add flour (a little at a time).
Add nuts and chocolate morsels.
Press ingredients in greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add eggs, then the oil.
Mix well.
Do not beat.
Stir.
Add vanilla, pineapple, pecans and bananas and mix well.
Spoon into three 9-inch cake pans.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Add tomato soup, water, seasonings, corn and green pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients (potatoes, onion, broth and water). Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook about 30 additional minutes.
(Very good on a cold winter day!)

title: romy's spam dip
directions: Mix and serve in center of whole loaf of bread.

title: chocolate walnut buttercream
directions: Set a mixing bowl in a basin of simmering water.
Add the chocolate and the coffee; heat, stirring often, until chocolate is blended and melted.
Combine the yolks, salt and sugar in another bowl.
Set the bowl in a basin of simmering water and beat the yolk mixture rapidly with a wire whisk.
Beat until it falls in a "ribbon" when the whisk is lifted.
Spoon the chocolate into the yolk mixture.
Return the bowl to the simmering water and continue beating.
Gradually add the butter; beat.
Remove the bowl from the heat.
Continue beating until the mixture thickens and becomes spreadable.
Add walnuts.
Cool.
Spread over the 2 cakes. Decorate with the 12 large walnuts.

title: beef in wine and sour cream sauce
directions: Sprinkle meat with paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Rub in well.
Heat the butter in a very hot skillet.
Add the meat stirring to separate the pieces so that they cook evenly.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove meat with slotted spoon.
Add onion to skillet and cook, stirring about 1 minute.
Add the wine and cook down to reduce by about half.
Lower the heat and add the sour cream, stirring.
Do not allow the sauce to boil or sour cream will curdle.
Return meat to the skillet and stir to blend.
Add the sour pickles and mix in well.
Serve with rice, noodles or sauteed potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Gather together all ingredients.
Cream sugar, oil and eggs. Add vanilla, pumpkin and mix dry ingredients all together.
Add to other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes and take out of pan and cool.

title: raisin toffee bars
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Combine butter and sugar and mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in bran flakes and raisins.
Add flour mixture and stir thoroughly.
Spread in a well-greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Frost with your favorite icing. Let stand until set.
Cut into bars.

title: barbecue shredded beef
directions: In a large Dutch oven, mix together water, 1 cup barbecue sauce, beer and garlic.
Add meat and cook, covered, over medium heat 2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Remove meat and shred into 2-inch strips (against grain).
Place meat back into pan with 2 cups cooking broth and remaining barbecue sauce.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until most of the liquid is absorbed.
Serve on sandwich rolls.
Makes 4 to 6 large sandwiches.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet and add onion, ketchup, water, and seasonings.
Simmer 10 min.
Add pork and beans and heat thoroughly.
Layer meat mixture, rice, and chips in casserole. Top with cheese.
Bake in hot oven for 15 min.
It's great for a picnic.

title: jalapeno chicken bites
directions: Lay bacon strip out.
Lay small piece of chicken on bacon strip and 1 sliced jalapeno on top of it.
Roll bacon strip lengthwise into a ball.
Stick toothpick in it to hold.
Sprinkle with Cajun seasoning.
Deep fry until brown.
Serve with barbecue sauce.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan and cook 1 1/2 hours, slowly, on slow to medium heat.
Stir often to keep from sticking to pan. When it gets thick, put in sterile jars with tops and lids.

title: basic vanilla ice cream *
directions: Scald 1-quart and 22 ounces of milk.
Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add enough milk to this dry mixture to make a thin paste. Stir this into hot milk and cook over low heat until slightly thickened, about 15 minutes.
Stir to prevent sticking.

title: bottoms up cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread frosting into bottom of prepared pan.
Sprinkle nuts over frosting.
In large bowl, blend cake mix, water, oil and eggs until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Pour batter over frosting in pan.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken
and
debone.
Cook
spaghetti
in chicken broth and drain.
Mix together Cheez Whiz, soup, mushrooms and chicken. Add mixture to spaghetti.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish apple dessert
directions: Beat egg and sugar until light and fluffy. Mix flour with baking powder. Add with vanilla and salt to the beaten egg. Stir in apples and nuts. Spread into greased 8-inch pie plate. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix soup and mayonnaise in bowl.
Add chicken, celery, onions and 1 cup cheese; mix well.
Spoon into baking dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, carrots and onion. Mix margarine and herb dressing. Place half dressing mix in greased casserole. Add squash mix. Sprinkle remaining herb mix. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 12.

title: hamburger-noodle casserole
directions: Cook hamburg, sliced onion and green pepper.
Add soups, rice and noodles and juice noodles were cooked in.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in boiler.
Heat on top of stove until cheese melts and is well blended.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and let stand 5 minutes.
Combine yeast mixture, melted oleo and flour in a large bowl.
Mix well. Stir in beaten egg and sugar (mixture will be a soft batter). Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 16 rolls.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse shrimp and drain.
Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Serve on crackers or French bread.

title: quick coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in mixer.
Mix for 20 seconds.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Bake 1 hour.
It makes its own crust as it bakes.

title: sweet potato pie #1
directions: Separate eggs.
Put aside egg whites.
Add egg yolks and all other ingredients.
Beat egg whites until foamy and fold into mixture.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and salt in butter.
Combine with corn, eggs, muffin mix and cheese.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put remaining 1/2 cup cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Chop onion and celery; saute in butter until clear.
Cook broccoli as directed.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients with soup and cheese.
Pour into greased casserole; cook for 1 hour at 350° or until dry.

title: torteno di verdure(an italian vegetable casserole)
directions: Slice eggplant crosswise into 1/2-inch rounds.

Place on lightly oiled baking sheet. Bake, covered with foil, at 400° until tender (approximately 45 minutes). Slice potato and boil until tender. Drain. Slice zucchini into 1/4-inch rounds. Slice tomatoes 1/2-inch thick. Set aside.

title: pineapple-cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Mix well and chill. Shape into balls and roll in pecans.

title: cherry winks
directions: Mix as usual and roll a ball of dough in crushed flakes.
Top each with 1/4 of a cherry.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes.

title: angel food cake
directions: Add cream of tartar, salt and flavorings to egg whites.
Beat until stiff but not dry.
Add 1/2 cup sugar.
Sift remaining sugar and flour 5 times.
Fold into egg white mixture.
Bake in a tube pan at 375° for 35 to
40 minutes.
Turn upside-down on a glass bottle to cool.

title: scotch bars
directions: Cream butter, both sugars and vanilla thoroughly.
Add egg yolk and beat until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour and oats; blend well.
Spread in greased 7 x 11-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and allow to cool. Melt chocolate chips over hot water and stir until smooth.
Spread over baked cookie and sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into bars while still warm.
Chocolate will become firm.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Combine melted oleo, egg and cake mix.
Spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, 2 eggs, brown sugar, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat with mixer until smooth. Spread over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
When cool, cut into small squares and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter together until crumbly. Line pie shell with half of crumb mixture.
Mix pudding and pour in pie shell.
Sprinkle some crumbs on top of pudding.
Put Cool Whip on top and sprinkle remaining crumbs on top of Cool Whip.

title: crock-pot pork chops and gravy
directions: Place pork chops in crock-pot.
Add cream of mushroom soup over pork chops.
Cook until tender.
Thicken broth with flour or cornstarch and a little water to make a paste.

title: best cobbler crust
directions: Melt butter; combine rest of ingredients and pour over butter. Do not stir.
Add canned fruit and 3/4 cup sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: low-fat chicken pasta
directions: In a large frying pan, mix soup, water, onion, garlic and chicken.
Cook until hot and ingredients are done.
Toss with the pasta and serve hot.

title: my favorite party mix
directions: Melt almond bark in double boiler.
Pour over rest of ingredients to toss.
Cool in refrigerator.
Store in airtight container.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
For variety, you can add some small marshmallows or use a can of fruit cocktail or mandarin oranges.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, using two 8-inch or two 9-inch layers.
Let cool completely.
Use one of the cake pans as a mold for ice cream layer.
Line pan with plastic wrap, spoon or scoop in ice cream and smooth with knife.
Let ice cream harden in freezer.
Once ice cream is hardened, place it between cake layers on a serving dish that is freezer safe and has a cover for storing in freezer.
Use Cool Whip as icing.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix all together.
Cover and bake 2 hours.
Stir.
Cook another 2 hours in 250°
oven. Delicious stew.

title: unbelievable fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese in pan over low heat.
Stir constantly. Mix in vanilla.
Pour over mixture of powdered sugar and cocoa in bowl.
Mix quickly until well blended.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat pecans over top.

title: pineapple glazed ham
directions: Bake ham according to directions on the label.
In a saucepan, combine remaining ingredients and simmer for about 5 minutes.
For the last 30 minutes of baking the ham, turn the oven up to 400° and baste with the pineapple marinade every 10 minutes.

title: potato chicken casserole
directions: In greased casserole dish, mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over top; bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blackberry crisp
directions: Place blackberries in a greased 1-quart baking dish. In a small bowl, combine the sugar, cornstarch, water and lemon juice until smooth. Pour over berries. Combine the oats, flour, brown sugar and cinnamon; cut in butter until crumbly. Sprinkle over berries. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until filling is bubbly. Serve warm with ice cream. Yield: 2 servings.

title: marian's cauatine(makes a lot)
directions: Brown meat and pepper slowly; add sauce.
Cook macaroni, then mix together in large bowl.
Pour layer of pasta in large baking dish, layer of sauce, layer of cheese
and layer of pepperoni. Repeat process; end with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Mix together as crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: rice krispie bars
directions: Melt sugar, Karo syrup and peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies; mix well!
Spread in jelly roll pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips together; spread on top of bars.

title: berry good thumbprint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream together shortening, butter and brown sugar.
