Add egg yolks and vanilla; blend well.
Add 2 cups flour (one cup at a time) and salt. Combine until a soft dough forms.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into beaten egg whites; roll in chopped walnuts.
Place 1 inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake cookies 5 minutes. Remove from oven; quickly, but gently press thumb into top of each cookie.
Return to oven; bake 8 minutes longer.
Cool on a wire rack.
Place a scant teaspoon of jam in each thumbprint.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: Cream oleo and peanut butter together.
Gradually add powdered sugar and mix by hand.
Form into balls and put on waxed paper. In top of double boiler melt chocolate chips and parawax.
Drop balls in chocolate and cover well.
Put back on waxed paper to set.

title: classic creamed corn au grautin
directions: Combine corn, cream, salt, sugar and white pepper in a pot and bring to a boil. Simmer 5 minutes. Make a roux from butter and flour. Add to corn and mix well.
Remove from heat. Serves 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Fill the bottom with pineapple, then add pie filling.
Pour cake mix over this and top with chopped nuts and butter squares.
Let cool and serve out of pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (can be used with any pie filling).

title: banana spice bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonfat cooking spray.
Stir flour, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and lite salt into a medium size bowl.
Stir in oat bran; set aside. In another medium size bowl, beat together the Egg Beaters, brown sugar and liquid Butter Buds.
Add bananas.
Add dry ingredients to banana mixture; beat until just combined.
Pour into prepared loaf pan.
Bake in oven for 50 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool on a wire rack.
Yields 1 loaf (12 slices).

title: incredibly easy chile rellenos
directions: Wash chiles and remove seeds.
Wrap chile strips around cheese strips.
Place side by side in a shallow 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Beat eggs with salt, then add milk and mix well.
Pour over stuffed chilies.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Do not overbake since it toughens the protein in both eggs and cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sour cream chicken supreme
directions: Saute onion in margarine in large skillet.
Add chicken pieces a few at a time and brown on both sides.
Add seasonings.
Add broth and simmer 20 minutes.
Add sour cream and heat thoroughly. Put eggs and pimento on top.
Serve on rice.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large
bowl
cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Crumble and stir
in mincemeat.
Drop from teaspoon 2
inches
apart
onto greased baking sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12
minutes
or
until lightly browned.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef, seasoned to taste with salt and pepper in melted butter (if needed).
Add mushrooms, onions and garlic; cook over low heat for 3 or 4 minutes, until onion is soft.
Add flour to pan; stir in.
Blend in tomato paste.
Gradually stir in beef broth.
Cook, stirring, over medium heat.
Stir in sour cream; cook only until heated through.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot, buttered noodles or rice.

title: chicken stew
directions: Stew chicken in 2 to 3 quarts water until bones can be easily removed, about 2 1/4 hours.
To reduce fat, chill broth until fat rises to top and skim off.
Combine boned chicken, broth and all other ingredients in stew pot and simmer until all is tender, stirring occasionally.
Add water, as necessary.
Longer, slower cooking makes it best.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Combine 1 cup water and raisins in saucepan; bring to boil. Cook for 5 minutes; cool.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add vanilla, raisin mixture and nuts.
Sift dry ingredients together; blend into creamed mixture.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
5 dozen.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except stuffing.
Dip chicken into mix and then dip in stuffing.
Pour 1 cup melted butter or margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until crunchy.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Rinse chickens and pat dry with paper towels.
Sprinkle flour lightly over both sides of pieces and salt and pepper to taste. Heat olive oil in nonstick skillet and fry chicken until golden on all sides.
Remove chicken as you fry it and put into oven-proof casserole or baking pan.
In same skillet, add onions and garlic to the olive oil and fry until golden.
Add mushrooms (drained, if using canned), then add tomato sauce and white wine.
Add more salt and pepper to taste, oregano and parsley, also.
Cook over medium heat until well blended, about 20 minutes.
Add olives.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good served with Risotto.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Boil carrots until tender. Cool and slice.
Alternate layer of carrots, pepper rings and onion rings in a dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour over veggies and refrigerate.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix vegetables in a bowl.

title: mom's cinnamon rolls
directions: Warm milk and water; add sugar and yeast.
Stir until yeast dissolves.
Add 2 cups flour and beat until smooth.
Leave in warm place 20 minutes or 1 hour.
Add sugar, shortening, warm water, 3 1/2 cups flour and salt.
Use a big spoon to mix.
Set back and let rise until double.
Punch down; roll out and spread with butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up into long roll; cut off 1-inch pieces. Place, spaced apart, in greased pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 350°.

title: perky hash brown casserole
directions: Pour melted butter over potatoes.
In another bowl, mix rest of ingredients except corn flakes.
Stir in potatoes.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and pour over 2 cups crushed corn flakes.
Toss thoroughly and spread over potato casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cabbage and green peppers.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over slaw and freeze.

title: maple nut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars; add flavorings and eggs, beating well after each.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in oats and nuts. Drop by teaspoon onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 14 dozen.

title: ye-ole famous peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook until it forms a soft ball.
Stir until the oleo melts. Then add 1 cup peanut butter.
Stir good until it starts to thicken and put in a buttered pan.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour, salt and sugar.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour mixture all at once.
Blend with spoon just until flour is all moistened and holds together.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and marinate for 24 hours.
Will keep for weeks in refrigerator.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, oil and 1 egg until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup of mix and pat the rest lightly into an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth.
Spread over baked mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup crumb mixture.
Bake 15 more minutes at 350°.

title: water whip pastry
directions: Put shortening in mixing bowl.
Add boiling water and milk and whip with a fork until all liquid is absorbed and a thick smooth mixture is formed.
Sift flour and salt into shortening whip and stir quickly into a dough.
Pick up and work until smooth.
Yield: pastry for a two crust pie.

title: sandy's snickerdoodles
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Roll in small walnut size balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° to 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Place rice in 13 x 9-inch dish lined with aluminum foil.
Add chicken.
Combine soups and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Seal foil securely over dish.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Can also be cooked in slow cooker all day.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch cake pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Layer coconut and chopped pecans in prepared pan.
Prepare cake mix, using package directions.
Pour over layers.

title: kindergarten play doh
directions: Mix flour, salt, cornstarch and cream of tartar in 2-quart glass bowl; gradually stir in water and oil until just about smooth.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 4 1/2 to 5 minutes or until mixture is very thick, stirring every minute (mixture will be very lumpy).
Cool enough to handle.
Knead until smooth, about 2 minutes.

title: peanut butter milk shake
directions: Place ingredients in a blender container.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 2 servings.

title: tuna cashew casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except noodles.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°. Sprinkle noodles on top.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat with onions and peppers.
Drain well.
Return to large sauce pan and add all other ingredients.
Simmer on low for 1 to 2 hours.
Watch closely, it can burn to the bottom of the pan easily.
Will freeze well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar and oil.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and powder, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add zucchini and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pans until about 2/3 full.
Makes 2 loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: german lebkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spread out on 4 cookie sheets that have been oiled, about 1/4-inch thick. Cook at 350° for 10 to 13
minutes. Take out of oven and pour this mixture over hot cookies.

title: chicken stir-fry over rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Saute chicken, onion and garlic in oil until chicken is browned, about 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add broth mixed with soup and veggies. Bring to a boil. add additional salt, pepper or other herbs while hot.
Fold in rice or spread over rice. (May vary choice of veggies as desired.)
Serves 4.

title: mixed veggie pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Drain; set aside.
Spray a large skillet with nonfat cooking spray.
Heat skillet; add chicken broth, broccoli, carrots, zucchini and onions.
Saute 4 minutes.
Add peppers and mushrooms.
Saute 4 more minutes.
Add pasta, tomato and white wine.
Stir lightly. Cook until heated.
Sprinkle with cheese, parsley and pepper flakes.
Serve right away.

title: scottish oat scones
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, rolled oats, sugar, baking powder, cream of tartar and salt.
Rub in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in raisins.
Add milk and egg.
Mix until just moist.

title: ida bemis' apple cobbler
directions: Cut apples up and place in bottom of buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Mix together the other ingredients; spread on apples.
(The mixture is "gooey" and won't spread perfectly.)
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: scratch cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, Crisco, eggs and 3/4 cup milk.
Beat until smooth.
Add remaining milk and vanilla; beat 2 minutes.
Pour in baking pans and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 layers.

title: easy and delicious wieners
directions: Place all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Turn on medium-high and cook for 1 1/2 hours.
Don't overcook.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy; add baking powder and salt. Continue beating until creamy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Then add crushed Ritz crackers and cut up pecans.
Add vanilla last. Grease a pie pan well.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tortellini and garden vegetable bake
directions: Cook tortellini in boiling salted water according to package directions, adding the carrot during the last 5 minutes of cooking and the sugar snap peas during the last 1 minute of cooking; drain.

title: shrimp macaroni salad
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients. Blend mayonnaise, mustard and salt. Toss slightly. Chill. Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: lemon pie filling
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar together.
Add it and lemon juice to beaten egg yolks.
Pour water on this mixture.
Place in double boiler and stir and cook until thickened.
Add butter.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.
Makes 1 pie.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream together the oleo, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Add and beat well the peanut butter, vanilla and corn syrup.
Add and mix well the uncooked oats, baking soda and salt.
Add and stir by hand the M&M's and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: philadelphia cheesecake brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package. Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Beat cream cheese with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth. Add sugar, mixing until blended. Add egg and vanilla; mix just until blended. Pour cream cheese mixture over brownie mixture. Cut through batter with knife several times for marble effect. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cream cheese mixture is lightly browned. Cool and then cut into squares.

title: texas rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 2-quart dish.
Saute onion in butter.
Add other ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 minutes.

title: sweet cereal mix
directions: Mix cereal, nuts and coconut in large bowl.
Cook butter, brown sugar and Karo in saucepan.
Bring to boil for 2 minutes; stir constantly.
Add syrup mixture to cereal mixing well.
Put on greased jelly roll pan and bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Put on wax paper to cool.

title: ice cream sundae topping
directions: Melt slowly butter, brown sugar, marshmallows and salt.
Take off stove and add 1 cup cream, vanilla and nuts.

title: fancy meringue kisses
directions: Beat egg whites and add sugar gradually.
Add the salt and vanilla.
Fold in carefully the dates and nuts.
The mixture will be quite stiff.
Then drop from teaspoon upon a well-greased cookie sheet.
Place a candied cherry on top.

title: texas jalapeno pepper jelly
directions: Put the peppers in a food processor on chop; chop finely.
In a large kettle, put the peppers with cider vinegar and pectin.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Bring to a boil.
Add 6 cups white sugar. Bring to a rolling boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Put in sterilized pint jars and seal with sterilized lids and rings.

title: low-fat banana pudding
directions: Mix together pudding, milk and sour cream. Layer Pyrex dish with cookies, pudding and then bananas with pudding as top layer. Garnish with Cool Whip if desired.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender in salted water.
Drain. Combine carrots, onion and green pepper.
Set aside.
Combine soup, vinegar, oil, sugar and mustard.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss lightly with fork.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Bring all ingredients, except vanilla and oatmeal to a hard boil for 1 minute.
Take off burner.
Pour in oatmeal.
Mix well. Place by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: dried beef dip in pumpernickel bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread until well blended.
Cut out a large cavity in the center of the bread.
Put the piece of bread that was cut out to the side.
Fill the cavity with the cream cheese mixture.
Place the loaf of bread with the cream cheese mixture into a preheated 350° oven.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Remove and place on serving tray.
Cut up the bread that was put to the side into dipping-size cubes.
Place these cubes around the loaf of bread.
After these cubes are gone, encourage the guests to tear off pieces of the bread bowl and keep on dipping until gone. Delicious, and have fun dipping!

title: rum balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into small balls. Roll into powdered sugar. Store in an airtight container.

title: brownies
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Blend butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Add nuts to batter or spread on top. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes in a well-greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or glass baking dish.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Fit pastry into pie plate.
Break crackers coarsely into pastry lined plate.
Combine water, sugar and cream of tartar in saucepan. Boil gently for 15 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Cool.
Pour syrup over crackers.
Dot generously with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with top crust.
Trim and flute edges together. Cut slits in top crust to let steam escape.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes until crust is crisp and golden.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Cook tomatoes first and drain off as much juice as you can into a container.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook until tender, adding tomato juice, if needed. Put in hot jars and seal (with hot lids).

title: cousin melissa's oyster fritters
directions: Mix milk and oil; stir flour into it to make a fritter batter. Stir until smooth.
Beat egg white stiff. Fold egg whites, salt and pepper into batter. Put drained oysters into batter.
Have oil for frying deep and hot.
Dip up a spoonful of batter, making sure it contains an oyster and drop into the hot fat.
Fry several at a time but do not crowd them. Drain on paper towels and serve at once.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Blend all ingredients with 1/3 cup catsup.
Place in ungreased shallow casserole dish.
Cover top with 1/4 cup catsup and bread crumbs.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven until browned.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix beans, sprouts, water chestnuts and soup.
Pour into a baking dish and dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Spread onion rings over top and bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: one pan goulash
directions: Brown meat, onion and macaroni until meat loses its color. Add tomato sauce, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer about 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and add other ingredients.
Mix well and pour into greased dish.

title: chinese chicken stock
directions: Put chicken in large stockpot. Place over medium heat. Toss in green onions, garlic, ginger, halved onion and white peppercorn. Pour 3 quarts cold water to cover chicken. Simmer gently for 1 hour, skimming off the foam on the surface periodically. Carefully remove from pot and pass the stock through a strainer lined with cheesecloth to remove the solids and excess fat. Great for noodle soup or egg drop soup.

title: chocolate wafers
directions: In a medium bowl, sift together the flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; set aside. In the bowl of an electric mixer, cream butter, vanilla and sugar; add eggs and milk. Mix until thoroughly blended. Add reserved flour mixture, scraping sides of the bowl. Divide the dough in half and shape into a flat disk. Wrap each disk in plastic wrap, then chill until firm.

title: chocolate butter frosting
directions: Melt the chocolate in the top of a double boiler over barely simmering water.
Cool to room temperature.
Place the butter in a large bowl and beat with an electric mixer until fluffy, about 1 minute.
Gradually beat in the sugar alternately with the eggs and vanilla.
Beat in the cooled chocolate to make a frosting of good spreading consistency.
Use at room temperature.
The frosting will set if chilled.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in well-greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Empty can of asparagus into shallow baking dish. Cover with mushroom soup after the chopped pimentos have been mixed with the asparagus.
Cover with Ritz crackers and sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° until crackers are brown (about 20 minutes).

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: In nonstick pan, pour teriyaki sauce and add chicken breast. Rotate chicken as it cooks.
After chicken is done, add pineapple rings to top on each breast and baste with teriyaki sauce, simmering 5 minutes more.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4 people.

title: quick chicken
directions: Skin and wash chicken pieces.
Fry quickly.
Drain.
Put in slow cooker on low.
Mix 1 can cream of chicken soup with 1/2 cup of water.
Pour over chicken.
Cook on low 6 hours.

title: willie's homemade chili mac
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Brush large skillet with small amount of fat.
Add ground beef and onion.
Cook until browned.
Add macaroni, a cup of water, chili powder, salt, sugar and beans.
Cover; simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese; place over low heat until cheese melts.
Yield:
5 to 6 servings.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Soak in brine solution (Morton Tender Quick) for 24 to 48 hours.
Wash, then smoke on medium heat for 3 to 4 hours.
Skin and dice into cubes.
Serve on Ritz crackers and cream cheese spread.

title: sloppy joes for 80
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Drain and set aside.
In large skillet, cook hamburger, stirring constantly, until browned.
Drain well.
Using large kettle, combine hamburger, onion and pepper.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer 1 hour.
(Best if made day ahead.
Remove all solidified fat before reheating.)
Quick cool in ice bath before refrigerating.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: tortilla dessert
directions: Spoon 1-2 tablespoons into flour tortillas. Roll up and place in large baking dish, open side down.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix all ingredients with beaters for 20 minutes.
Take cheese cake pan and grease with butter.
Place a thick coat of graham cracker crumbs and pour in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Turn off oven and let stand 1 hour.

title: minestrone and meatball soup
directions: Mix first five ingredients together for the meatballs.
Pour remaining onion soup mix in large kettle.
Add the canned tomatoes and also fill each can with water.
Add to tomatoes.
Bring to a boil and drop in small meatballs.
Let simmer for 30 minutes. Then add the vegetables and simmer another 20 minutes.
(You can also add another package of dried onion soup mix if you like.)

title: caramel corn
directions: In 2 1/2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup, butter, cream of tartar and salt.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly, to hard boil stage (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda quickly, but thoroughly.

title: duch lettuce
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce; add to bacon and heat just to boiling, stirring constantly.
Tear lettuce into pieces; pour hot dressing over and toss lightly.
Serves 4.

title: mexican cabbage
directions: Brown ground meat, bell pepper, onion, garlic and cumin in a Dutch oven; drain off fat.
Add soup, Ro-Tel and tomatoes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Add cabbage; cover and simmer 45 minutes or until cabbage is done.

title: easy grasshopper pie(or dessert)
directions: Mix and press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate, or press into bottom of square baking dish.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients and form meatballs.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop cucumbers and onions; put 1/2 cup of salt over them.
Let stand 45 minutes until it makes a brine; drain.
Mix all other ingredients; pour over cucumbers and onions.
Cook over medium heat until it changes color.
Pack into jars and seal.
Makes around 12 quarts according to size of cucumbers and onions.

title: country rice with shrimp
directions: In a deep skillet heat oil; stir in rice, stirring occasionally until rice is golden (2 to 3 minutes).
Stir in chicken broth and ginger root.
Continue until mixture comes to full boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; continue cooking until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Stir in all remaining ingredients except onion.
Continue cooking until shrimp turns pink, stirring occasionally.
Stir in onion and cook 2 to 3 minutes, then serve. Yields 5 to 6 servings.

title: baked carrots
directions: Place carrots in buttered 4-cup casserole. Season with sugar, salt and pepper.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Cover.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: applesauce banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put bananas in bowl and mash with mixer. Mix in sugar. Let set 15 minutes. Add applesauce and eggs and beat well. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Put in 9 x 5 loaf pan sprayed with nonstick spray and bake 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: butterscotch oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar, egg, water and vanilla until creamy.
Add combined remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Add chips last.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Add Italian dressing and seasoning.
Mix and add other ingredients according to taste. Toss well and chill.

title: cucumbers and onions in sour cream
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers.
Peel and slice onion and separate rings.
Place onion rings in ice water for 20 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix sour cream with vinegar.
Add sour cream mixture to the cucumbers and onions about 30 minutes before serving.
Salt to taste.
Refrigerate.

title: easy red velvet two layer cake
directions: Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Pastry:
Roll half very thin and use it to line a 2-inch deep baking pan.
Roll other half thin and cut into 2-inch strips. Bake half the strips in a preheated 375° oven until lightly browned.

title: maple drops
directions: Mix all together. Heat oven to 350°.
Drop by level tablespoon about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 10 minutes. Remove and cool. Frost with maple frosting.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: In an ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan, break bacon strips into smaller pieces and cover bottom.
In a large bowl, put soup and milk and stir with a whisk until smooth.
Stir in rice and seasoning.
Add chicken and mix well.
Pour over bacon and smooth out.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: honeymooner's hamburger beans
directions: Cook hamburger in small amount of water, stirring to break into very small pieces.
Pour into a colander and wash with hot water to get the fat out.
Return to rinsed pan.
Add onion, green pepper, ketchup and beans.
Cover and simmer until green pepper and onion are cooked.
Add brown sugar and red and black pepper to taste. Cook for 10 minutes or so more.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed, place in air tight container, place in refrigerator over night.
To use roll out or pinch off as much as needed.
Use all at once or a little at a time.
Will keep up to two weeks in refrigerator.
Bake at 400 until brown (about 10 minutes).

title: coconut bonbons
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate and wax.
Turn down to simmer.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and roll into firm little balls.
Dip into chocolate and place on wax paper.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet or Dutch oven over medium heat until bacon is crisp.
Remove and drain.
Pour off excess fat, reserving 3 tablespoons drippings.
Add onion, garlic, green pepper and gumbo file to bacon drippings and cook, stirring constantly, until vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and blend in flour; return to heat and cook over low heat 1 minute.
Stir in tomatoes and puree.
Add remaining ingredients except shrimp and cook over moderate heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add shrimp and crumbled bacon.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer until shrimp are tender.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken breasts in wine
directions: Place chicken in baking dish, cheese slices on top.
Pour soup and vermouth over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing over top and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: day ahead chicken
directions: Chicken may be skinned, if preferred.
Place chicken snugly in baking dish, skin side down.
Mix honey, mustard, curry and soy sauce.
Pour over chicken and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight, covered.
Turn chicken skin side up.
Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Baste well with sauce and continue baking, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Spoon sauce over chicken and serve.
Serves 4.

title: corn bread supreme
directions: Emma Dawkins, wife
of P. W., the Agricultural Teacher, teamed with him
to
teach the girl students and their mothers how to cook and preserve the vegetables from the farm.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Combine crushed pretzels, butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Press onto bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sheet cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Glaze with powdered sugar and milk icing while still hot.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add soup, milk, Cheese Whiz, then broccoli, rice, salt and pepper.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tasty taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Unroll dough, press onto bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick bottom and sides with fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cover crust with meat mixture, top with cheese spread. Continue baking until cheese begins to melt.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with sour cream, if desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Preperation time 15 minutes.
Baking time 15 minutes.

title: brazilian rice
directions: In a 4-quart pot, heat the oil over the medium-high heat and stir-fry the onion and garlic until golden.
Pour in the rice and stir for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the water, bay leaf, tomatoes and salt.

title: mud fish stew
directions: Brown fatback first and then bacon.
Add onion and brown.
Add ketchup and enough water to get thickness desired.
Add tomato paste.
Add teaspoon of black pepper.
Add 1/2 teaspoon hot sauce. Bring to a boil.
Add 1 tablespoon salt.
Add fish, cut in small pieces.
Cook about 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin sheet cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together and pour onto a large cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°

title: relish, farm style
directions: Pour 1 cup salt over the first six ingredients.
Cover with water and let stand overnight.

title: beef jerky
directions: Partially freeze meat and then slice into 1/8-inch wide and 4-inch long strips.
Combine other ingredients.
Mix with beef strips in glass bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Lay in single layers on a broiler pan.
Bake at 140° to 150° for 12 to 14 hours.
Blot with paper towel.

title: snow white taffy
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and stir until sugar is dissolved. Cook without stirring to very firm ball stage.
Remove from heat; add flavoring.
Pour into well greased shallow pan.
When cool enough to handle, pull until white and firm.
Roll into rope and cut with scissors or knife.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: In large saucepan, over medium-high heat, cook carrots, onions and garlic in margarine until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add ginger, curry, cinnamon and nutmeg; cook for 1 minute.
Add squash and apple juice.
Heat to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes or until squash is tender. In blender or food processor container, puree soup, in batches, until smooth.
Return to saucepan; heat through.
Serve hot or chilled with crackers. Makes 8 servings.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Cream the butter and shortening together until light and fluffy. Add vanilla and gradually cream in sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nanny linda's pizza and sauce
directions: For the dough, mix the first five ingredients together and let rise until doubled in size.
Makes enough for 2 pizzas.

title: cream cheese and chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and pecans first.
Add chicken, celery, salt and pepper.
Stir all together well.

title: no cholesterol chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and dust with flour.
Put everything in a large bowl and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
May be glazed if you like.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Dice 6 slices of bacon; brown and remove from pan.
Brown beef; cut in 4-inch strips.
Put aside.
Flame 2 tablespoons brandy.
Saute garlic cloves, mushrooms and white onions.

title: big mama's tea cakes
directions: Mix everything well.
Press onto large sheet pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned around edges, 10 to 12 minutes.
May be rolled and cut, or use cookie molds.
A great cookie if rolled thin and cut for a children's cookie decorating party.
Taste great.

title: pudding pumpkin bread(breakfast)
directions: Grease and flour 2 full size loaf pans.
In a large mixer bowl sift flour, salt, soda and spices.
Stir in pudding mix. Make a well in center and add beaten eggs, sugar, oil, pumpkin and vanilla.
Beat on medium until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Do not overbeat.
Fill the pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Will make 6 small loaves if you wish.

title: helenann's liver pate
directions: Saute chicken livers in margarine.
Set aside to cool.
Put other 6 ingredients in blender to blend.
Put livers and juices through fine grinder.
Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Stuff pieces of celery ribs or serve with crackers.

title: tuna casserole(my children's favorite)
directions: Add milk to rest of ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cover for the first 20 minutes.

title: aunt bill's brown candy
directions: Combine 2 cups sugar and milk in saucepan and cook slowly. Put 1 cup sugar in heavy iron skillet and put over low heat. Begin stirring with wooden spoon and keep sugar moving so it won't scorch.
Takes about 30 minutes to melt sugar.
At not time, let smoke so it will darken.
It should be about the color of light brown syrup.
Begin pouring in pan of milk and sugar; keep very low heat.
Stir constantly.

title: dog biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients, adding only enough water to hold ingredients together to form a dough that can be rolled and cut. Roll 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into small dog bone shapes.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: stained glass jello salad
directions: Add 1 cup hot water and 1/2 cup cold water to each of the lime, orange and cherry gelatins in separate 8-inch square pans. Chill overnight.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange potatoes in layers in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle each layer with onion, salt and pepper.
Dot with margarine or butter.
Pour hot milk over top. Bake, uncovered, for about 1 1/2 hours until tender.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Prepare pastry for two-crust pie.
In saucepan mix sugar, flour, salt, cranberries and water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly; boil and stir 5 minutes or until cranberries pop. Remove from heat; stir in extract.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan. Cover with top crust; seal and flute.
Cover edge with 2 to 3 inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Remove foil last 10 minutes of baking.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll dough into 1/2 to 1-inch balls. Put on cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly and put almond on top and bake at 250° for 10 minutes or according to your oven.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Beat egg whites in small bowl.
In a large bowl, mix 2/3 cup cocoa and cornstarch.
Put 3/4 cup milk into cocoa mixture.
In
a large heavy saucepan, bring to boil on high heat, whisking constantly.
Remove pan from heat.
Mix cocoa mixture into hot milk mixture.
Boil on medium-high heat. Boil 2 minutes.
Remove pan from heat.
Whisk 1 cup hot cocoa mixture into egg whites. Pour mixture into pan.
Cook on medium-low heat 2 minutes. Do not boil. Remove pan from heat. Add vanilla. Blend well.
Pour pudding into serving dishes. Cool to room temperature. Cover and chill 1 hour. Garnish with cocoa.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut squash in half; remove seeds.
Place cut side down in a shallow pan; add 1/2-inch water to pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Discard water; turn squash cut side up.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine honey, butter, Worcestershire sauce and raisins.
Spoon into squash.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies (2)
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add orange juice, orange peel and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients, then add the oatmeal.
Stir.
If desired, add;
cinnamon, dates, raisins or nut meats.
These are moist and flavorful. A very old recipe.
Bake at 375° for 12-15 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
In a buttered casserole, make 2 to 3 layers of macaroni, corned beef, onion and cheese.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over layers.
Scatter buttered crumbs on top. Bake at 350° until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 1 cup juice.
Combine remaining fruit and nuts in large bowl.
Toss gently.
Mix pineapple juice and pudding.
Beat on high for one minute.
Pour pudding mix over fruit and pecans; toss gently.

title: blueberry skillet cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat into margarine mixture alternating with milk.
Stir in almond.
Mix 1 teaspoon almond in pie mix.
Spoon into bottom of ungreased 10-inch heavy skillet.
Carefully spread cake batter over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or when cake springs back.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn out on plate.

title: great potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes. Put everything but corn flakes together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix as listed, except for chocolate chips and the powdered sugar and shaved chocolate mixture.
Add chocolate chips last. Bake in tube pan or Bundt pan at 350° for approximately 50 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
After removing from pan, sprinkle with 1/4 cup shaved German chocolate and 1/4 cup powdered sugar that has been mixed together.

title: tomato jam
directions: First, prepare tomatoes.
Scald, peel and chop about 2 1/4 pounds fully ripe tomatoes.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Measure 3 cups into a large saucepan.
Add lemon rind, lemon juice and cut up lemon pieces.
To the measured fruit in the saucepan, add the sugar.
Mix well.
Place over high heat; bring to a full, rolling boil and boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; at once stir in Certo fruit pectin. Skim off foam with metal spoon, then stir and skim for 5 minutes to cool slightly to prevent floating fruit.
Ladle into glasses. Cover at once with 1/8-inch hot paraffin.

title: easy boiled custard
directions: Mix in blender or with mixer all ingredients. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chilled corn salad
directions: Mix sour cream, mayo, beef broth and vinegar together.
In a medium bowl mix all other ingredients and pour mixture over vegetables.
Mix well and chill until serving time.

title: sour cream lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, lemon rind, juice, egg yolks and milk in heavy saucepan; cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir	in butter and cool mixture to room temperature.
Stir in
sour
cream	and
pour filling into pie shell.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cheesy oven omelet
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 x 8-inch cake pan with the butter.
In a large bowl, beat the next 6 ingredients together. Stir in the Bac*Os, cheese and scallions.
Pour in pan.
Bake, uncovered, 35 minutes or until center is set and puffy.
Serves 6.

title: sugar-free banana nut bread
directions: Mix mashed bananas, oil, egg and sweetener.
Add dry ingredients.
Last, stir in nuts and raisins.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 or 40 minutes.

title: polish russian dill pickles(hot)
directions: Boil all but cukes for 3 minutes.
Put cukes in jars; pour hot mixture over bottled cukes and seal as for regular dills.
Add extra garlic and fresh hot pepper per jar for extra dip, if desired.
Process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Mix cheese with sausage.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Add to sausage and cheese.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: maria's pizza bread(by special request from friends who have eaten it)
directions: Note:
Use fresh herbs when in season!

title: louisiana seafood gumbo
directions: Make roux of oil and flour, stirring constantly, until dark brown.
Add shrimp to roux and cook for a few minutes.
Set aside.
Smother okra and onions in oil.
Add tomatoes and garlic when okra is almost done.
Cook a few minutes longer, then add water and salt and pepper.
Combine shrimp roux mixture with okra and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Add oysters, crabmeat and whole crabs; simmer until crabs are cooked.
Add parsley and green onions; simmer another 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve over rice and let each person add fresh file to their taste.

title: surprise company appetizer
directions: Cut wonton wrappers in circles small enough to fit mini muffin tins.
Bake wrappers for 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Heat all remaining ingredients together in saucepan.
Spoon sauce into baked wrappers.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Mix together and press into a greased pan (I use a 9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes (until brown).
Let cool.

title: fat-free mexican corn fritters
directions: Combine dry ingredients and stir thoroughly.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix.
Spray skillet with butter flavor nonstick cooking spray and warm over medium heat.
Drop medium-size spoonfuls of batter into skillet.
Brown on one side, burn and brown on the other side.
Repeat for remaining batter.

title: creamy broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, heat margarine until bubbly and hot; add onion and saute briefly (do not brown).
Add flour and stir quickly to thoroughly combine; remove from heat and gradually stir in milk, stirring until thoroughly blended.
Return to heat and cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is thick and creamy, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in salt and pepper.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix sugar, egg yolks, flour and cocoa; add milk.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Add margarine and vanilla; mix well. Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie crusts.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1 tablespoon vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour on top of pie.
Brown in oven at 250°.
Let set in oven until pie won't run.

title: aunt myrtle's soft cookies
directions: Cream sugars, oleo and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add all together.
Beat eggs and work in.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet by tablespoon.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes until lightly brown at 350°.

title: mama gage's dumplings
directions: Sift flour and baking powder with salt.
Mix in shortening. Mix with cold water to biscuit-like dough.
Roll thin and cut in 1 x 2-inch strips.
Drop in boiling chicken broth, cover and cook for 15 minutes or until tender.

title: buttermilk crescent rolls
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and soda to yeast.
Heat buttermilk, water and margarine to 120°.
Add dry ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup flour.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in more flour to make soft dough.
On floured board, knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Place in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double in size.
Punch down.
On floured board roll into 2 circles. Brush with margarine.
Cut each into 12 triangles.
Roll up each. Seal.
Put on greased baking sheet and curve.
Let rise 1 hour. Bake in 350° oven.

title: easiest chicken and dumpling recipe ever
directions: Fill large pot 1/2 to 2/3 full with water. Add chicken broth and chicken. Bring to a boil. Mix together Bisquick and milk. Stir (mixture may be a little lumpy). Drop mixture by spoonful into boiling water. Reduce heat to medium and continue boiling, uncovered, for 10 minutes and then cover and cook 10 more minutes.

title: firehouse casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage (add salt and pepper).
Drain off grease.
In casserole dish, mix together meat, soups and cooked shellroni. Cover completely with grated cheese.
Heat in hot oven until cheese melts.
Goes good with Texas toast. Serves 6 people or 2 firemen.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased hot cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.

title: colic helper or how to quiet a colicy baby
directions: Put baby in battery operated swing.
Turn on swing.
Put vacuum cleaner very near baby.
Turn on vacuum.
If no positive results, place baby in padded laundry basket.
Place laundry basket on top of dryer while clothes are drying, being careful to watch baby at all times to prevent basket from being vibrated off dryer.

title: school rolls
directions: Mix warm water, yeast, salt, sugar and shortening in mixing bowl.
Stir until sugar is dissolved and everything is mixed well. Let set and rise until it gets bubbly.
Add flour enough so dough will handle good, but not stiff.
Mix for about 5 minutes or so. Let stand until it rises and doubles in bulk.
Roll out about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut and put in greased sheet.
Let rise again until doubled.
Cook at 350° until done.
